55 /* this macro is used to make sure that heap file identifier is initialized
56  * properly that heap file scan routines will work properly.
57  */
58 #define UT_CAST_TO_NULL_HEAP_OID(hfidp,oidp) \
59  do \
60  { \
61  (oidp)->pageid = NULL_PAGEID; \
62  (oidp)->volid = (hfidp)->vfid.volid; \
63  (oidp)->slotid = NULL_SLOTID; \
64  } \
65  while (0)

69 /* ISS_RANGE_DETAILS stores information about the two ranges we use
70  * interchangeably in Index Skip Scan mode: along with the real range, we
71  * use a "fake" one to obtain the next value for the index's first column.
72  *
73  * ISS_RANGE_DETAILS tries to completely encapsulate one of these ranges, so
74  * that whenever the need arises, we can "swap" them. */
75 typedef struct iss_range_details ISS_RANGE_DETAILS;
76 struct iss_range_details
77 {
78  int key_cnt;
79  KEY_RANGE *key_ranges;
80  SCAN_PRED key_pred;
81  RANGE_TYPE range_type;
82  int part_key_desc; /* last partial key domain is descending */
83 };
84

195 /*
196  * scan_init_iss () - initialize index skip scan structure
197  * return: error code
198  * isidp: pointer to index scan id structure that contains iss structure
199  */
200 int
201 scan_init_iss (INDX_SCAN_ID * isidp)
202 {
203  DB_VALUE *last_key = NULL;
204  INDEX_SKIP_SCAN *iss = NULL;
205 
206  if (isidp == NULL)
207  {
208  assert_release (false);
209  er_set (ER_FATAL_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_GENERIC_ERROR, 0);
210 
211  return ER_FAILED;
212  }
213 
214  iss = &isidp->iss;
215 
216  /* initialize iss structure */
217  iss->current_op = ISS_OP_NONE;
218  iss->skipped_range = NULL;
219 
220  if (isidp->indx_info == NULL)
221  {
222  /* no index info specified so no iss needed */
223  iss->use = false;
224  return NO_ERROR;
225  }
226 
227  iss->use = isidp->indx_info->use_iss != 0;
228 
229  if (!iss->use)
230  {
231  /* if not using iss, nothing more to do */
232  return NO_ERROR;
233  }
234 
235  /* assign range */
236  iss->skipped_range = &isidp->indx_info->iss_range;
237 
238  if (iss->skipped_range->key1 == NULL || iss->skipped_range->key1->value.funcp == NULL
239  || iss->skipped_range->key1->value.funcp->operand == NULL
240  || iss->skipped_range->key1->value.funcp->operand->value.type != TYPE_DBVAL)
241  {
242  /* this should never happen */
243  assert_release (false);
244  er_set (ER_FATAL_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_GENERIC_ERROR, 0);
245 
246  return ER_FAILED;
247  }
248 
249  /* reset key value */
250  last_key = &iss->skipped_range->key1->value.funcp->operand->value.value.dbval;
251 
252  if (!DB_IS_NULL (last_key))
253  {
254  pr_clear_value (last_key);
255  db_make_null (last_key);
256  }
257 
258  return NO_ERROR;
259 }
260 
261 /*
262  * scan_init_index_scan () - initialize an index scan structure with the
263  * specified OID buffer
264  * return : void
265  * isidp (in) : index scan
266  * oid_list (in) : OID list.
267  * mvcc_snapshot(in) : MVCC snapshot
268  */
269 void
270 scan_init_index_scan (INDX_SCAN_ID * isidp, struct btree_iscan_oid_list *oid_list, MVCC_SNAPSHOT * mvcc_snapshot)
271 {
272  if (isidp == NULL)
273  {
274  assert (false);
275  return;
276  }
277 
278  isidp->oid_list = oid_list;
279  isidp->copy_buf = NULL;
280  isidp->copy_buf_len = 0;
281  memset ((void *) (&(isidp->indx_cov)), 0, sizeof (INDX_COV));
282  isidp->indx_info = NULL;
283  memset ((void *) (&(isidp->multi_range_opt)), 0, sizeof (MULTI_RANGE_OPT));
284  scan_init_iss (isidp);
285  isidp->scan_cache.mvcc_snapshot = mvcc_snapshot;
286  isidp->need_count_only = false;
287  isidp->check_not_vacuumed = false;
288  isidp->not_vacuumed_res = DISK_VALID;
289 }
290 
291 /*
292  * scan_save_range_details () - save range details from the index scan id to
293  * a "backup" iss_range_details structure.
294  * return: error code
295  * rdp_dest: pointer to range details structure to be filled with data from isidp_src
296  * isidp_src: pointer to index scan id
297  */
298 static int
299 scan_save_range_details (INDX_SCAN_ID * isidp_src, ISS_RANGE_DETAILS * rdp_dest)
300 {
301  if (rdp_dest == NULL || isidp_src == NULL || isidp_src->indx_info == NULL)
302  {
303  assert (false);
304  return ER_FAILED;
305  }
306 
307  rdp_dest->key_cnt = isidp_src->indx_info->key_info.key_cnt;
308  rdp_dest->key_ranges = isidp_src->indx_info->key_info.key_ranges;
309  rdp_dest->key_pred = isidp_src->key_pred;
310  rdp_dest->range_type = isidp_src->indx_info->range_type;
311  rdp_dest->part_key_desc = isidp_src->bt_scan.btid_int.part_key_desc;
312 
313  return NO_ERROR;
314 }
315 
316 /*
317  * scan_restore_range_details () - restore range details from the backup
318  * structure into the index scan id.
319  * return: error code
320  * rdp_src: pointer to range details structure to be restored
321  * isidp_dest: pointer to index scan id to be filled
322  *
323  * Note:
324  * The index scan is reset so that it is considered a brand new scan (for
325  * instance, curr_keyno is set to -1 etc.)
326  */
327 static int
328 scan_restore_range_details (ISS_RANGE_DETAILS * rdp_src, INDX_SCAN_ID * isidp_dest)
329 {
330  if (isidp_dest == NULL || rdp_src == NULL || isidp_dest->indx_info == NULL)
331  {
332  return ER_FAILED;
333  }
334 
335  isidp_dest->curr_keyno = -1;
336  isidp_dest->indx_info->key_info.key_cnt = rdp_src->key_cnt;
337 
338  isidp_dest->indx_info->key_info.key_ranges = rdp_src->key_ranges;
339  isidp_dest->key_pred = rdp_src->key_pred;
340  isidp_dest->indx_info->range_type = rdp_src->range_type;
341  isidp_dest->bt_scan.btid_int.part_key_desc = rdp_src->part_key_desc;
342 
343  return NO_ERROR;
344 }
345 
346 /*
347  * scan_get_next_iss_value () - retrieve the next value to be used in the
348  * index skip scan: the next value from the
349  * first column of the index.
350  * return: S_SUCCESS on successfully retrieving the next value
351  * S_ERROR on encountering an error
352  * S_END when the search does not find any "next value" (reached
353  * end of the btree).
354  * thread_p(in):
355  * scan_id (in): scan id
356  * isidp (in): index scan id
357  *
358  * Note:
359  * This function is called from call_get_next_index_oidset whenever the
360  * current value for the first index column is exhausted and we need to go on
361  * to the next possible value of C1. It is ONLY called within an index skip
362  * scan optimization context (ONLY when isidp->iss.use is TRUE).
363  * We call scan_get_index_oidset(), which in turn calls btree_range_search,
364  * but first we set the stage: prepare a "fake" range to obtain the next value
365  * for C1 (the first column), extract the value that btree_range_search returns
366  * inside isidp->iss.dbval, fill in slot 0 of the real range ([C1=?]) with
367  * that new value, and restore the real range as if it were ready to be used
368  * for the first time.
369  */
370 static SCAN_CODE
371 scan_get_next_iss_value (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, SCAN_ID * scan_id, INDX_SCAN_ID * isidp)
372 {
373  /* we are being called either before any other btree range search, or after somebody finished a real range search and
374  * wants to advance to the next value for the first column of the index. */
375 
376  INDEX_SKIP_SCAN *iss = NULL;
377  DB_VALUE *last_key = NULL;
378  ISS_RANGE_DETAILS scan_range_det, fetch_range_det;
379  bool descending_skip_key = false;
380  bool descending_scan = false;
381  int i;
382 
383  if (isidp == NULL)
384  {
385  /* null pointer was passed to function */
386  assert_release (false);
387  er_set (ER_FATAL_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_GENERIC_ERROR, 0);
388 
389  return S_ERROR;
390  }
391 
392  if (!isidp->iss.use)
393  {
394  /* not using iss but function was called; should not be here */
395  assert_release (false);
396  er_set (ER_FATAL_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_GENERIC_ERROR, 0);
397 
398  return S_ERROR;
399  }
400 
401  if (isidp->iss.skipped_range == NULL || isidp->iss.skipped_range->key1 == NULL
402  || isidp->iss.skipped_range->key1->value.funcp == NULL
403  || isidp->iss.skipped_range->key1->value.funcp->operand == NULL
404  || isidp->iss.skipped_range->key1->value.funcp->operand->value.type != TYPE_DBVAL)
405  {
406  /* the fetch range is corrupted; should not be here */
407  assert_release (false);
408  er_set (ER_FATAL_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_GENERIC_ERROR, 0);
409 
410  return S_ERROR;
411  }
412 
413  if (isidp->bt_scan.btid_int.key_type == NULL || isidp->bt_scan.btid_int.key_type->setdomain == NULL
414  || TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (isidp->bt_scan.btid_int.key_type) != DB_TYPE_MIDXKEY)
415  {
416  /* key type is not midxkey so this is not a multi-column index; should not be here */
417  assert_release (false);
418  er_set (ER_FATAL_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_GENERIC_ERROR, 0);
419 
420  return S_ERROR;
421  }
422 
423  /* populate local variables iss and last_key */
424  descending_skip_key = isidp->bt_scan.btid_int.key_type->setdomain->is_desc;
425  iss = &isidp->iss;
426  last_key = &iss->skipped_range->key1->value.funcp->operand->value.value.dbval;
427 
428  if (iss->current_op == ISS_OP_NONE)
429  {
430  /* first iteration of index skip scan; set up range for fetching first value. key1 might be set but will be
431  * ignored for INF_INF range. */
432  iss->current_op = ISS_OP_GET_FIRST_KEY;
433  iss->skipped_range->range = INF_INF;
434  }
435  else if (iss->current_op == ISS_OP_DO_RANGE_SEARCH)
436  {
437  /* find out whether the first column of the index is asc or desc */
438  descending_scan = (isidp->bt_scan.use_desc_index ? true : false);
439  if (descending_skip_key)
440  {
441  descending_scan = !descending_scan;
442  }
443 
444  if (descending_scan)
445  {
446  /* if we're doing a descending scan, we can stop before searching for first_column < NULL since it won't
447  * produce any results */
448  if (DB_IS_NULL (last_key))
449  {
450  pr_clear_value (last_key);
451  db_make_null (last_key);
452 
453  return S_END;
454  }
455 
456  /* set the upper bound to last used key value and lower bound to NULL (i.e. infinity) */
457  iss->skipped_range->key2 = iss->skipped_range->key1;
458  iss->skipped_range->key1 = NULL;
459  }
460 
461  /* set up ISS state for searching next distinct key */
462  iss->current_op = ISS_OP_SEARCH_NEXT_DISTINCT_KEY;
463  iss->skipped_range->range = (descending_scan ? INF_LT : GT_INF);
464  }
465  else
466  {
467  /* operator is neither ISS_OP_NONE nor ISS_OP_DO_RANGE_SEARCH; we shouldn't be here */
468  assert_release (false);
469  er_set (ER_FATAL_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_GENERIC_ERROR, 0);
470 
471  return S_ERROR;
472  }
473 
474  /* populate details structure for the fetch range so we can load it */
475  fetch_range_det.key_cnt = 1;
476  fetch_range_det.key_ranges = iss->skipped_range;
477  fetch_range_det.key_pred.pred_expr = NULL;
478  fetch_range_det.key_pred.pr_eval_fnc = NULL;
479  fetch_range_det.key_pred.regu_list = NULL;
480  fetch_range_det.range_type = R_RANGE;
481  fetch_range_det.part_key_desc = descending_skip_key;
482 
483  /* save current range details */
484  if (scan_save_range_details (isidp, &scan_range_det) != NO_ERROR)
485  {
486  if (descending_scan)
487  {
488  /* return range to initial state before exit */
489  iss->skipped_range->key1 = iss->skipped_range->key2;
490  iss->skipped_range->key2 = NULL;
491  }
492  return S_ERROR;
493  }
494 
495  /* load the range we set up for fetching the next key of the first column */
496  scan_restore_range_details (&fetch_range_det, isidp);
497 
498  isidp->curr_keyno = -1;
499 
500  /* run a scan to get next key for first index column; value will be stored in the lower (or higher) bound of the
501  * fetch range (i.e. in last_key) */
502  if (scan_get_index_oidset (thread_p, scan_id, NULL, NULL) != NO_ERROR)
503  {
504  if (descending_scan)
505  {
506  /* return range to initial state before exit */
507  iss->skipped_range->key1 = iss->skipped_range->key2;
508  iss->skipped_range->key2 = NULL;
509  }
510  scan_restore_range_details (&scan_range_det, isidp);
511  return S_ERROR;
512  }
513 
514  /* undo bounds swapping if scan is descending */
515  if (descending_scan)
516  {
517  iss->skipped_range->key1 = iss->skipped_range->key2;
518  iss->skipped_range->key2 = NULL;
519  }
520 
521  /* as soon as the scan returned, convert the midxkey dbvalue to real db value (if necessary) */
522  if (scan_id->s.isid.oids_count == 0)
523  {
524  /* no other keys exist; restore scan range and exit */
525  scan_restore_range_details (&scan_range_det, isidp);
526  return S_END;
527  }
528  else if (DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (last_key) == DB_TYPE_MIDXKEY)
529  {
530  /* scan_get_index_oidset() returned a midxkey */
531  DB_VALUE first_midxkey_val;
532  DB_VALUE tmp;
533  int ret;
534 
535  /* initialize temporary variables */
536  db_make_null (&first_midxkey_val);
537  db_make_null (&tmp);
538 
539  /* put pointer to first value of midxkey into first_midxkey_val */
540  ret = pr_midxkey_get_element_nocopy (&last_key->data.midxkey, 0, &first_midxkey_val, NULL, NULL);
541  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
542  {
543  scan_restore_range_details (&scan_range_det, isidp);
544  return S_ERROR;
545  }
546 
547  /* first_midxkey_val may hold pointer to first value from last_key, which we actually want to place in last_key.
548  * steps: 1. clone first_midxkey_val to a temp variable so we have a DB_VALUE independent of last_key 2. clear
549  * last_key (no longer holds important data) 3. clone temp variable to last_key (for later use) 4. clear tmp (we
550  * no longer need it) */
551  pr_clone_value (&first_midxkey_val, &tmp);
552  pr_clear_value (last_key);
553  pr_clone_value (&tmp, last_key);
554  pr_clear_value (&tmp);
555  pr_clear_value (&first_midxkey_val);
556  }
557 
558  /* use last_key in scan_range */
559  for (i = 0; i < scan_range_det.key_cnt; i++)
560  {
561  KEY_RANGE *kr = &(scan_range_det.key_ranges[i]);
562 
563  if (kr == NULL)
564  {
565  continue;
566  }
567 
568  if (kr->key1 != NULL)
569  {
570  assert_release (kr->key1->type == TYPE_FUNC && TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (kr->key1->domain) == DB_TYPE_MIDXKEY);
571  assert_release (kr->key1->value.funcp->operand);
572 
573  if (kr->key1->value.funcp->operand != NULL)
574  {
575  REGU_VARIABLE *regu = &kr->key1->value.funcp->operand->value;
576 
577  regu->type = TYPE_DBVAL;
578  regu->domain = tp_domain_resolve_default (DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (last_key));
579 
580  pr_clear_value (&regu->value.dbval);
581  pr_clone_value (last_key, &regu->value.dbval);
582  }
583  }
584 
585  if (kr->key2 != NULL)
586  {
587  assert_release (kr->key2->type == TYPE_FUNC && TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (kr->key2->domain) == DB_TYPE_MIDXKEY);
588  assert_release (kr->key2->value.funcp->operand);
589 
590  if (kr->key2->value.funcp->operand != NULL)
591  {
592  REGU_VARIABLE *regu = &kr->key2->value.funcp->operand->value;
593 
594  regu->type = TYPE_DBVAL;
595  regu->domain = tp_domain_resolve_default (DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (last_key));
596 
597  pr_clear_value (&regu->value.dbval);
598  pr_clone_value (last_key, &regu->value.dbval);
599  }
600  }
601  }
602 
603  /* restore the range used for normal scanning */
604  scan_restore_range_details (&scan_range_det, isidp);
605 
606  /* prepare for range search */
607  isidp->iss.current_op = ISS_OP_DO_RANGE_SEARCH;
608  isidp->curr_keyno = -1;
609 
610  return S_SUCCESS;
611 }
612

665 /*
666  * scan_init_indx_coverage () - initialize INDX_COV structure
667  * return: error code
668  *
669  * coverage_enabled(in): true if coverage is enabled
670  * output_val_list(in): output val list
671  * regu_val_list(in): regu val list
672  * vd(in): val descriptor
673  * query_id(in): the query id
674  * max_key_len(in): the maximum key length
675  * indx_cov(in/out): index coverage data
676  */
677 static int
678 scan_init_indx_coverage (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, int coverage_enabled, OUTPTR_LIST * output_val_list,
679  REGU_VARIABLE_LIST regu_val_list, VAL_DESCR * vd, QUERY_ID query_id, int max_key_len,
680  int func_index_col_id, INDX_COV * indx_cov)
681 {
682  int err = NO_ERROR;
683  int num_membuf_pages = 0;
684 
685  if (indx_cov == NULL)
686  {
687  return ER_FAILED;
688  }
689 
690  indx_cov->val_descr = vd;
691  indx_cov->output_val_list = output_val_list;
692  indx_cov->regu_val_list = regu_val_list;
693  indx_cov->query_id = query_id;
694 
695  if (coverage_enabled == false)
696  {
697  indx_cov->type_list = NULL;
698  indx_cov->list_id = NULL;
699  indx_cov->tplrec = NULL;
700  indx_cov->lsid = NULL;
701  indx_cov->max_tuples = 0;
702  indx_cov->func_index_col_id = -1;
703  return NO_ERROR;
704  }
705 
706  indx_cov->func_index_col_id = func_index_col_id;
707  indx_cov->type_list =
708  (QFILE_TUPLE_VALUE_TYPE_LIST *) db_private_alloc (thread_p, sizeof (QFILE_TUPLE_VALUE_TYPE_LIST));
709  if (indx_cov->type_list == NULL)
710  {
711  err = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
712  goto exit_on_error;
713  }
714 
715  if (qdata_get_valptr_type_list (thread_p, output_val_list, indx_cov->type_list) != NO_ERROR)
716  {
717  err = ER_FAILED;
718  goto exit_on_error;
719  }
720 
721  /*
722  * Covering index scan needs large-size memory buffer in order to decrease
723  * the number of times doing stop-and-resume during btree_range_search.
724  * To do it, QFILE_FLAG_USE_KEY_BUFFER is introduced. If the flag is set,
725  * the list file allocates PRM_INDEX_SCAN_KEY_BUFFER_PAGES pages memory
726  * for its memory buffer, which is generally larger than prm_get_integer_value (PRM_ID_TEMP_MEM_BUFFER_PAGES).
727  */
728  indx_cov->list_id = qfile_open_list (thread_p, indx_cov->type_list, NULL, query_id, QFILE_FLAG_USE_KEY_BUFFER);
729  if (indx_cov->list_id == NULL)
730  {
731  err = ER_FAILED;
732  goto exit_on_error;
733  }
734 
735  num_membuf_pages = qmgr_get_temp_file_membuf_pages (indx_cov->list_id->tfile_vfid);
736  assert (num_membuf_pages > 0);
737 
738  if (max_key_len > 0 && num_membuf_pages > 0)
739  {
740  indx_cov->max_tuples = num_membuf_pages * IO_PAGESIZE / max_key_len;
741  indx_cov->max_tuples = MAX (indx_cov->max_tuples, 1);
742  }
743  else
744  {
745  indx_cov->max_tuples = IDX_COV_DEFAULT_TUPLES;
746  }
747 
748  indx_cov->tplrec = (QFILE_TUPLE_RECORD *) db_private_alloc (thread_p, sizeof (QFILE_TUPLE_RECORD));
749  if (indx_cov->tplrec == NULL)
750  {
751  err = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
752  goto exit_on_error;
753  }
754  indx_cov->tplrec->size = 0;
755  indx_cov->tplrec->tpl = NULL;
756 
757  indx_cov->lsid = (QFILE_LIST_SCAN_ID *) db_private_alloc (thread_p, sizeof (QFILE_LIST_SCAN_ID));
758  if (indx_cov->lsid == NULL)
759  {
760  err = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
761  goto exit_on_error;
762  }
763  indx_cov->lsid->status = S_CLOSED;
764 
765  return NO_ERROR;
766 
767 exit_on_error:
768 
769  if (indx_cov->type_list != NULL)
770  {
771  if (indx_cov->type_list->domp != NULL)
772  {
773  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, indx_cov->type_list->domp);
774  }
775  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, indx_cov->type_list);
776  }
777 
778  if (indx_cov->list_id != NULL)
779  {
780  QFILE_FREE_AND_INIT_LIST_ID (indx_cov->list_id);
781  }
782 
783  if (indx_cov->tplrec != NULL)
784  {
785  if (indx_cov->tplrec->tpl != NULL)
786  {
787  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, indx_cov->tplrec->tpl);
788  }
789  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, indx_cov->tplrec);
790  }
791 
792  if (indx_cov->lsid != NULL)
793  {
794  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, indx_cov->lsid);
795  }
796 
797  return err;
798 }
799 
800 /*
801  * scan_init_index_key_limit () - initialize/reset index key limits
802  * return: error code
803  */
804 static int
805 scan_init_index_key_limit (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, INDX_SCAN_ID * isidp, KEY_INFO * key_infop, VAL_DESCR * vd)
806 {
807  DB_VALUE *dbvalp;
808  TP_DOMAIN *domainp = tp_domain_resolve_default (DB_TYPE_BIGINT);
809  bool is_lower_limit_negative = false;
810  TP_DOMAIN_STATUS dom_status;
811 
812  if (key_infop->key_limit_l != NULL)
813  {
814  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, key_infop->key_limit_l, vd, NULL, NULL, NULL, &dbvalp) != NO_ERROR)
815  {
816  return ER_FAILED;
817  }
818  dom_status = tp_value_coerce (dbvalp, dbvalp, domainp);
819  if (dom_status != DOMAIN_COMPATIBLE)
820  {
821  (void) tp_domain_status_er_set (dom_status, ARG_FILE_LINE, dbvalp, domainp);
822 
823  return ER_FAILED;
824  }
825 
826  if (DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (dbvalp) != DB_TYPE_BIGINT)
827  {
828  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_QPROC_INVALID_DATATYPE, 0);
829  return ER_QPROC_INVALID_DATATYPE;
830  }
831  else
832  {
833  isidp->key_limit_lower = db_get_bigint (dbvalp);
834  }
835 
836  if (isidp->key_limit_lower < 0)
837  {
838  if (key_infop->is_user_given_keylimit == true)
839  {
840  /* We don't allow users to give us a bad keylimit bound */
841 
842  /* still want to have better error code */
843  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_QPROC_INVALID_PARAMETER, 0);
844  return ER_QPROC_INVALID_PARAMETER;
845  }
846 
847  /* Optimizer adopts keylimit optimization */
848 
849  /* SELECT * from t where ROWNUM = 0 order by a: this would sometimes get optimized using keylimit, if the
850  * circumstances are right. in this case, the lower limit would be "0-1", effectiveley -1. We cannot allow
851  * that to happen, since -1 is a special value meaning "there is no lower limit", and certain critical
852  * decisions (such as resetting the key limit for multiple ranges) depend on knowing whether or not there is
853  * a lower key limit. We set a flag to remember, later on, to "adjust" the key limits such that, if the lower
854  * limit is negative, to return no results.
855  */
856  is_lower_limit_negative = true;
857  }
858  }
859  else
860  {
861  isidp->key_limit_lower = -1;
862  }
863 
864  if (key_infop->key_limit_u != NULL)
865  {
866  if (fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, key_infop->key_limit_u, vd, NULL, NULL, NULL, &dbvalp) != NO_ERROR)
867  {
868  return ER_FAILED;
869  }
870  dom_status = tp_value_coerce (dbvalp, dbvalp, domainp);
871  if (dom_status != DOMAIN_COMPATIBLE)
872  {
873  (void) tp_domain_status_er_set (dom_status, ARG_FILE_LINE, dbvalp, domainp);
874 
875  return ER_FAILED;
876  }
877  if (DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (dbvalp) != DB_TYPE_BIGINT)
878  {
879  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_QPROC_INVALID_DATATYPE, 0);
880  return ER_QPROC_INVALID_DATATYPE;
881  }
882  else
883  {
884  isidp->key_limit_upper = db_get_bigint (dbvalp);
885  }
886 
887  if (isidp->key_limit_upper < 0)
888  {
889  if (key_infop->is_user_given_keylimit == true)
890  {
891  /* We don't allow users to give us a bad keylimit bound */
892 
893  /* still want to have better error code */
894  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_QPROC_INVALID_PARAMETER, 0);
895  return ER_QPROC_INVALID_PARAMETER;
896  }
897 
898  /* Optimizer adopts keylimit optimization */
899 
900  /* Try to sanitize the upper value. It might have been computed from operations on host variables, which are
901  * unpredictable.
902  */
903  isidp->key_limit_upper = 0;
904  }
905  }
906  else
907  {
908  isidp->key_limit_upper = -1;
909  }
910 
911  if (is_lower_limit_negative && isidp->key_limit_upper > 0)
912  {
913  /* decrease the upper limit: key_limit_lower is negative */
914  isidp->key_limit_upper += isidp->key_limit_lower;
915  if (isidp->key_limit_upper < 0)
916  {
917  isidp->key_limit_upper = 0;
918  }
919  isidp->key_limit_lower = 0; /* reset it to something usable */
920  }
921 
922  return NO_ERROR;
923 }
924 
925 /*
926  * scan_alloc_oid_list () - Allocate an index scan OID list.
927  *
928  * return : Error code.
929  * oid_buf_p (out) : Allocated buffer.
930  * oid_buf_capacity (out) : Allocated buffer capacity.
931  */
932 static int
933 scan_alloc_oid_list (BTREE_ISCAN_OID_LIST ** oid_list_p)
934 {
935  /* Assert expected arguments. */
936  assert (oid_list_p != NULL && *oid_list_p == NULL);
937 
938  /* Allocate OID list entry. */
939  *oid_list_p = (BTREE_ISCAN_OID_LIST *) malloc (sizeof (BTREE_ISCAN_OID_LIST));
940  if (*oid_list_p == NULL)
941  {
942  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, sizeof (BTREE_ISCAN_OID_LIST));
943  return ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
944  }
945 
946  /* Allocate OID list buffer. */
947  (*oid_list_p)->capacity = ISCAN_OID_BUFFER_CAPACITY / OR_OID_SIZE;
948  (*oid_list_p)->oidp = (OID *) malloc ((*oid_list_p)->capacity * OR_OID_SIZE);
949  if ((*oid_list_p)->oidp == NULL)
950  {
951  /* Could not allocate memory. */
952  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, (*oid_list_p)->capacity * OR_OID_SIZE);
953 
954  /* Free already allocated. */
955  free_and_init (*oid_list_p);
956  return ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
957  }
958  /* Allocation successful. */
959  /* Initialize other fields. */
960  (*oid_list_p)->next_list = NULL;
961  (*oid_list_p)->max_oid_cnt = (*oid_list_p)->capacity;
962  (*oid_list_p)->oid_cnt = 0;
963  return NO_ERROR;
964 }
965 
966 /*
967  * scan_free_oid_list () - Free an index scan OID list.
968  *
969  * return : void
970  */
971 static void
972 scan_free_oid_list (BTREE_ISCAN_OID_LIST * oid_list_p)
973 {
974  assert (oid_list_p != NULL);
975 
976  if (oid_list_p->oidp != NULL)
977  {
978  free_and_init (oid_list_p->oidp);
979  }
980  free_and_init (oid_list_p);
981 }
982 
983 /*
984  * scan_alloc_iscan_oid_buf_list () - Allocate or use a preallocated buffer for index scan OID list.
985  *
986  * return : Error code.
987  * oid_list (out) : Output OID list with allocated buffer.
988  */
989 static int
990 scan_alloc_iscan_oid_buf_list (BTREE_ISCAN_OID_LIST ** oid_list)
991 {
992 #if defined (SERVER_MODE)
993  int rv;
994 #endif /* SERVER_MODE */
995  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
996 
997  /* Assert expected argument. */
998  assert (oid_list != NULL && *oid_list == NULL);
999 
1000  /* Is buffer empty? */
1001  if (scan_Iscan_oid_buf_list != NULL)
1002  {
1003  /* Not empty. */
1004  /* Protect by mutex and try to get from buffer. */
1005  rv = pthread_mutex_lock (&scan_Iscan_oid_buf_list_mutex);
1006  /* Was buffer emptied? */
1007  if (scan_Iscan_oid_buf_list != NULL)
1008  {
1009  /* Not empty */
1010  /* Pop first entry. */
1011  *oid_list = scan_Iscan_oid_buf_list;
1012 
1013  /* Update buffer. */
1014  scan_Iscan_oid_buf_list = scan_Iscan_oid_buf_list->next_list;
1015  scan_Iscan_oid_buf_list_count--;
1016  pthread_mutex_unlock (&scan_Iscan_oid_buf_list_mutex);
1017 
1018  /* Reset next_list link. */
1019  (*oid_list)->next_list = NULL;
1020  return NO_ERROR;
1021  }
1022  /* Empty. */
1023  pthread_mutex_unlock (&scan_Iscan_oid_buf_list_mutex);
1024  }
1025 
1026  /* Allocate a new OID list entry. */
1027  error_code = scan_alloc_oid_list (oid_list);
1028  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
1029  {
1030  ASSERT_ERROR ();
1031  return error_code;
1032  }
1033  /* Safe guard. */
1034  assert (*oid_list != NULL);
1035  assert ((*oid_list)->oidp != NULL);
1036  assert ((*oid_list)->capacity > 0);
1037 
1038  /* Success. */
1039  return NO_ERROR;
1040 }
1041 
1042 /*
1043  * scan_free_iscan_oid_buf_list () - Free OID buffer from OID list of index scan.
1044  *
1045  * return : Void.
1046  * oid_list (in) : OID list to free.
1047  */
1048 static void
1049 scan_free_iscan_oid_buf_list (BTREE_ISCAN_OID_LIST * oid_list)
1050 {
1051 #if defined (SERVER_MODE)
1052  int rv;
1053 #endif /* SERVER_MODE */
1054 
1055  /* Free entry. */
1056  rv = pthread_mutex_lock (&scan_Iscan_oid_buf_list_mutex);
1057  /* Is buffer at its full capacity? */
1058  if (scan_Iscan_oid_buf_list_count < MAX_NTRANS)
1059  {
1060  /* Add oid_list to scan_Iscan_oid_buf_list */
1061  oid_list->next_list = scan_Iscan_oid_buf_list;
1062  scan_Iscan_oid_buf_list = oid_list;
1063  scan_Iscan_oid_buf_list_count++;
1064  }
1065  else
1066  {
1067  /* Too many buffers, just free it. */
1068  scan_free_oid_list (oid_list);
1069  }
1070  pthread_mutex_unlock (&scan_Iscan_oid_buf_list_mutex);
1071 }
1072 
1073 /*
1074  * rop_to_range () - map left/right to range operator
1075  * return:
1076  * range(out): full-RANGE operator
1077  * left(in): left-side range operator
1078  * right(in): right-side range operator
1079  */
1080 static void
1081 rop_to_range (RANGE * range, ROP_TYPE left, ROP_TYPE right)
1082 {
1083  int i;
1084 
1085  *range = NA_NA;
1086 
1087  for (i = 0; i < rop_range_table_size; i++)
1088  {
1089  if (left == rop_range_table[i].left && right == rop_range_table[i].right)
1090  {
1091  /* found match */
1092  *range = rop_range_table[i].range;
1093  break;
1094  }
1095  }
1096 }
1097 
1098 /*
1099  * range_to_rop () - map range to left/right operator
1100  * return:
1101  * left(out): left-side range operator
1102  * right(out): right-side range operator
1103  * range(in): full-RANGE operator
1104  */
1105 static void
1106 range_to_rop (ROP_TYPE * left, ROP_TYPE * right, RANGE range)
1107 {
1108  int i;
1109 
1110  *left = ROP_NA;
1111  *right = ROP_NA;
1112 
1113  for (i = 0; i < rop_range_table_size; i++)
1114  {
1115  if (range == rop_range_table[i].range)
1116  {
1117  /* found match */
1118  *left = rop_range_table[i].left;
1119  *right = rop_range_table[i].right;
1120  break;
1121  }
1122  }
1123 }
1124 
1125 /*
1126  * scan_key_compare ()
1127  * val1(in):
1128  * val2(in):
1129  * num_index_term(in):
1130  * return:
1131  */
1132 static int
1133 scan_key_compare (DB_VALUE * val1, DB_VALUE * val2, int num_index_term)
1134 {
1135  int rc = DB_UNK;
1136  DB_TYPE key_type;
1137  int dummy_size1, dummy_size2, dummy_diff_column;
1138  bool dummy_dom_is_desc, dummy_next_dom_is_desc;
1139 
1140  if (val1 == NULL || val2 == NULL)
1141  {
1142  assert_release (0);
1143  return rc;
1144  }
1145 
1146  if (DB_IS_NULL (val1))
1147  {
1148  if (DB_IS_NULL (val2))
1149  {
1150  rc = DB_EQ;
1151  }
1152  else
1153  {
1154  rc = DB_LT;
1155  }
1156  }
1157  else if (DB_IS_NULL (val2))
1158  {
1159  rc = DB_GT;
1160  }
1161  else
1162  {
1163  key_type = DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (val1);
1164  if (key_type == DB_TYPE_MIDXKEY)
1165  {
1166  rc =
1167  pr_midxkey_compare (db_get_midxkey (val1), db_get_midxkey (val2), 1, 1, num_index_term, NULL, &dummy_size1,
1168  &dummy_size2, &dummy_diff_column, &dummy_dom_is_desc, &dummy_next_dom_is_desc);
1169  }
1170  else
1171  {
1172  rc = tp_value_compare (val1, val2, 1, 1);
1173  }
1174  }
1175 
1176  return rc;
1177 }
1178 
1179 /*
1180  * compare_val_op () - compare two values specified by range operator
1181  * return:
1182  * val1(in):
1183  * op1(in):
1184  * val2(in):
1185  * op2(in):
1186  * num_index_term(in):
1187  */
1188 static ROP_TYPE
1189 compare_val_op (DB_VALUE * val1, ROP_TYPE op1, DB_VALUE * val2, ROP_TYPE op2, int num_index_term)
1190 {
1191  int rc;
1192 
1193  if (op1 == ROP_GT_INF) /* val1 is -INF */
1194  {
1195  return (op1 == op2) ? ROP_EQ : ROP_LT;
1196  }
1197  if (op1 == ROP_LT_INF) /* val1 is +INF */
1198  {
1199  return (op1 == op2) ? ROP_EQ : ROP_GT;
1200  }
1201  if (op2 == ROP_GT_INF) /* val2 is -INF */
1202  {
1203  return (op2 == op1) ? ROP_EQ : ROP_GT;
1204  }
1205  if (op2 == ROP_LT_INF) /* val2 is +INF */
1206  {
1207  return (op2 == op1) ? ROP_EQ : ROP_LT;
1208  }
1209 
1210  rc = scan_key_compare (val1, val2, num_index_term);
1211 
1212  if (rc == DB_EQ)
1213  {
1214  /* (val1, op1) == (val2, op2) */
1215  if (op1 == op2)
1216  {
1217  return ROP_EQ;
1218  }
1219  if (op1 == ROP_EQ || op1 == ROP_GE || op1 == ROP_LE)
1220  {
1221  if (op2 == ROP_EQ || op2 == ROP_GE || op2 == ROP_LE)
1222  {
1223  return ROP_EQ;
1224  }
1225  return (op2 == ROP_GT) ? ROP_LT_ADJ : ROP_GT_ADJ;
1226  }
1227  if (op1 == ROP_GT)
1228  {
1229  if (op2 == ROP_EQ || op2 == ROP_GE || op2 == ROP_LE)
1230  {
1231  return ROP_GT_ADJ;
1232  }
1233  return (op2 == ROP_LT) ? ROP_GT : ROP_EQ;
1234  }
1235  if (op1 == ROP_LT)
1236  {
1237  if (op2 == ROP_EQ || op2 == ROP_GE || op2 == ROP_LE)
1238  {
1239  return ROP_LT_ADJ;
1240  }
1241  return (op2 == ROP_GT) ? ROP_LT : ROP_EQ;
1242  }
1243  }
1244  else if (rc == DB_LT)
1245  {
1246  /* (val1, op1) < (val2, op2) */
1247  return ROP_LT;
1248  }
1249  else if (rc == DB_GT)
1250  {
1251  /* (val1, op1) > (val2, op2) */
1252  return ROP_GT;
1253  }
1254 
1255  /* tp_value_compare() returned error? */
1256  return (rc == DB_EQ) ? ROP_EQ : ROP_NA;
1257 }
1258 
1259 /*
1260  * key_val_compare () - key value sorting function
1261  * return:
1262  * p1 (in): pointer to key1 range
1263  * p2 (in): pointer to key2 range
1264  */
1265 static int
1266 key_val_compare (const void *p1, const void *p2)
1267 {
1268  int p1_num_index_term, p2_num_index_term;
1269  DB_VALUE *p1_key, *p2_key;
1270 
1271  p1_num_index_term = ((KEY_VAL_RANGE *) p1)->num_index_term;
1272  p2_num_index_term = ((KEY_VAL_RANGE *) p2)->num_index_term;
1273  assert_release (p1_num_index_term == p2_num_index_term);
1274 
1275  p1_key = &((KEY_VAL_RANGE *) p1)->key1;
1276  p2_key = &((KEY_VAL_RANGE *) p2)->key1;
1277 
1278  return scan_key_compare (p1_key, p2_key, p1_num_index_term);
1279 }
1280 
1281 /*
1282  * eliminate_duplicated_keys () - elimnate duplicated key values
1283  * return: number of keys, -1 for error
1284  * key_vals (in): pointer to array of KEY_VAL_RANGE structure
1285  * key_cnt (in): number of keys; size of key_vals
1286  */
1287 static int
1288 eliminate_duplicated_keys (KEY_VAL_RANGE * key_vals, int key_cnt)
1289 {
1290  int n;
1291  KEY_VAL_RANGE *curp, *nextp;
1292 
1293  curp = key_vals;
1294  nextp = key_vals + 1;
1295  n = 0;
1296  while (key_cnt > 1 && n < key_cnt - 1)
1297  {
1298  if (tp_value_compare (&curp->key1, &nextp->key1, 1, 1) == DB_EQ)
1299  {
1300  pr_clear_value (&nextp->key1);
1301  pr_clear_value (&nextp->key2);
1302  memmove (nextp, nextp + 1, sizeof (KEY_VAL_RANGE) * (key_cnt - n - 2));
1303  key_cnt--;
1304  }
1305  else
1306  {
1307  curp++;
1308  nextp++;
1309  n++;
1310  }
1311  }
1312 
1313  return key_cnt;
1314 }
1315 
1316 /*
1317  * merge_key_ranges () - merge search key ranges
1318  * return: number of keys, -1 for error
1319  * key_vals (in): pointer to array of KEY_VAL_RANGE structure
1320  * key_cnt (in): number of keys; size of key_vals
1321  */
1322 static int
1323 merge_key_ranges (KEY_VAL_RANGE * key_vals, int key_cnt)
1324 {
1325  int cur_n, next_n;
1326  KEY_VAL_RANGE *curp, *nextp;
1327  ROP_TYPE cur_op1, cur_op2, next_op1, next_op2;
1328  ROP_TYPE cmp_1, cmp_2, cmp_3, cmp_4;
1329  bool is_mergeable;
1330 
1331  cmp_1 = cmp_2 = cmp_3 = cmp_4 = ROP_NA;
1332 
1333  curp = key_vals;
1334  cur_n = 0;
1335  while (key_cnt > 1 && cur_n < key_cnt - 1)
1336  {
1337  range_to_rop (&cur_op1, &cur_op2, curp->range);
1338 
1339  nextp = curp + 1;
1340  next_n = cur_n + 1;
1341  while (next_n < key_cnt)
1342  {
1343  range_to_rop (&next_op1, &next_op2, nextp->range);
1344 
1345  /* check if the two key ranges are mergable */
1346  is_mergeable = true; /* init */
1347  cmp_1 = cmp_2 = cmp_3 = cmp_4 = ROP_NA;
1348 
1349  if (is_mergeable == true)
1350  {
1351  cmp_1 = compare_val_op (&curp->key2, cur_op2, &nextp->key1, next_op1, curp->num_index_term);
1352  if (cmp_1 == ROP_NA || cmp_1 == ROP_LT)
1353  {
1354  is_mergeable = false; /* error or disjoint */
1355  }
1356  }
1357 
1358  if (is_mergeable == true)
1359  {
1360  cmp_2 = compare_val_op (&curp->key1, cur_op1, &nextp->key2, next_op2, curp->num_index_term);
1361  if (cmp_2 == ROP_NA || cmp_2 == ROP_GT)
1362  {
1363  is_mergeable = false; /* error or disjoint */
1364  }
1365  }
1366 
1367  if (is_mergeable == true)
1368  {
1369  /* determine the lower bound of the merged key range */
1370  cmp_3 = compare_val_op (&curp->key1, cur_op1, &nextp->key1, next_op1, curp->num_index_term);
1371  if (cmp_3 == ROP_NA)
1372  {
1373  is_mergeable = false;
1374  }
1375  }
1376 
1377  if (is_mergeable == true)
1378  {
1379  /* determine the upper bound of the merged key range */
1380  cmp_4 = compare_val_op (&curp->key2, cur_op2, &nextp->key2, next_op2, curp->num_index_term);
1381  if (cmp_4 == ROP_NA)
1382  {
1383  is_mergeable = false;
1384  }
1385  }
1386 
1387  if (is_mergeable == false)
1388  {
1389  /* they are disjoint */
1390  nextp++;
1391  next_n++;
1392  continue; /* skip and go ahead */
1393  }
1394 
1395  /* determine the lower bound of the merged key range */
1396  if (cmp_3 == ROP_GT_ADJ || cmp_3 == ROP_GT)
1397  {
1398  pr_clear_value (&curp->key1);
1399  curp->key1 = nextp->key1; /* bitwise copy */
1400  db_make_null (&nextp->key1);
1401  cur_op1 = next_op1;
1402  }
1403  else
1404  {
1405  pr_clear_value (&nextp->key1);
1406  }
1407 
1408  /* determine the upper bound of the merged key range */
1409  if (cmp_4 == ROP_LT || cmp_4 == ROP_LT_ADJ)
1410  {
1411  pr_clear_value (&curp->key2);
1412  curp->key2 = nextp->key2; /* bitwise copy */
1413  db_make_null (&nextp->key2);
1414  cur_op2 = next_op2;
1415  }
1416  else
1417  {
1418  pr_clear_value (&nextp->key2);
1419  }
1420 
1421  /* determine the new range type */
1422  rop_to_range (&curp->range, cur_op1, cur_op2);
1423  /* remove merged one(nextp) */
1424  memmove (nextp, nextp + 1, sizeof (KEY_VAL_RANGE) * (key_cnt - next_n - 1));
1425  key_cnt--;
1426  }
1427 
1428  curp++;
1429  cur_n++;
1430  }
1431 
1432  return key_cnt;
1433 }
1434 
1435 /*
1436  * check_key_vals () - check key values
1437  * return: number of keys, -1 for error
1438  * key_vals (in): pointer to array of KEY_VAL_RANGE structure
1439  * key_cnt (in): number of keys; size of key_vals
1440  * chk_fn (in): check function for key_vals
1441  */
1442 static int
1443 check_key_vals (KEY_VAL_RANGE * key_vals, int key_cnt, QPROC_KEY_VAL_FU * key_val_fn)
1444 {
1445  if (key_cnt <= 1)
1446  {
1447  return key_cnt;
1448  }
1449 
1450  qsort ((void *) key_vals, key_cnt, sizeof (KEY_VAL_RANGE), key_val_compare);
1451 
1452  return ((*key_val_fn) (key_vals, key_cnt));
1453 }
1454 
1455 /*
1456  * scan_dbvals_to_midxkey () -
1457  * return: NO_ERROR or ER_code
1458  *
1459  * retval (out):
1460  * indexal (out):
1461  * btree_domainp (in):
1462  * num_term (in):
1463  * func (in):
1464  * vd (in):
1465  * key_minmax (in):
1466  * is_iss (in)
1467  */
1468 static int
1469 scan_dbvals_to_midxkey (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, DB_VALUE * retval, bool * indexable, TP_DOMAIN * btree_domainp,
1470  int num_term, REGU_VARIABLE * func, VAL_DESCR * vd, int key_minmax, bool is_iss)
1471 {
1472  int ret = NO_ERROR;
1473  DB_VALUE *val = NULL;
1474  DB_TYPE val_type_id;
1475  DB_MIDXKEY midxkey;
1476 
1477  int idx_ncols = 0, natts, i, j;
1478  int buf_size, nullmap_size;
1479  unsigned char *bits;
1480 
1481  REGU_VARIABLE_LIST operand;
1482 
1483  char *nullmap_ptr; /* ponter to boundbits */
1484  char *key_ptr; /* current position in key */
1485 
1486  OR_BUF buf;
1487 
1488  bool need_new_setdomain = false;
1489  TP_DOMAIN *idx_setdomain = NULL, *vals_setdomain = NULL;
1490  TP_DOMAIN *idx_dom = NULL, *val_dom = NULL, *dom = NULL, *next = NULL;
1491  TP_DOMAIN dom_buf;
1492  DB_VALUE *coerced_values = NULL;
1493  bool *has_coerced_values = NULL;
1494 
1495  *indexable = false;
1496 
1497  if (TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (func->domain) != DB_TYPE_MIDXKEY)
1498  {
1499  assert (false);
1500  return ER_FAILED;
1501  }
1502 
1503  idx_ncols = btree_domainp->precision;
1504  if (idx_ncols <= 0)
1505  {
1506  assert (false);
1507  return ER_FAILED;
1508  }
1509 
1510  idx_setdomain = btree_domainp->setdomain;
1511 
1512 #if !defined(NDEBUG)
1513  {
1514  int dom_ncols = 0;
1515 
1516  for (idx_dom = idx_setdomain; idx_dom != NULL; idx_dom = idx_dom->next)
1517  {
1518  dom_ncols++;
1519  if (idx_dom->precision < 0)
1520  {
1521  assert (false);
1522  return ER_FAILED;
1523  }
1524  }
1525 
1526  if (dom_ncols <= 0)
1527  {
1528  assert (false);
1529  return ER_FAILED;
1530  }
1531 
1532  assert (dom_ncols == idx_ncols);
1533  }
1534 #endif /* NDEBUG */
1535 
1536  buf_size = 0;
1537  midxkey.buf = NULL;
1538  midxkey.min_max_val.position = -1;
1539 
1540  /* bitmap is always fully sized */
1541  nullmap_size = OR_MULTI_BOUND_BIT_BYTES (idx_ncols);
1542  buf_size = nullmap_size;
1543 
1544  /* check to need a new setdomain */
1545  for (operand = func->value.funcp->operand, idx_dom = idx_setdomain, i = 0; operand != NULL && idx_dom != NULL;
1546  operand = operand->next, idx_dom = idx_dom->next, i++)
1547  {
1548  ret = fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, &(operand->value), vd, NULL, NULL, NULL, &val);
1549  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
1550  {
1551  goto err_exit;
1552  }
1553 
1554  if (DB_IS_NULL (val))
1555  {
1556  if (is_iss && i == 0)
1557  {
1558  /* If this is INDEX SKIP SCAN we allow the first column to be NULL and we don't need a new domain for it */
1559  continue;
1560  }
1561  else
1562  {
1563  /* to fix multi-column index NULL problem */
1564  goto end;
1565  }
1566  }
1567 
1568  val_type_id = DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (val);
1569  if (TP_IS_STRING_TYPE (val_type_id))
1570  {
1571  /* we need to check for maxes */
1572  if (val->data.ch.medium.is_max_string)
1573  {
1574  /* oops, we found max. */
1575  midxkey.min_max_val.position = i;
1576  midxkey.min_max_val.type = MAX_COLUMN;
1577 
1578  /* just stop here */
1579  break;
1580  }
1581  }
1582 
1583  if (TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (idx_dom) != val_type_id)
1584  {
1585  /* allocate DB_VALUE array to store coerced values. */
1586  if (has_coerced_values == NULL)
1587  {
1588  assert (has_coerced_values == NULL && coerced_values == NULL);
1589  coerced_values = (DB_VALUE *) db_private_alloc (thread_p, sizeof (DB_VALUE) * idx_ncols);
1590  if (coerced_values == NULL)
1591  {
1592  goto err_exit;
1593  }
1594  for (j = 0; j < idx_ncols; j++)
1595  {
1596  db_make_null (&coerced_values[j]);
1597  }
1598 
1599  has_coerced_values = (bool *) db_private_alloc (thread_p, sizeof (bool) * idx_ncols);
1600  if (has_coerced_values == NULL)
1601  {
1602  goto err_exit;
1603  }
1604  memset (has_coerced_values, 0x0, sizeof (bool) * idx_ncols);
1605  }
1606 
1607  /* Coerce the value to index domain. If there is loss, we should make a new setdomain. */
1608  ret = tp_value_coerce_strict (val, &coerced_values[i], idx_dom);
1609  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
1610  {
1611  need_new_setdomain = true;
1612  }
1613  else
1614  {
1615  has_coerced_values[i] = true;
1616  }
1617  }
1618  else if (TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (idx_dom) == DB_TYPE_NUMERIC || TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (idx_dom) == DB_TYPE_CHAR
1619  || TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (idx_dom) == DB_TYPE_BIT || TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (idx_dom) == DB_TYPE_NCHAR)
1620  {
1621  /* skip variable string domain : DB_TYPE_VARCHAR, DB_TYPE_VARNCHAR, DB_TYPE_VARBIT */
1622 
1623  val_dom = tp_domain_resolve_value (val, &dom_buf);
1624  if (val_dom == NULL)
1625  {
1626  goto err_exit;
1627  }
1628 
1629  if (!tp_domain_match_ignore_order (idx_dom, val_dom, TP_EXACT_MATCH))
1630  {
1631  need_new_setdomain = true;
1632  }
1633  }
1634  }
1635 
1636  /* calculate midxkey's size & make a new setdomain if need */
1637  /* NOTICE that this will stop the iteration on MAX_COLUMN value if exists.
1638  * Remaining key values including MAX_COLUMN position will be filled as NULL
1639  * by btree_coerce_key at the end of this function.
1640  */
1641  for (operand = func->value.funcp->operand, idx_dom = idx_setdomain, natts = 0;
1642  operand != NULL && idx_dom != NULL
1643  && (midxkey.min_max_val.position == -1 || natts < midxkey.min_max_val.position);
1644  operand = operand->next, idx_dom = idx_dom->next, natts++)
1645  {
1646  /* If there is coerced value, we will use it regardless of whether a new setdomain is required or not. */
1647  if (has_coerced_values != NULL && has_coerced_values[natts] == true)
1648  {
1649  assert (coerced_values != NULL);
1650  val = &coerced_values[natts];
1651  }
1652  else
1653  {
1654  ret = fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, &(operand->value), vd, NULL, NULL, NULL, &val);
1655  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
1656  {
1657  goto err_exit;
1658  }
1659  }
1660 
1661  if (need_new_setdomain == true)
1662  {
1663  /* make a value's domain */
1664  val_dom = tp_domain_resolve_value (val, &dom_buf);
1665  if (val_dom == NULL)
1666  {
1667  goto err_exit;
1668  }
1669 
1670  val_dom = tp_domain_copy (val_dom, false);
1671  if (val_dom == NULL)
1672  {
1673  goto err_exit;
1674  }
1675  val_dom->is_desc = idx_dom->is_desc;
1676 
1677  /* make a new setdomain */
1678  if (vals_setdomain == NULL)
1679  {
1680  assert (dom == NULL);
1681  vals_setdomain = val_dom;
1682  }
1683  else
1684  {
1685  assert (dom != NULL);
1686  dom->next = val_dom;
1687  }
1688 
1689  dom = val_dom;
1690  }
1691  else
1692  {
1693  dom = idx_dom;
1694  }
1695 
1696  if (DB_IS_NULL (val))
1697  {
1698  if (is_iss && natts == 0)
1699  {
1700  /* We allow the first column to be NULL and we're not writing it in the MIDXKEY buffer */
1701  continue;
1702  }
1703  else
1704  {
1705  /* impossible case */
1706  assert_release (false);
1707  goto end;
1708  }
1709  }
1710 
1711  if (dom->type->index_lengthval == NULL)
1712  {
1713  buf_size += dom->type->disksize;
1714  }
1715  else
1716  {
1717  buf_size += (*(dom->type->index_lengthval)) (val);
1718  }
1719  }
1720 
1721  /* add more domain to setdomain for partial key */
1722  if (need_new_setdomain == true)
1723  {
1724  assert (dom != NULL);
1725  if (idx_dom != NULL)
1726  {
1727  val_dom = tp_domain_copy (idx_dom, false);
1728  if (val_dom == NULL)
1729  {
1730  goto err_exit;
1731  }
1732 
1733  dom->next = val_dom;
1734  }
1735  }
1736 
1737  midxkey.buf = (char *) db_private_alloc (thread_p, buf_size);
1738  if (midxkey.buf == NULL)
1739  {
1740  retval->need_clear = false;
1741  goto err_exit;
1742  }
1743 
1744  nullmap_ptr = midxkey.buf;
1745  key_ptr = nullmap_ptr + nullmap_size;
1746 
1747  OR_BUF_INIT (buf, key_ptr, buf_size - nullmap_size);
1748 
1749  if (nullmap_size > 0)
1750  {
1751  bits = (unsigned char *) nullmap_ptr;
1752  for (i = 0; i < nullmap_size; i++)
1753  {
1754  bits[i] = (unsigned char) 0;
1755  }
1756  }
1757 
1758  /* generate multi columns key (values -> midxkey.buf) */
1759  for (operand = func->value.funcp->operand, i = 0, dom = (vals_setdomain != NULL) ? vals_setdomain : idx_setdomain;
1760  operand != NULL && dom != NULL && (i < natts); operand = operand->next, dom = dom->next, i++)
1761  {
1762  if (has_coerced_values != NULL && has_coerced_values[i] == true)
1763  {
1764  assert (coerced_values != NULL);
1765  val = &coerced_values[i];
1766  }
1767  else
1768  {
1769  ret = fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, &(operand->value), vd, NULL, NULL, NULL, &val);
1770  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
1771  {
1772  goto err_exit;
1773  }
1774  }
1775 
1776  if (DB_IS_NULL (val))
1777  {
1778  if (is_iss && i == 0)
1779  {
1780  /* There is nothing to write for NULL. Just make sure the bit is not set */
1781  OR_CLEAR_BOUND_BIT (nullmap_ptr, i);
1782  continue;
1783  }
1784  else
1785  {
1786  /* impossible case */
1787  assert_release (false);
1788  goto end;
1789  }
1790  }
1791 
1792  (*((dom->type)->index_writeval)) (&buf, val);
1793  OR_ENABLE_BOUND_BIT (nullmap_ptr, i);
1794  }
1795 
1796  assert (buf_size == CAST_BUFLEN (buf.ptr - midxkey.buf));
1797 
1798  /* Make midxkey DB_VALUE */
1799  midxkey.size = buf_size;
1800  midxkey.ncolumns = natts;
1801 
1802  if (vals_setdomain != NULL)
1803  {
1804  midxkey.domain = tp_domain_construct (DB_TYPE_MIDXKEY, NULL, idx_ncols, 0, vals_setdomain);
1805  if (midxkey.domain == NULL)
1806  {
1807  goto err_exit;
1808  }
1809 
1810  midxkey.domain = tp_domain_cache (midxkey.domain);
1811  }
1812  else
1813  {
1814  midxkey.domain = btree_domainp;
1815  }
1816 
1817  ret = db_make_midxkey (retval, &midxkey);
1818  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
1819  {
1820  goto err_exit;
1821  }
1822 
1823  retval->need_clear = true;
1824 
1825  *indexable = true;
1826 
1827  ret = btree_coerce_key (retval, num_term, btree_domainp, key_minmax);
1828 
1829  if (has_coerced_values)
1830  {
1831  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, has_coerced_values);
1832  }
1833 
1834  if (coerced_values)
1835  {
1836  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, coerced_values);
1837  }
1838 
1839  return ret;
1840 
1841 end:
1842  if (midxkey.buf)
1843  {
1844  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, midxkey.buf);
1845  }
1846 
1847  if (vals_setdomain != NULL)
1848  {
1849  for (dom = vals_setdomain; dom != NULL; dom = next)
1850  {
1851  next = dom->next;
1852  tp_domain_free (dom);
1853  }
1854  }
1855 
1856  if (has_coerced_values)
1857  {
1858  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, has_coerced_values);
1859  }
1860 
1861  if (coerced_values)
1862  {
1863  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, coerced_values);
1864  }
1865 
1866  return ret;
1867 
1868 err_exit:
1869 
1870  if (ret == NO_ERROR && (ret = er_errid ()) == NO_ERROR)
1871  {
1872  ret = ER_FAILED;
1873  }
1874 
1875  goto end;
1876 }
1877 
1878 /*
1879  * scan_regu_key_to_index_key:
1880  */
1881 static int
1882 scan_regu_key_to_index_key (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, KEY_RANGE * key_ranges, KEY_VAL_RANGE * key_val_range,
1883  INDX_SCAN_ID * iscan_id, TP_DOMAIN * btree_domainp, VAL_DESCR * vd)
1884 {
1885  bool indexable = true;
1886  int key_minmax;
1887  int curr_key_prefix_length = 0;
1888  int count;
1889  int ret = NO_ERROR;
1890  REGU_VARIABLE_LIST requ_list;
1891  DB_TYPE db_type;
1892  int key_len;
1893 
1894  assert ((key_ranges->range >= GE_LE && key_ranges->range <= INF_LT) || (key_ranges->range == EQ_NA));
1895  assert (!(key_ranges->key1 == NULL && key_ranges->key2 == NULL));
1896 
1897  if (iscan_id->bt_attrs_prefix_length && iscan_id->bt_num_attrs == 1)
1898  {
1899  curr_key_prefix_length = iscan_id->bt_attrs_prefix_length[0];
1900  }
1901 
1902  if (key_ranges->key1)
1903  {
1904  if (key_ranges->key1->type == TYPE_FUNC && key_ranges->key1->value.funcp->ftype == F_MIDXKEY)
1905  {
1906  for (requ_list = key_ranges->key1->value.funcp->operand, count = 0; requ_list; requ_list = requ_list->next)
1907  {
1908  count++;
1909  }
1910  }
1911  else
1912  {
1913  count = 1;
1914  }
1915  key_val_range->num_index_term = count;
1916  }
1917 
1918  if (key_ranges->key2)
1919  {
1920  if (key_ranges->key2->type == TYPE_FUNC && key_ranges->key2->value.funcp->ftype == F_MIDXKEY)
1921  {
1922  for (requ_list = key_ranges->key2->value.funcp->operand, count = 0; requ_list; requ_list = requ_list->next)
1923  {
1924  count++;
1925  }
1926  }
1927  else
1928  {
1929  assert_release (key_val_range->num_index_term <= 1);
1930  count = 1;
1931  }
1932  key_val_range->num_index_term = MAX (key_val_range->num_index_term, count);
1933  }
1934 
1935  if (key_ranges->key1)
1936  {
1937  if (key_ranges->key1->type == TYPE_FUNC && key_ranges->key1->value.funcp->ftype == F_MIDXKEY)
1938  {
1939  if (key_val_range->range == GT_INF || key_val_range->range == GT_LE || key_val_range->range == GT_LT)
1940  {
1941  key_minmax = BTREE_COERCE_KEY_WITH_MAX_VALUE;
1942  }
1943  else
1944  {
1945  key_minmax = BTREE_COERCE_KEY_WITH_MIN_VALUE;
1946  }
1947 
1948  ret =
1949  scan_dbvals_to_midxkey (thread_p, &key_val_range->key1, &indexable, btree_domainp,
1950  key_val_range->num_index_term, key_ranges->key1, vd, key_minmax, iscan_id->iss.use);
1951  }
1952  else
1953  {
1954  ret = fetch_copy_dbval (thread_p, key_ranges->key1, vd, NULL, NULL, NULL, &key_val_range->key1);
1955  db_type = DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (&key_val_range->key1);
1956 
1957  if (ret == NO_ERROR && curr_key_prefix_length > 0)
1958  {
1959  if (TP_IS_CHAR_TYPE (db_type) || TP_IS_BIT_TYPE (db_type))
1960  {
1961  key_len = db_get_string_length (&key_val_range->key1);
1962 
1963  if (key_len > curr_key_prefix_length)
1964  {
1965  ret = db_string_truncate (&key_val_range->key1, curr_key_prefix_length);
1966  key_val_range->is_truncated = true;
1967  }
1968  }
1969  }
1970 
1971  assert (DB_VALUE_TYPE (&key_val_range->key1) != DB_TYPE_MIDXKEY);
1972  }
1973 
1974  if (ret != NO_ERROR || indexable == false)
1975  {
1976  key_val_range->range = NA_NA;
1977 
1978  return ret;
1979  }
1980  }
1981 
1982  if (key_ranges->key2)
1983  {
1984  if (key_ranges->key2->type == TYPE_FUNC && key_ranges->key2->value.funcp->ftype == F_MIDXKEY)
1985  {
1986  if (key_val_range->range == INF_LT || key_val_range->range == GE_LT || key_val_range->range == GT_LT)
1987  {
1988  key_minmax = BTREE_COERCE_KEY_WITH_MIN_VALUE;
1989  }
1990  else
1991  {
1992  key_minmax = BTREE_COERCE_KEY_WITH_MAX_VALUE;
1993  }
1994 
1995  ret =
1996  scan_dbvals_to_midxkey (thread_p, &key_val_range->key2, &indexable, btree_domainp,
1997  key_val_range->num_index_term, key_ranges->key2, vd, key_minmax, iscan_id->iss.use);
1998  }
1999  else
2000  {
2001  ret = fetch_copy_dbval (thread_p, key_ranges->key2, vd, NULL, NULL, NULL, &key_val_range->key2);
2002 
2003  db_type = DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (&key_val_range->key2);
2004 
2005  if (ret == NO_ERROR && curr_key_prefix_length > 0)
2006  {
2007  if (TP_IS_CHAR_TYPE (db_type) || TP_IS_BIT_TYPE (db_type))
2008  {
2009  key_len = db_get_string_length (&key_val_range->key2);
2010 
2011  if (key_len > curr_key_prefix_length)
2012  {
2013  ret = db_string_truncate (&key_val_range->key2, curr_key_prefix_length);
2014  key_val_range->is_truncated = true;
2015  }
2016  }
2017  }
2018 
2019  assert (DB_VALUE_TYPE (&key_val_range->key2) != DB_TYPE_MIDXKEY);
2020  }
2021 
2022  if (ret != NO_ERROR || indexable == false)
2023  {
2024  key_val_range->range = NA_NA;
2025 
2026  return ret;
2027  }
2028  }
2029  else
2030  {
2031  if (key_ranges->key1 == NULL)
2032  {
2033  /* impossible case */
2034  assert (false);
2035 
2036  key_val_range->range = NA_NA;
2037 
2038  return ER_FAILED;
2039  }
2040 
2041  if ((iscan_id->indx_info->range_type == R_KEY || iscan_id->indx_info->range_type == R_KEYLIST)
2042  && key_ranges->key1->type == TYPE_FUNC && key_ranges->key1->value.funcp->ftype == F_MIDXKEY)
2043  {
2044  assert (key_val_range->range == EQ_NA);
2045 
2046  key_minmax = BTREE_COERCE_KEY_WITH_MAX_VALUE;
2047 
2048  ret =
2049  scan_dbvals_to_midxkey (thread_p, &key_val_range->key2, &indexable, btree_domainp,
2050  key_val_range->num_index_term, key_ranges->key1, vd, key_minmax, iscan_id->iss.use);
2051  }
2052  else
2053  {
2054  ret = pr_clone_value (&key_val_range->key1, &key_val_range->key2);
2055  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
2056  {
2057  key_val_range->range = NA_NA;
2058 
2059  return ret;
2060  }
2061  }
2062  }
2063 
2064  if (key_val_range->range == EQ_NA)
2065  {
2066  key_val_range->range = GE_LE;
2067  }
2068 
2069  switch (iscan_id->indx_info->range_type)
2070  {
2071  case R_KEY:
2072  case R_KEYLIST:
2073  /* When key received as NULL, currently this is assumed an UNBOUND value and no object value in the index is
2074  * equal to NULL value in the index scan context. They can be equal to NULL only in the "is NULL" context. */
2075 
2076  /* to fix multi-column index NULL problem */
2077  if (DB_IS_NULL (&key_val_range->key1))
2078  {
2079  key_val_range->range = NA_NA;
2080 
2081  return ret;
2082  }
2083  break;
2084 
2085  case R_RANGE:
2086  case R_RANGELIST:
2087  /* When key received as NULL, currently this is assumed an UNBOUND value and no object value in the index is
2088  * equal to NULL value in the index scan context. They can be equal to NULL only in the "is NULL" context. */
2089  if (key_val_range->range >= GE_LE && key_val_range->range <= GT_LT)
2090  {
2091  /* to fix multi-column index NULL problem */
2092  if (DB_IS_NULL (&key_val_range->key1) || DB_IS_NULL (&key_val_range->key2))
2093  {
2094  key_val_range->range = NA_NA;
2095 
2096  return ret;
2097  }
2098  else
2099  {
2100  int c = DB_UNK;
2101 
2102  c = scan_key_compare (&key_val_range->key1, &key_val_range->key2, key_val_range->num_index_term);
2103 
2104  if (c == DB_UNK)
2105  {
2106  /* impossible case */
2107  assert_release (false);
2108 
2109  key_val_range->range = NA_NA;
2110 
2111  return ER_FAILED;
2112  }
2113  else if (c > 0)
2114  {
2115  key_val_range->range = NA_NA;
2116 
2117  return ret;
2118  }
2119  }
2120  }
2121  else if (key_val_range->range >= GE_INF && key_val_range->range <= GT_INF)
2122  {
2123  /* to fix multi-column index NULL problem */
2124  if (DB_IS_NULL (&key_val_range->key1))
2125  {
2126  key_val_range->range = NA_NA;
2127 
2128  return ret;
2129  }
2130  }
2131  else if (key_val_range->range >= INF_LE && key_val_range->range <= INF_LT)
2132  {
2133  /* to fix multi-column index NULL problem */
2134  if (DB_IS_NULL (&key_val_range->key2))
2135  {
2136  key_val_range->range = NA_NA;
2137 
2138  return ret;
2139  }
2140  }
2141  break;
2142 
2143  default:
2144  assert_release (false);
2145  break; /* impossible case */
2146  }
2147 
2148  return ret;
2149 }
2150 
2151 /*
2152  * scan_get_index_oidset () - Fetch the next group of set of object identifiers
2153  * from the index associated with the scan identifier.
2154  * return: NO_ERROR, or ER_code
2155  * s_id(in): Scan identifier
2156  *
2157  * Note: If you feel the need
2158  */
2159 static int
2160 scan_get_index_oidset (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, SCAN_ID * s_id, DB_BIGINT * key_limit_upper,
2161  DB_BIGINT * key_limit_lower)
2162 {
2163  INDX_SCAN_ID *iscan_id;
2164  FILTER_INFO key_filter;
2165  INDX_INFO *indx_infop;
2166  BTREE_SCAN *bts;
2167  int key_cnt, i;
2168  KEY_VAL_RANGE *key_vals;
2169  KEY_RANGE *key_ranges;
2170  RANGE range, saved_range;
2171  int ret = NO_ERROR;
2172  int curr_key_prefix_length = 0;
2173 
2174  /* pointer to INDX_SCAN_ID structure */
2175  iscan_id = &s_id->s.isid;
2176 
2177  /* pointer to INDX_INFO in INDX_SCAN_ID structure */
2178  indx_infop = iscan_id->indx_info;
2179 
2180  /* pointer to index scan info. structure */
2181  bts = &iscan_id->bt_scan;
2182 
2183  /* number of keys */
2184  if (iscan_id->curr_keyno == -1) /* very first time */
2185  {
2186  key_cnt = indx_infop->key_info.key_cnt;
2187  }
2188  else
2189  {
2190  key_cnt = iscan_id->key_cnt;
2191  }
2192 
2193  /* key values */
2194  key_vals = iscan_id->key_vals;
2195 
2196  /* key ranges */
2197  key_ranges = indx_infop->key_info.key_ranges;
2198 
2199  if (key_cnt < 1 || !key_vals || !key_ranges)
2200  {
2201  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_QPROC_INVALID_XASLNODE, 0);
2202  return ER_FAILED;
2203  }
2204 
2205  if (iscan_id->bt_attrs_prefix_length && iscan_id->bt_num_attrs == 1)
2206  {
2207  curr_key_prefix_length = iscan_id->bt_attrs_prefix_length[0];
2208  }
2209 
2210  /* if it is the first time of this scan */
2211  if (iscan_id->curr_keyno == -1 && indx_infop->key_info.key_cnt == key_cnt)
2212  {
2213  /* make DB_VALUE key values from KEY_VALS key ranges */
2214  for (i = 0; i < key_cnt; i++)
2215  {
2216  /* initialize DB_VALUE first for error case */
2217  key_vals[i].range = NA_NA;
2218  db_make_null (&key_vals[i].key1);
2219  db_make_null (&key_vals[i].key2);
2220  key_vals[i].is_truncated = false;
2221  key_vals[i].num_index_term = 0;
2222  }
2223 
2224  for (i = 0; i < key_cnt; i++)
2225  {
2226  key_vals[i].range = key_ranges[i].range;
2227  if (key_vals[i].range == INF_INF)
2228  {
2229  continue;
2230  }
2231 
2232  ret =
2233  scan_regu_key_to_index_key (thread_p, &key_ranges[i], &key_vals[i], iscan_id, bts->btid_int.key_type,
2234  s_id->vd);
2235 
2236  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
2237  {
2238  goto exit_on_error;
2239  }
2240 
2241  assert_release (key_vals[i].num_index_term > 0);
2242  }
2243 
2244  /* eliminating duplicated keys and merging ranges are required even though the query optimizer does them because
2245  * the search keys or ranges could be unbound values at optimization step such as join attribute */
2246  if (indx_infop->range_type == R_KEYLIST)
2247  {
2248  /* eliminate duplicated keys in the search key list */
2249  key_cnt = iscan_id->key_cnt = check_key_vals (key_vals, key_cnt, eliminate_duplicated_keys);
2250  }
2251  else if (indx_infop->range_type == R_RANGELIST)
2252  {
2253  /* merge search key ranges */
2254  key_cnt = iscan_id->key_cnt = check_key_vals (key_vals, key_cnt, merge_key_ranges);
2255  }
2256 
2257  /* if is order by skip and first column is descending, the order will be reversed so reverse the key ranges to be
2258  * desc. */
2259  if ((indx_infop->range_type == R_KEYLIST || indx_infop->range_type == R_RANGELIST)
2260  && ((indx_infop->orderby_desc && indx_infop->orderby_skip)
2261  || (indx_infop->groupby_desc && indx_infop->groupby_skip)))
2262  {
2263  /* in both cases we should reverse the key lists if we have a reverse order by or group by which is skipped */
2264  check_key_vals (key_vals, key_cnt, reverse_key_list);
2265  }
2266 
2267  if (key_cnt < 0)
2268  {
2269  goto exit_on_error;
2270  }
2271 
2272  iscan_id->curr_keyno = 0;
2273  }
2274 
2275  /*
2276  * init vars to execute B+tree key range search
2277  */
2278 
2279  ret = NO_ERROR;
2280 
2281  /* set key filter information */
2282  scan_init_filter_info (&key_filter, &iscan_id->key_pred, &iscan_id->key_attrs, s_id->val_list, s_id->vd,
2283  &iscan_id->cls_oid, iscan_id->bt_num_attrs, iscan_id->bt_attr_ids, &iscan_id->num_vstr,
2284  iscan_id->vstr_ids);
2285  iscan_id->oids_count = 0;
2286  key_filter.func_idx_col_id = iscan_id->indx_info->func_idx_col_id;
2287 
2288  if (iscan_id->multi_range_opt.use && iscan_id->multi_range_opt.cnt > 0)
2289  {
2290  /* reset any previous results for multiple range optimization */
2291  int i;
2292 
2293  for (i = 0; i < iscan_id->multi_range_opt.cnt; i++)
2294  {
2295  if (iscan_id->multi_range_opt.top_n_items[i] != NULL)
2296  {
2297  pr_clear_value (&(iscan_id->multi_range_opt.top_n_items[i]->index_value));
2298  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, iscan_id->multi_range_opt.top_n_items[i]);
2299  }
2300  }
2301 
2302  iscan_id->multi_range_opt.cnt = 0;
2303  }
2304 
2305  /* if the end of this scan */
2306  if (iscan_id->curr_keyno > key_cnt)
2307  {
2308  return NO_ERROR;
2309  }
2310  else
2311  {
2312  /* Clear output val list to avoid memory leak. */
2313  REGU_VARIABLE_LIST p;
2314  for (p = iscan_id->indx_cov.regu_val_list; p; p = p->next)
2315  {
2316  pr_clear_value (p->value.vfetch_to);
2317  }
2318  }
2319 
2320  switch (indx_infop->range_type)
2321  {
2322  case R_KEY:
2323  /* key value search */
2324 
2325  /* check prerequisite condition */
2326  range = key_vals[0].range;
2327 
2328  if (range == NA_NA)
2329  {
2330  /* skip this key value */
2331  iscan_id->curr_keyno++;
2332  break;
2333  }
2334 
2335  if (key_cnt != 1)
2336  {
2337  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_QPROC_INVALID_XASLNODE, 0);
2338  goto exit_on_error;
2339  }
2340 
2341  ret =
2342  btree_prepare_bts (thread_p, bts, &indx_infop->btid, iscan_id, &key_vals[0], &key_filter,
2343  &iscan_id->cls_oid, key_limit_upper, key_limit_lower, true, NULL);
2344  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
2345  {
2346  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
2347  goto exit_on_error;
2348  }
2349  ret = btree_range_scan (thread_p, bts, btree_range_scan_select_visible_oids);
2350  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
2351  {
2352  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
2353  goto exit_on_error;
2354  }
2355  iscan_id->oids_count = bts->n_oids_read_last_iteration;
2356  assert (iscan_id->oids_count >= 0);
2357 
2358  /* We only want to advance the key ptr if we've exhausted the current crop of oids on the current key. */
2359  if (BTREE_END_OF_SCAN (bts))
2360  {
2361  iscan_id->curr_keyno++;
2362  }
2363 
2364  if (iscan_id->multi_range_opt.use)
2365  {
2366  /* with multiple range optimization, we store the only the top N OIDS or index keys: the only valid exit
2367  * condition from 'btree_range_search' is when the index scan has reached the end for this key */
2368  assert (BTREE_END_OF_SCAN (bts));
2369  }
2370 
2371  break;
2372 
2373  case R_RANGE:
2374  /* range search */
2375 
2376  /* check prerequisite condition */
2377  saved_range = range = key_vals[0].range;
2378 
2379  if (range == NA_NA)
2380  {
2381  /* skip this key value */
2382  iscan_id->curr_keyno++;
2383  break;
2384  }
2385 
2386  if (key_cnt != 1 || range < GE_LE || range > INF_INF)
2387  {
2388  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_QPROC_INVALID_XASLNODE, 0);
2389  goto exit_on_error;
2390  }
2391 
2392  if (range >= GE_INF && range <= GT_INF)
2393  {
2394  pr_clear_value (&key_vals[0].key2);
2395  PRIM_SET_NULL (&key_vals[0].key2);
2396  }
2397 
2398  if (range >= INF_LE && range <= INF_LT)
2399  {
2400  pr_clear_value (&key_vals[0].key1);
2401  PRIM_SET_NULL (&key_vals[0].key1);
2402  }
2403 
2404  if (key_vals[0].is_truncated == true)
2405  { /* specially, key value search */
2406  range = GE_LE;
2407  }
2408 
2409  if (range == INF_INF)
2410  {
2411  /* if we reached the key count limit, break */
2412  if (iscan_id->curr_keyno >= key_cnt)
2413  {
2414  iscan_id->curr_keyno++;
2415  break;
2416  }
2417 
2418  pr_clear_value (&key_vals[0].key1);
2419  pr_clear_value (&key_vals[0].key2);
2420  PRIM_SET_NULL (&key_vals[0].key1);
2421  PRIM_SET_NULL (&key_vals[0].key2);
2422 
2423  assert_release (key_vals[0].num_index_term == 0);
2424  }
2425 
2426  key_vals[0].range = range;
2427  ret =
2428  btree_prepare_bts (thread_p, bts, &indx_infop->btid, iscan_id, &key_vals[0], &key_filter,
2429  &iscan_id->cls_oid, key_limit_upper, key_limit_lower, true, NULL);
2430  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
2431  {
2432  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
2433  goto exit_on_error;
2434  }
2435  ret = btree_range_scan (thread_p, bts, btree_range_scan_select_visible_oids);
2436  key_vals[0].range = saved_range;
2437  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
2438  {
2439  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
2440  goto exit_on_error;
2441  }
2442  iscan_id->oids_count = bts->n_oids_read_last_iteration;
2443  assert (iscan_id->oids_count >= 0);
2444 
2445  /* We only want to advance the key ptr if we've exhausted the current crop of oids on the current key. */
2446  if (BTREE_END_OF_SCAN (bts))
2447  {
2448  iscan_id->curr_keyno++;
2449  }
2450 
2451  if (iscan_id->multi_range_opt.use)
2452  {
2453  /* with multiple range optimization, we store the only the top N OIDS or index keys: the only valid exit
2454  * condition from 'btree_range_search' is when the index scan has reached the end for this key */
2455  assert (BTREE_END_OF_SCAN (bts));
2456  }
2457  break;
2458 
2459  case R_KEYLIST:
2460  /* multiple key value search */
2461 
2462  /* for each key value */
2463  while (iscan_id->curr_keyno < key_cnt)
2464  {
2465  /* check prerequisite condition */
2466  range = key_vals[iscan_id->curr_keyno].range;
2467 
2468  if (range == NA_NA)
2469  {
2470  /* skip this key value and continue to the next */
2471  iscan_id->curr_keyno++;
2472  if (key_limit_upper && !key_limit_lower && indx_infop->key_info.key_limit_reset)
2473  {
2474  if (scan_init_index_key_limit (thread_p, iscan_id, &indx_infop->key_info, s_id->vd) != NO_ERROR)
2475  {
2476  goto exit_on_error;
2477  }
2478  *key_limit_upper = iscan_id->key_limit_upper;
2479  }
2480  continue;
2481  }
2482 
2483  ret =
2484  btree_prepare_bts (thread_p, bts, &indx_infop->btid, iscan_id, &key_vals[iscan_id->curr_keyno],
2485  &key_filter, &iscan_id->cls_oid, key_limit_upper, key_limit_lower, true, NULL);
2486  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
2487  {
2488  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
2489  goto exit_on_error;
2490  }
2491  ret = btree_range_scan (thread_p, bts, btree_range_scan_select_visible_oids);
2492  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
2493  {
2494  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
2495  goto exit_on_error;
2496  }
2497  iscan_id->oids_count = bts->n_oids_read_last_iteration;
2498  assert (iscan_id->oids_count >= 0);
2499 
2500  /* We only want to advance the key ptr if we've exhausted the current crop of oids on the current key. */
2501  if (BTREE_END_OF_SCAN (bts))
2502  {
2503  iscan_id->curr_keyno++;
2504  /* reset upper key limit, if flag is set */
2505  if (key_limit_upper && !key_limit_lower && indx_infop->key_info.key_limit_reset)
2506  {
2507  if (scan_init_index_key_limit (thread_p, iscan_id, &indx_infop->key_info, s_id->vd) != NO_ERROR)
2508  {
2509  goto exit_on_error;
2510  }
2511  *key_limit_upper = iscan_id->key_limit_upper;
2512  }
2513  }
2514 
2515  if (iscan_id->multi_range_opt.use)
2516  {
2517  /* with multiple range optimization, we store the only the top N OIDS or index keys: the only valid exit
2518  * condition from 'btree_range_search' is when the index scan has reached the end for this key */
2519  assert (BTREE_END_OF_SCAN (bts));
2520  /* continue loop : exhaust all keys in one shot when in multiple range search optimization mode */
2521  continue;
2522  }
2523  if (iscan_id->oids_count > 0)
2524  {
2525  /* we've got some result */
2526  break;
2527  }
2528  }
2529 
2530  break;
2531 
2532  case R_RANGELIST:
2533  /* multiple range search */
2534 
2535  /* for each key value */
2536  while (iscan_id->curr_keyno < key_cnt)
2537  {
2538  /* check prerequisite condition */
2539  saved_range = range = key_vals[iscan_id->curr_keyno].range;
2540 
2541  if (range == NA_NA)
2542  {
2543  /* skip this key value and continue to the next */
2544  iscan_id->curr_keyno++;
2545  if (key_limit_upper && !key_limit_lower && indx_infop->key_info.key_limit_reset)
2546  {
2547  if (scan_init_index_key_limit (thread_p, iscan_id, &indx_infop->key_info, s_id->vd) != NO_ERROR)
2548  {
2549  goto exit_on_error;
2550  }
2551  *key_limit_upper = iscan_id->key_limit_upper;
2552  }
2553  continue;
2554  }
2555 
2556  if (range < GE_LE || range > INF_INF)
2557  {
2558  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_QPROC_INVALID_XASLNODE, 0);
2559  goto exit_on_error;
2560  }
2561 
2562  if (range >= GE_INF && range <= GT_INF)
2563  {
2564  pr_clear_value (&key_vals[iscan_id->curr_keyno].key2);
2565  PRIM_SET_NULL (&key_vals[iscan_id->curr_keyno].key2);
2566  }
2567 
2568  if (key_vals[iscan_id->curr_keyno].is_truncated == true)
2569  { /* specially, key value search */
2570  range = GE_LE;
2571  }
2572 
2573  if (range >= INF_LE && range <= INF_LT)
2574  {
2575  pr_clear_value (&key_vals[iscan_id->curr_keyno].key1);
2576  PRIM_SET_NULL (&key_vals[iscan_id->curr_keyno].key1);
2577  }
2578 
2579  if (range == INF_INF)
2580  {
2581  if (key_cnt != 1)
2582  {
2583  assert_release (0);
2584  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_QPROC_INVALID_XASLNODE, 0);
2585  goto exit_on_error;
2586  }
2587 
2588  /* if we reached the key count limit, break */
2589  if (iscan_id->curr_keyno >= key_cnt)
2590  {
2591  iscan_id->curr_keyno++;
2592  break;
2593  }
2594 
2595  pr_clear_value (&key_vals[0].key1);
2596  pr_clear_value (&key_vals[0].key2);
2597  PRIM_SET_NULL (&key_vals[0].key1);
2598  PRIM_SET_NULL (&key_vals[0].key2);
2599  }
2600 
2601  key_vals[iscan_id->curr_keyno].range = range;
2602  ret =
2603  btree_prepare_bts (thread_p, bts, &indx_infop->btid, iscan_id, &key_vals[iscan_id->curr_keyno],
2604  &key_filter, &iscan_id->cls_oid, key_limit_upper, key_limit_lower, true, NULL);
2605  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
2606  {
2607  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
2608  goto exit_on_error;
2609  }
2610  ret = btree_range_scan (thread_p, bts, btree_range_scan_select_visible_oids);
2611  key_vals[iscan_id->curr_keyno].range = saved_range;
2612  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
2613  {
2614  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
2615  goto exit_on_error;
2616  }
2617  iscan_id->oids_count = bts->n_oids_read_last_iteration;
2618  assert (iscan_id->oids_count >= 0);
2619 
2620  /* We only want to advance the key ptr if we've exhausted the current crop of oids on the current key. */
2621  if (BTREE_END_OF_SCAN (bts))
2622  {
2623  iscan_id->curr_keyno++;
2624  /* reset upper key limit, if flag is set */
2625  if (key_limit_upper && !key_limit_lower && indx_infop->key_info.key_limit_reset)
2626  {
2627  if (scan_init_index_key_limit (thread_p, iscan_id, &indx_infop->key_info, s_id->vd) != NO_ERROR)
2628  {
2629  goto exit_on_error;
2630  }
2631  *key_limit_upper = iscan_id->key_limit_upper;
2632  }
2633  }
2634 
2635  if (iscan_id->multi_range_opt.use)
2636  {
2637  /* with multiple range optimization, we store the only the top N OIDS or index keys: the only valid exit
2638  * condition from 'btree_range_search' is when the index scan has reached the end for this key */
2639  assert (BTREE_END_OF_SCAN (bts));
2640  /* continue loop : exhaust all keys in one shot when in multiple range search optimization mode */
2641  continue;
2642  }
2643  if (iscan_id->oids_count > 0)
2644  {
2645  /* we've got some result */
2646  break;
2647  }
2648  }
2649 
2650  break;
2651 
2652  default:
2653  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_QPROC_INVALID_XASLNODE, 0);
2654  goto exit_on_error;
2655 
2656  }
2657 
2658  /* When covering index is used, 'index_scan_in_oid_order' parameter is ignored. */
2659  if (iscan_id->oid_list != NULL && iscan_id->oid_list->oidp != NULL && iscan_id->oids_count > 1
2660  && iscan_id->iscan_oid_order == true && iscan_id->need_count_only == false)
2661  {
2662  qsort (iscan_id->oid_list->oidp, iscan_id->oids_count, sizeof (OID), oid_compare);
2663  }
2664 
2665 end:
2666 
2667  if (key_limit_upper != NULL && *key_limit_upper == 0)
2668  {
2669  /* End scan here! */
2670  iscan_id->curr_keyno = key_cnt;
2671  }
2672 
2673  /* if the end of this scan */
2674  if (iscan_id->curr_keyno == key_cnt)
2675  {
2676  for (i = 0; i < key_cnt; i++)
2677  {
2678  pr_clear_value (&key_vals[i].key1);
2679  pr_clear_value (&key_vals[i].key2);
2680  }
2681  iscan_id->curr_keyno++; /* to prevent duplicate frees */
2682  }
2683 
2684  if (thread_is_on_trace (thread_p))
2685  {
2686  s_id->scan_stats.read_keys += iscan_id->bt_scan.read_keys;
2687  iscan_id->bt_scan.read_keys = 0;
2688  s_id->scan_stats.qualified_keys += iscan_id->bt_scan.qualified_keys;
2689  iscan_id->bt_scan.qualified_keys = 0;
2690  }
2691 
2692  return ret;
2693 
2694 exit_on_error:
2695  iscan_id->curr_keyno = key_cnt; /* set as end of this scan */
2696 
2697  ret = (ret == NO_ERROR && (ret = er_errid ()) == NO_ERROR) ? ER_FAILED : ret;
2698  goto end;
2699 }
2700 
2701 /*
2702  *
2703  * SCAN MANAGEMENT ROUTINES
2704  *
2705  */
2706 
2707 /*
2708  * scan_init_scan_id () -
2709  * return:
2710  * scan_id(out): Scan identifier
2711  * mvcc_select_lock_needed(in):
2712  * scan_op_type(in): scan operation type
2713  * fixed(in):
2714  * grouped(in):
2715  * single_fetch(in):
2716  * join_dbval(in):
2717  * val_list(in):
2718  * vd(in):
2719  *
2720  * Note: If you feel the need
2721  */
2722 static void
2723 scan_init_scan_id (SCAN_ID * scan_id, bool mvcc_select_lock_needed, SCAN_OPERATION_TYPE scan_op_type, int fixed,
2724  int grouped, QPROC_SINGLE_FETCH single_fetch, DB_VALUE * join_dbval, VAL_LIST * val_list,
2725  VAL_DESCR * vd)
2726 {
2727  scan_id->status = S_OPENED;
2728  scan_id->position = S_BEFORE;
2729  scan_id->direction = S_FORWARD;
2730 
2731  scan_id->mvcc_select_lock_needed = mvcc_select_lock_needed;
2732  scan_id->scan_op_type = scan_op_type;
2733  scan_id->fixed = fixed;
2734 
2735  scan_id->grouped = grouped; /* is it grouped or single scan? */
2736  scan_id->qualified_block = false;
2737  scan_id->single_fetch = single_fetch;
2738  scan_id->single_fetched = false;
2739  scan_id->null_fetched = false;
2740  scan_id->qualification = QPROC_QUALIFIED;
2741 
2742  /* join term */
2743  scan_id->join_dbval = join_dbval;
2744 
2745  /* value list and descriptor */
2746  scan_id->val_list = val_list; /* points to the XASL tree */
2747  scan_id->vd = vd; /* set value descriptor pointer */
2748  scan_id->scan_immediately_stop = false;
2749 }
2750 
2751 /*
2752  * scan_open_heap_scan () -
2753  * return: NO_ERROR
2754  * scan_id(out): Scan identifier
2755  * mvcc_select_lock_needed(in):
2756  * scan_op_type(in): scan operation type
2757  * fixed(in):
2758  * grouped(in):
2759  * single_fetch(in):
2760  * join_dbval(in):
2761  * val_list(in):
2762  * vd(in):
2763  * cls_oid(in):
2764  * hfid(in):
2765  * regu_list_pred(in):
2766  * pr(in):
2767  * regu_list_rest(in):
2768  * num_attrs_pred(in):
2769  * attrids_pred(in):
2770  * cache_pred(in):
2771  * num_attrs_rest(in):
2772  * attrids_rest(in):
2773  * cache_rest(in):
2774  * cache_recordinfo(in):
2775  * regu_list_recordinfo(in):
2776  *
2777  * Note: If you feel the need
2778  */
2779 int
2780 scan_open_heap_scan (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, SCAN_ID * scan_id,
2781  /* fields of SCAN_ID */
2782  bool mvcc_select_lock_needed, SCAN_OPERATION_TYPE scan_op_type, int fixed, int grouped,
2783  QPROC_SINGLE_FETCH single_fetch, DB_VALUE * join_dbval, VAL_LIST * val_list, VAL_DESCR * vd,
2784  /* fields of HEAP_SCAN_ID */
2785  OID * cls_oid, HFID * hfid, REGU_VARIABLE_LIST regu_list_pred, PRED_EXPR * pr,
2786  REGU_VARIABLE_LIST regu_list_rest, int num_attrs_pred, ATTR_ID * attrids_pred,
2787  HEAP_CACHE_ATTRINFO * cache_pred, int num_attrs_rest, ATTR_ID * attrids_rest,
2788  HEAP_CACHE_ATTRINFO * cache_rest, SCAN_TYPE scan_type, DB_VALUE ** cache_recordinfo,
2789  REGU_VARIABLE_LIST regu_list_recordinfo)
2790 {
2791  HEAP_SCAN_ID *hsidp;
2792  DB_TYPE single_node_type = DB_TYPE_NULL;
2793 
2794  /* scan type is HEAP SCAN or HEAP SCAN RECORD INFO */
2795  assert (scan_type == S_HEAP_SCAN || scan_type == S_HEAP_SCAN_RECORD_INFO);
2796  scan_id->type = scan_type;
2797 
2798  /* initialize SCAN_ID structure */
2799  scan_init_scan_id (scan_id, mvcc_select_lock_needed, scan_op_type, fixed, grouped, single_fetch, join_dbval, val_list,
2800  vd);
2801 
2802  /* initialize HEAP_SCAN_ID structure */
2803  hsidp = &scan_id->s.hsid;
2804 
2805  /* class object OID */
2806  COPY_OID (&hsidp->cls_oid, cls_oid);
2807 
2808  /* heap file identifier */
2809  hsidp->hfid = *hfid; /* bitwise copy */
2810 
2811  /* OID within the heap */
2812  UT_CAST_TO_NULL_HEAP_OID (&hsidp->hfid, &hsidp->curr_oid);
2813 
2814  /* scan predicates */
2815  scan_init_scan_pred (&hsidp->scan_pred, regu_list_pred, pr,
2816  ((pr) ? eval_fnc (thread_p, pr, &single_node_type) : NULL));
2817  /* attribute information from predicates */
2818  scan_init_scan_attrs (&hsidp->pred_attrs, num_attrs_pred, attrids_pred, cache_pred);
2819 
2820  /* regulator variable list for other than predicates */
2821  hsidp->rest_regu_list = regu_list_rest;
2822 
2823  /* attribute information from other than predicates */
2824  scan_init_scan_attrs (&hsidp->rest_attrs, num_attrs_rest, attrids_rest, cache_rest);
2825 
2826  /* flags */
2827  /* do not reset hsidp->caches_inited here */
2828  hsidp->scancache_inited = false;
2829  hsidp->scanrange_inited = false;
2830 
2831  hsidp->cache_recordinfo = cache_recordinfo;
2832  hsidp->recordinfo_regu_list = regu_list_recordinfo;
2833 
2834  return NO_ERROR;
2835 }

2837 /*
2838  * scan_open_heap_page_scan () - Opens a page by page heap scan.
2839  *
2840  * return : Error code.
2841  * thread_p (in) :
2842  * scan_id (in) :
2843  * val_list (in) :
2844  * vd (in) :
2845  * cls_oid (in) :
2846  * hfid (in) :
2847  * pr (in) :
2848  * scan_type (in) :
2849  * cache_page_info (in) :
2850  * regu_list_page_info (in) :
2851  */
2852 int
2853 scan_open_heap_page_scan (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, SCAN_ID * scan_id,
2854  /* fields of SCAN_ID */
2855  VAL_LIST * val_list, VAL_DESCR * vd,
2856  /* fields of HEAP_SCAN_ID */
2857  OID * cls_oid, HFID * hfid, PRED_EXPR * pr, SCAN_TYPE scan_type, DB_VALUE ** cache_page_info,
2858  REGU_VARIABLE_LIST regu_list_page_info)
2859 {
2860  HEAP_PAGE_SCAN_ID *hpsidp = NULL;
2861  DB_TYPE single_node_type = DB_TYPE_NULL;
2862 
2863  scan_id->type = scan_type;
2864 
2865  scan_init_scan_id (scan_id, true, S_SELECT, true, false, QPROC_NO_SINGLE_INNER, NULL, val_list, vd);
2866 
2867  hpsidp = &scan_id->s.hpsid;
2868 
2869  COPY_OID (&hpsidp->cls_oid, cls_oid);
2870  hpsidp->hfid = *hfid;
2871  hpsidp->cache_page_info = cache_page_info;
2872  hpsidp->page_info_regu_list = regu_list_page_info;
2873  scan_init_scan_pred (&hpsidp->scan_pred, NULL, pr, (pr == NULL) ? NULL : eval_fnc (thread_p, pr, &single_node_type));
2874  VPID_SET_NULL (&hpsidp->curr_vpid);
2875  return NO_ERROR;
2876 }

2878 /*
