2880  * return: NO_ERROR
2881  * scan_id(out): Scan identifier
2882  * grouped(in):
2883  * single_fetch(in):
2884  * join_dbval(in):
2885  * val_list(in):
2886  * vd(in):
2887  * cls_oid(in):
2888  * hfid(in):
2889  * regu_list_pred(in):
2890  * pr(in):
2891  * regu_list_rest(in):
2892  * num_attrs_pred(in):
2893  * attrids_pred(in):
2894  * cache_pred(in):
2895  * num_attrs_rest(in):
2896  * attrids_rest(in):
2897  * cache_rest(in):
2898  *
2899  * Note: If you feel the need
2900  */
2901 int
2902 scan_open_class_attr_scan (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, SCAN_ID * scan_id,
2903  /* fields of SCAN_ID */
2904  int grouped, QPROC_SINGLE_FETCH single_fetch, DB_VALUE * join_dbval, VAL_LIST * val_list,
2905  VAL_DESCR * vd,
2906  /* fields of HEAP_SCAN_ID */
2907  OID * cls_oid, HFID * hfid, REGU_VARIABLE_LIST regu_list_pred, PRED_EXPR * pr,
2908  REGU_VARIABLE_LIST regu_list_rest, int num_attrs_pred, ATTR_ID * attrids_pred,
2909  HEAP_CACHE_ATTRINFO * cache_pred, int num_attrs_rest, ATTR_ID * attrids_rest,
2910  HEAP_CACHE_ATTRINFO * cache_rest)
2911 {
2912  HEAP_SCAN_ID *hsidp;
2913  DB_TYPE single_node_type = DB_TYPE_NULL;
2914 
2915  /* scan type is CLASS ATTR SCAN */
2916  scan_id->type = S_CLASS_ATTR_SCAN;
2917 
2918  /* initialize SCAN_ID structure */
2919  /* mvcc_select_lock_needed = false, fixed = true */
2920  scan_init_scan_id (scan_id, false, S_SELECT, true, grouped, single_fetch, join_dbval, val_list, vd);
2921 
2922  /* initialize HEAP_SCAN_ID structure */
2923  hsidp = &scan_id->s.hsid;
2924 
2925  /* class object OID */
2926  COPY_OID (&hsidp->cls_oid, cls_oid);
2927  /* heap file identifier */
2928  hsidp->hfid = *hfid; /* bitwise copy */
2929  /* OID within the heap */
2930  UT_CAST_TO_NULL_HEAP_OID (&hsidp->hfid, &hsidp->curr_oid);
2931 
2932  /* scan predicates */
2933  scan_init_scan_pred (&hsidp->scan_pred, regu_list_pred, pr,
2934  ((pr) ? eval_fnc (thread_p, pr, &single_node_type) : NULL));
2935  /* attribute information from predicates */
2936  scan_init_scan_attrs (&hsidp->pred_attrs, num_attrs_pred, attrids_pred, cache_pred);
2937  /* regulator vairable list for other than predicates */
2938  hsidp->rest_regu_list = regu_list_rest;
2939  /* attribute information from other than predicates */
2940  scan_init_scan_attrs (&hsidp->rest_attrs, num_attrs_rest, attrids_rest, cache_rest);

2945  hsidp->scanrange_inited = false;

3201  }
3202

3204  if (TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (BTS->btid_int.key_type) == DB_TYPE_MIDXKEY)
3205  {

3207  need_copy_buf = true;
3208  }
3209  else
3210  { /* single-column index */
3211  if (indx_info->key_info.key_ranges[0].range != EQ_NA)
3212  {
3213  /* found single-column key-range, not key-val */
3214  if (QSTR_IS_ANY_CHAR_OR_BIT (TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (BTS->btid_int.key_type)))
3215  {
3216  /* this type needs index key copy_buf */
3217  need_copy_buf = true;

3226  if (isidp->copy_buf == NULL)

3249  goto exit_on_error;
3250  }
3251

3253  {
3254  bool use_multi_range_opt = (isidp->bt_num_attrs > 1 && isidp->indx_info->key_info.key_limit_reset == true
3255  && isidp->key_limit_upper > 0 && isidp->key_limit_upper < DB_INT32_MAX
3256  && isidp->key_limit_lower == -1) ? true : false;
3257 
3258  if (scan_init_multi_range_optimization (thread_p, &(isidp->multi_range_opt), use_multi_range_opt,

3268 
3269 exit_on_error:
3270 
3271  if (isidp->key_vals)
3272  {
3273  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->key_vals);
3274  }
3275  if (isidp->bt_attr_ids)
3276  {
3277  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->bt_attr_ids);
3278  }
3279  if (isidp->vstr_ids)
3280  {
3281  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->vstr_ids);
3282  }
3283  if (isidp->oid_list != NULL)

3285  scan_free_iscan_oid_buf_list (isidp->oid_list);
3286  isidp->oid_list = NULL;
3287  }
3288  if (isidp->copy_buf)
3289  {
3290  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->copy_buf);
3291  }
3292  if (isidp->indx_cov.type_list != NULL)
3293  {
3294  if (isidp->indx_cov.type_list->domp != NULL)
3295  {
3296  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->indx_cov.type_list->domp);
3297  }
3298  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->indx_cov.type_list);
3299  }
3300  if (isidp->indx_cov.list_id != NULL)
3301  {
3302  QFILE_FREE_AND_INIT_LIST_ID (isidp->indx_cov.list_id);
3303  }
3304  if (isidp->indx_cov.tplrec != NULL)
3305  {
3306  if (isidp->indx_cov.tplrec->tpl != NULL)
3307  {
3308  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->indx_cov.tplrec->tpl);
3309  }
3310  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->indx_cov.tplrec);
3311  }
3312  if (isidp->indx_cov.lsid != NULL)
3313  {
3314  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->indx_cov.lsid);
3315  }
3316 
3317  return (ret == NO_ERROR && (ret = er_errid ()) == NO_ERROR) ? ER_FAILED : ret;

3483  if (isidp->key_vals)
3484  {
3485  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->key_vals);
3486  }
3487  if (isidp->bt_attr_ids)
3488  {
3489  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->bt_attr_ids);
3490  }
3491  if (isidp->vstr_ids)
3492  {
3493  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->vstr_ids);
3494  }
3495  assert (isidp->oid_list == NULL);
3496  if (isidp->copy_buf)
3497  {
3498  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->copy_buf);
3499  }
3500  if (isidp->indx_cov.type_list != NULL)
3501  {
3502  if (isidp->indx_cov.type_list->domp != NULL)
3503  {
3504  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->indx_cov.type_list->domp);
3505  }
3506  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->indx_cov.type_list);
3507  }
3508  if (isidp->indx_cov.list_id != NULL)
3509  {
3510  QFILE_FREE_AND_INIT_LIST_ID (isidp->indx_cov.list_id);
3511  }
3512  if (isidp->indx_cov.tplrec != NULL)
3513  {
3514  if (isidp->indx_cov.tplrec->tpl != NULL)
3515  {
3516  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->indx_cov.tplrec->tpl);
3517  }
3518  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->indx_cov.tplrec);
3519  }
3520  if (isidp->indx_cov.lsid != NULL)
3521  {
3522  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->indx_cov.lsid);
3523  }
3524 
3525  return (ret == NO_ERROR && (ret = er_errid ()) == NO_ERROR) ? ER_FAILED : ret;
3526 }

3528 /*
3529  * scan_open_index_node_info_scan () - Opens a scan on b-tree nodes.
3530  *
3531  * return : Error code.
3532  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry.
3533  * scan_id (out) : Scan data.
3534  * val_list (in) : XASL value list.
3535  * vd (in) : XASL value descriptors.
3536  * indx_info (in) : Index info.
3537  * pr (in) : Scan predicate.
3538  * node_info_values (in) : Array of value pointers to store b-tree node
3539  * information.
3540  * node_info_regu_list (in) : Regulator variable list.
3541  */
3542 int
3543 scan_open_index_node_info_scan (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, SCAN_ID * scan_id,
3544  /* fields of SCAN_ID */
3545  VAL_LIST * val_list, VAL_DESCR * vd,
3546  /* fields of INDX_SCAN_ID */
3547  INDX_INFO * indx_info, PRED_EXPR * pr, DB_VALUE ** node_info_values,
3548  REGU_VARIABLE_LIST node_info_regu_list)
3549 {
3550  INDEX_NODE_SCAN_ID *idx_nsid_p = NULL;
3551  VPID root_vpid;
3552  PAGE_PTR root_page = NULL;
3553  BTREE_ROOT_HEADER *root_header = NULL;
3554  DB_TYPE single_node_type = DB_TYPE_NULL;
3555  BTID *btid = NULL;
3556 
3557  assert (scan_id != NULL);
3558 
3559  scan_id->type = S_INDX_NODE_INFO_SCAN;
3560 
3561  /* initialize SCAN_ID structure */
3562  scan_init_scan_id (scan_id, 1, S_SELECT, false, false, QPROC_NO_SINGLE_INNER, NULL, val_list, vd);
3563 
3564  idx_nsid_p = &scan_id->s.insid;
3565  idx_nsid_p->indx_info = indx_info;
3566 
3567  /* scan predicate */
3568  scan_init_scan_pred (&idx_nsid_p->scan_pred, NULL, pr, ((pr) ? eval_fnc (thread_p, pr, &single_node_type) : NULL));
3569 
3570  BTREE_NODE_SCAN_INIT (&idx_nsid_p->btns);
3571 
3572  /* read root_page page header info */
3573  btid = &indx_info->btid;
3574 
3575  root_vpid.pageid = btid->root_pageid;
3576  root_vpid.volid = btid->vfid.volid;
3577 
3578  root_page = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &root_vpid, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_READ, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
3579  if (root_page == NULL)
3580  {
3581  return ER_FAILED;
3582  }
3583  root_header = btree_get_root_header (thread_p, root_page);
3584  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, root_page);
3585 
3586  /* construct BTID_INT structure */
3587  idx_nsid_p->btns.btid_int.sys_btid = btid;
3588  if (btree_glean_root_header_info (thread_p, root_header, &idx_nsid_p->btns.btid_int) != NO_ERROR)
3589  {
3590  return ER_FAILED;
3591  }
3592 
3593  idx_nsid_p->node_info_values = node_info_values;
3594  idx_nsid_p->node_info_regu_list = node_info_regu_list;
3595  idx_nsid_p->caches_inited = false;
3596 
3597  return NO_ERROR;
3598 }

3649 /*
3650  * scan_open_showstmt_scan () -
3651  * return: NO_ERROR
3652  * scan_id(out): Scan identifier
3653  * grouped(in):
3654  * single_fetch(in):
3655  * join_dbval(in):
3656  * val_list(in):
3657  * vd(in):
3658  * show_type(in):
3659  * arg_list(in):
3660  */
3661 int
3662 scan_open_showstmt_scan (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, SCAN_ID * scan_id,
3663  /* fields of SCAN_ID */
3664  int grouped, QPROC_SINGLE_FETCH single_fetch, DB_VALUE * join_dbval, VAL_LIST * val_list,
3665  VAL_DESCR * vd,
3666  /* fields of SHOWSTMT_SCAN_ID */
3667  PRED_EXPR * pr, SHOWSTMT_TYPE show_type, REGU_VARIABLE_LIST arg_list)
3668 {
3669  SHOWSTMT_SCAN_ID *stsidp;
3670  int i, arg_cnt, out_cnt;
3671  REGU_VARIABLE_LIST regu_var_p;
3672  REGU_VARIABLE *regu;
3673  QPROC_DB_VALUE_LIST valp;
3674  DB_VALUE **arg_values = NULL, **out_values = NULL;
3675  DB_TYPE single_node_type = DB_TYPE_NULL;
3676  int error;
3677 
3678  /* scan type is S_SHOWSTMT_SCAN */
3679  scan_id->type = S_SHOWSTMT_SCAN;
3680 
3681  /* initialize SCAN_ID structure */
3682  /* readonly_scan = true, fixed = true */
3683  scan_init_scan_id (scan_id, true, S_SELECT, true, grouped, single_fetch, join_dbval, val_list, vd);
3684 
3685  /* initialize SHOWSTMT_SCAN_ID structure */
3686  stsidp = &scan_id->s.stsid;
3687 
3688  for (regu_var_p = arg_list, i = 0; regu_var_p; regu_var_p = regu_var_p->next)
3689  {
3690  i++;
3691  }
3692 
3693  arg_cnt = i;
3694  if (arg_cnt > 0)
3695  {
3696  arg_values = (DB_VALUE **) db_private_alloc (thread_p, arg_cnt * sizeof (DB_VALUE *));
3697  if (arg_values == NULL)
3698  {
3699  error = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
3700  goto exit_on_error;
3701  }
3702 
3703  for (regu_var_p = arg_list, i = 0; regu_var_p; regu_var_p = regu_var_p->next, i++)
3704  {
3705  regu = &regu_var_p->value;
3706  assert (regu != NULL && regu->type == TYPE_POS_VALUE);
3707  error = fetch_peek_dbval (thread_p, regu, vd, NULL, NULL, NULL, &arg_values[i]);
3708  if (error != NO_ERROR)
3709  {
3710  goto exit_on_error;
3711  }
3712  }
3713  assert (i == arg_cnt);
3714  }
3715 
3716  /* prepare out_values */
3717  out_cnt = val_list->val_cnt;
3718  out_values = (DB_VALUE **) db_private_alloc (thread_p, out_cnt * sizeof (DB_VALUE *));
3719  if (out_values == NULL)
3720  {
3721  error = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
3722  goto exit_on_error;
3723  }
3724 
3725  for (valp = val_list->valp, i = 0; valp; valp = valp->next, i++)
3726  {
3727  out_values[i] = valp->val;
3728  }
3729  assert (i == out_cnt);
3730 
3731  stsidp->show_type = show_type;
3732  stsidp->arg_values = arg_values;
3733  stsidp->arg_cnt = arg_cnt;
3734  stsidp->out_values = out_values;
3735  stsidp->out_cnt = out_cnt;
3736  stsidp->cursor = 0;
3737  stsidp->ctx = NULL;
3738 
3739  /* scan predicates */
3740  scan_init_scan_pred (&stsidp->scan_pred, NULL, pr, ((pr) ? eval_fnc (thread_p, pr, &single_node_type) : NULL));
3741 
3742  return NO_ERROR;
3743 
3744 exit_on_error:
3745  if (arg_values != NULL)
3746  {
3747  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, arg_values);
3748  }
3749 
3750  if (out_values != NULL)
3751  {
3752  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, out_values);
3753  }
3754  return error;
3755 }

3870 /*
3871  * scan_start_scan () - Start the scan process on the given scan identifier.
3872  * return: NO_ERROR, or ER_code
3873  * scan_id(out): Scan identifier
3874  *
3875  * Note: If you feel the need
3876  */
3877 int
3878 scan_start_scan (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, SCAN_ID * scan_id)
3879 {
3880  int ret = NO_ERROR;
3881  int i;
3882  HEAP_SCAN_ID *hsidp = NULL;
3883  INDX_SCAN_ID *isidp = NULL;
3884  INDEX_NODE_SCAN_ID *insidp = NULL;
3885  LLIST_SCAN_ID *llsidp = NULL;
3886  SET_SCAN_ID *ssidp = NULL;
3887  REGU_VALUES_SCAN_ID *rvsidp = NULL;
3888  REGU_VALUE_LIST *regu_value_list = NULL;
3889  REGU_VARIABLE_LIST list_node = NULL;
3890  MVCC_SNAPSHOT *mvcc_snapshot = NULL;
3891 
3892  switch (scan_id->type)
3893  {
3894  case S_HEAP_SCAN:
3895  case S_HEAP_SCAN_RECORD_INFO:
3896  hsidp = &scan_id->s.hsid;
3897  UT_CAST_TO_NULL_HEAP_OID (&hsidp->hfid, &hsidp->curr_oid);
3898  if (!OID_IS_ROOTOID (&hsidp->cls_oid))
3899  {
3900  mvcc_snapshot = logtb_get_mvcc_snapshot (thread_p);
3901  if (mvcc_snapshot == NULL)
3902  {
3903  goto exit_on_error;
3904  }
3905  }
3906  if (scan_id->grouped)
3907  {
3908  ret = heap_scanrange_start (thread_p, &hsidp->scan_range, &hsidp->hfid, &hsidp->cls_oid, mvcc_snapshot);
3909  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
3910  {
3911  goto exit_on_error;
3912  }
3913  hsidp->scanrange_inited = true;
3914  }
3915  else
3916  {
3917  /* A new argument(is_indexscan = false) is appended */
3918  ret =
3919  heap_scancache_start (thread_p, &hsidp->scan_cache, &hsidp->hfid, &hsidp->cls_oid, scan_id->fixed, false,
3920  mvcc_snapshot);
3921  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
3922  {
3923  goto exit_on_error;
3924  }
3925  hsidp->scancache_inited = true;
3926  }
3927  if (hsidp->caches_inited != true)
3928  {
3929  hsidp->pred_attrs.attr_cache->num_values = -1;
3930  ret =
3931  heap_attrinfo_start (thread_p, &hsidp->cls_oid, hsidp->pred_attrs.num_attrs, hsidp->pred_attrs.attr_ids,
3932  hsidp->pred_attrs.attr_cache);
3933  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
3934  {
3935  goto exit_on_error;
3936  }
3937  hsidp->rest_attrs.attr_cache->num_values = -1;
3938  ret =
3939  heap_attrinfo_start (thread_p, &hsidp->cls_oid, hsidp->rest_attrs.num_attrs, hsidp->rest_attrs.attr_ids,
3940  hsidp->rest_attrs.attr_cache);
3941  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
3942  {
3943  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, hsidp->pred_attrs.attr_cache);
3944  goto exit_on_error;
3945  }
3946  if (hsidp->cache_recordinfo != NULL)
3947  {
3948  /* initialize cache_recordinfo values */
3949  for (i = 0; i < HEAP_RECORD_INFO_COUNT; i++)
3950  {
3951  db_make_null (hsidp->cache_recordinfo[i]);
3952  }
3953  }
3954  hsidp->caches_inited = true;
3955  }
3956  break;
3957 
3958  case S_HEAP_PAGE_SCAN:
3959  VPID_SET_NULL (&scan_id->s.hpsid.curr_vpid);
3960  break;
3961 
3962  case S_CLASS_ATTR_SCAN:
3963  hsidp = &scan_id->s.hsid;
3964  hsidp->pred_attrs.attr_cache->num_values = -1;
3965  if (hsidp->caches_inited != true)
3966  {
3967  ret =
3968  heap_attrinfo_start (thread_p, &hsidp->cls_oid, hsidp->pred_attrs.num_attrs, hsidp->pred_attrs.attr_ids,
3969  hsidp->pred_attrs.attr_cache);
3970  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
3971  {
3972  goto exit_on_error;
3973  }
3974  hsidp->rest_attrs.attr_cache->num_values = -1;
3975  ret =
3976  heap_attrinfo_start (thread_p, &hsidp->cls_oid, hsidp->rest_attrs.num_attrs, hsidp->rest_attrs.attr_ids,
3977  hsidp->rest_attrs.attr_cache);
3978  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
3979  {
3980  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, hsidp->pred_attrs.attr_cache);
3981  goto exit_on_error;
3982  }
3983  hsidp->caches_inited = true;
3984  }
3985  break;
3986 
3987  case S_INDX_SCAN:
3988  isidp = &scan_id->s.isid;
3989  if (!OID_IS_ROOTOID (&isidp->cls_oid))
3990  {
3991  mvcc_snapshot = logtb_get_mvcc_snapshot (thread_p);
3992  if (mvcc_snapshot == NULL)
3993  {
3994  goto exit_on_error;
3995  }
3996  }
3997 
3998  /* A new argument(is_indexscan = true) is appended */
3999  ret =
4000  heap_scancache_start (thread_p, &isidp->scan_cache, &isidp->hfid, &isidp->cls_oid, scan_id->fixed, true,
4001  mvcc_snapshot);
4002  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
4003  {
4004  goto exit_on_error;
4005  }
4006  isidp->scancache_inited = true;
4007  if (isidp->caches_inited != true)
4008  {
4009  if (isidp->range_pred.regu_list != NULL)
4010  {
4011  isidp->range_attrs.attr_cache->num_values = -1;
4012  ret =
4013  heap_attrinfo_start (thread_p, &isidp->cls_oid, isidp->range_attrs.num_attrs,
4014  isidp->range_attrs.attr_ids, isidp->range_attrs.attr_cache);
4015  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
4016  {
4017  goto exit_on_error;
4018  }
4019  }
4020  if (isidp->key_pred.regu_list != NULL)
4021  {
4022  isidp->key_attrs.attr_cache->num_values = -1;
4023  ret =
4024  heap_attrinfo_start (thread_p, &isidp->cls_oid, isidp->key_attrs.num_attrs, isidp->key_attrs.attr_ids,
4025  isidp->key_attrs.attr_cache);
4026  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
4027  {
4028  if (isidp->range_pred.regu_list != NULL)
4029  {
4030  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, isidp->range_attrs.attr_cache);
4031  }
4032  goto exit_on_error;
4033  }
4034  }
4035  isidp->pred_attrs.attr_cache->num_values = -1;
4036  ret =
4037  heap_attrinfo_start (thread_p, &isidp->cls_oid, isidp->pred_attrs.num_attrs, isidp->pred_attrs.attr_ids,
4038  isidp->pred_attrs.attr_cache);
4039  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
4040  {
4041  if (isidp->range_pred.regu_list != NULL)
4042  {
4043  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, isidp->range_attrs.attr_cache);
4044  }
4045  if (isidp->key_pred.regu_list != NULL)
4046  {
4047  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, isidp->key_attrs.attr_cache);
4048  }
4049  goto exit_on_error;
4050  }
4051  isidp->rest_attrs.attr_cache->num_values = -1;
4052  ret =
4053  heap_attrinfo_start (thread_p, &isidp->cls_oid, isidp->rest_attrs.num_attrs, isidp->rest_attrs.attr_ids,
4054  isidp->rest_attrs.attr_cache);
4055  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
4056  {
4057  if (isidp->range_pred.regu_list != NULL)
4058  {
4059  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, isidp->range_attrs.attr_cache);
4060  }
4061  if (isidp->key_pred.regu_list != NULL)
4062  {
4063  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, isidp->key_attrs.attr_cache);
4064  }
4065  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, isidp->pred_attrs.attr_cache);
4066  goto exit_on_error;
4067  }
4068  isidp->caches_inited = true;
4069  }
4070  isidp->oids_count = 0;
4071  isidp->curr_keyno = -1;
4072  isidp->curr_oidno = -1;
4073  isidp->one_range = false;
4074  break;
4075 
4076  case S_INDX_KEY_INFO_SCAN:
4077  isidp = &scan_id->s.isid;
4078 
4079  if (!isidp->caches_inited)
4080  {
4081  for (i = 0; i < BTREE_KEY_INFO_COUNT; i++)
4082  {
4083  db_make_null (isidp->key_info_values[i]);
4084  }
4085  }
4086  isidp->caches_inited = true;
4087  isidp->oids_count = 0;
4088  isidp->curr_keyno = -1;
4089  isidp->curr_oidno = -1;
4090  break;
4091 
4092  case S_INDX_NODE_INFO_SCAN:
4093  insidp = &scan_id->s.insid;
4094 
4095  if (!insidp->caches_inited)
4096  {
4097  for (i = 0; i < BTREE_NODE_INFO_COUNT; i++)
4098  {
4099  db_make_null (insidp->node_info_values[i]);
4100  }
4101  insidp->caches_inited = true;
4102  }
4103  BTREE_NODE_SCAN_INIT (&insidp->btns);
4104  break;
4105 
4106  case S_LIST_SCAN:
4107  llsidp = &scan_id->s.llsid;
4108  /* open list file scan */
4109  if (qfile_open_list_scan (llsidp->list_id, &llsidp->lsid) != NO_ERROR)
4110  {
4111  goto exit_on_error;
4112  }
4113  qfile_start_scan_fix (thread_p, &llsidp->lsid);
4114  break;
4115 
4116  case S_SHOWSTMT_SCAN:
4117  if (showstmt_start_scan (thread_p, scan_id) != NO_ERROR)
4118  {
4119  goto exit_on_error;
4120  }
4121  break;
4122 
4123  case S_VALUES_SCAN:
4124  rvsidp = &scan_id->s.rvsid;
4125  if (rvsidp->regu_list == NULL)
4126  {
4127  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_QPROC_INVALID_XASLNODE, 0);
4128  goto exit_on_error;
4129  }
4130 
4131  for (list_node = rvsidp->regu_list; list_node; list_node = list_node->next)
4132  {
4133  regu_value_list = list_node->value.value.reguval_list;
4134  assert (regu_value_list != NULL && regu_value_list->regu_list != NULL);
4135 
4136  regu_value_list->current_value = regu_value_list->regu_list;
4137  }
4138  break;
4139 
4140  case S_SET_SCAN:
4141  ssidp = &scan_id->s.ssid;
4142  db_make_null (&ssidp->set);
4143  break;
4144 
4145  case S_METHOD_SCAN:
4146  break;
4147 
4148  default:
4149  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_QPROC_INVALID_XASLNODE, 0);
4150  goto exit_on_error;
4151  } /* switch (scan_id->type) */
4152 
4153  /* set scan status as started */
4154  scan_id->position = S_BEFORE;
4155  scan_id->direction = S_FORWARD;
4156  scan_id->status = S_STARTED;
4157  scan_id->qualified_block = false;
4158  scan_id->single_fetched = false;
4159  scan_id->null_fetched = false;
4160 
4161  return ret;
4162 
4163 exit_on_error:
4164 
4165  return (ret == NO_ERROR && (ret = er_errid ()) == NO_ERROR) ? ER_FAILED : ret;
4166 }
4167 
4168 /*
4169  * scan_reset_scan_block () - Move the scan back to the beginning point inside the current scan block.
4170  * return: S_SUCCESS, S_END, S_ERROR
4171  * s_id(in/out): Scan identifier
4172  *
4173  * Note: If you feel the need
4174  */
4175 SCAN_CODE
4176 scan_reset_scan_block (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, SCAN_ID * s_id)
4177 {
4178  SCAN_CODE status = S_SUCCESS;
4179 
4180  s_id->single_fetched = false;
4181  s_id->null_fetched = false;
4182 
4183  switch (s_id->type)
4184  {
4185  case S_HEAP_SCAN:
4186  if (s_id->grouped)
4187  {
4188  OID_SET_NULL (&s_id->s.hsid.curr_oid);
4189  }
4190  else
4191  {
4192  s_id->position = (s_id->direction == S_FORWARD) ? S_BEFORE : S_AFTER;
4193  OID_SET_NULL (&s_id->s.hsid.curr_oid);
4194  }
4195  break;
4196 
4197  case S_INDX_SCAN:
4198  if (s_id->grouped)
4199  {
4200  if (s_id->direction == S_FORWARD && s_id->s.isid.iscan_oid_order == true)
4201  {
4202  s_id->s.isid.curr_oidno = s_id->s.isid.oids_count;
4203  s_id->direction = S_BACKWARD;
4204  }
4205  else
4206  {
4207  s_id->s.isid.curr_oidno = -1;
4208  s_id->direction = S_FORWARD;
4209  }
4210 
4211  /* reinitialize index skip scan structure */
4212  if (scan_init_iss (&s_id->s.isid) != NO_ERROR)
4213  {
4214  status = S_ERROR;
4215  break;
4216  }
4217  }
4218  else
4219  {
4220  INDX_COV *indx_cov_p;
4221 
4222  s_id->s.isid.curr_oidno = -1;
4223  s_id->s.isid.curr_keyno = -1;
4224  s_id->position = S_BEFORE;
4225  BTREE_RESET_SCAN (&s_id->s.isid.bt_scan);
4226 
4227  /* reset key limits */
4228  if (s_id->s.isid.indx_info)
4229  {
4230  if (scan_init_index_key_limit (thread_p, &s_id->s.isid, &s_id->s.isid.indx_info->key_info, s_id->vd) !=
4231  NO_ERROR)
4232  {
4233  status = S_ERROR;
4234  break;
4235  }
4236  }
4237 
4238  /* reinitialize index skip scan structure */
4239  if (scan_init_iss (&s_id->s.isid) != NO_ERROR)
4240  {
4241  status = S_ERROR;
4242  break;
4243  }
4244 
4245  /* reset index covering */
4246  indx_cov_p = &(s_id->s.isid.indx_cov);
4247  if (indx_cov_p->lsid != NULL)
4248  {
4249  qfile_close_scan (thread_p, indx_cov_p->lsid);
4250  }
4251 
4252  if (indx_cov_p->list_id != NULL)
4253  {
4254  qfile_destroy_list (thread_p, indx_cov_p->list_id);
4255  QFILE_FREE_AND_INIT_LIST_ID (indx_cov_p->list_id);
4256 
4257  indx_cov_p->list_id = qfile_open_list (thread_p, indx_cov_p->type_list, NULL, indx_cov_p->query_id, 0);
4258  if (indx_cov_p->list_id == NULL)
4259  {
4260  status = S_ERROR;
4261  }
4262  }
4263  }
4264  break;
4265 
4266  case S_LIST_SCAN:
4267  /* may have scanned some already so clean up */
4268  qfile_end_scan_fix (thread_p, &s_id->s.llsid.lsid);
4269  qfile_close_scan (thread_p, &s_id->s.llsid.lsid);
4270 
4271  /* open list file scan for this outer row */
4272  if (qfile_open_list_scan (s_id->s.llsid.list_id, &s_id->s.llsid.lsid) != NO_ERROR)
4273  {
4274  status = S_ERROR;
4275  break;
4276  }
4277  qfile_start_scan_fix (thread_p, &s_id->s.llsid.lsid);
4278  s_id->position = S_BEFORE;
4279  s_id->s.llsid.lsid.position = S_BEFORE;
4280  break;
4281 
4282  case S_SHOWSTMT_SCAN:
4283  s_id->s.stsid.cursor = 0;
4284  s_id->position = S_BEFORE;
4285  break;
4286 
4287  case S_CLASS_ATTR_SCAN:
4288  case S_SET_SCAN:
4289  s_id->position = S_BEFORE;
4290  break;
4291 
4292  default:
4293  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_QPROC_INVALID_XASLNODE, 0);
4294  status = S_ERROR;
4295  break;
4296  } /* switch (s_id->type) */
4297 
4298 
4299  return status;
4300 }
4301 
4302 /*
4303  * scan_next_scan_block () - Move the scan to the next scan block.
4304  * If there are no more scan blocks left, S_END is returned.
4305  * return: S_SUCCESS, S_END, S_ERROR
4306  * s_id(in/out): Scan identifier
4307  *
4308  * Note: If you feel the need
4309  */
4310 SCAN_CODE
4311 scan_next_scan_block (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, SCAN_ID * s_id)
4312 {
4313  SCAN_CODE sp_scan;
4314 
4315  s_id->single_fetched = false;
4316  s_id->null_fetched = false;
4317  s_id->qualified_block = false;
4318 
4319  switch (s_id->type)
4320  {
4321  case S_HEAP_SCAN:
4322  case S_HEAP_SCAN_RECORD_INFO:
4323  case S_HEAP_PAGE_SCAN:
4324  if (s_id->grouped)
4325  { /* grouped, fixed scan */
4326 
4327  if (s_id->direction == S_FORWARD)
4328  {
4329  sp_scan = heap_scanrange_to_following (thread_p, &s_id->s.hsid.scan_range, NULL);
4330  }
4331  else
4332  {
4333  sp_scan = heap_scanrange_to_prior (thread_p, &s_id->s.hsid.scan_range, NULL);
4334  }
4335 
4336  return ((sp_scan == S_SUCCESS) ? S_SUCCESS : (sp_scan == S_END) ? S_END : S_ERROR);
4337  }
4338  else
4339  {
4340  return ((s_id->direction ==
4341  S_FORWARD) ? ((s_id->position == S_BEFORE) ? S_SUCCESS : S_END) : ((s_id->position ==
4342  S_AFTER) ? S_SUCCESS : S_END));
4343  }
4344 
4345  case S_INDX_SCAN:
4346  if (s_id->grouped)
4347  {
4348  if ((s_id->direction == S_FORWARD && s_id->position == S_BEFORE)
4349  || (!BTREE_END_OF_SCAN (&s_id->s.isid.bt_scan) || s_id->s.isid.indx_info->range_type == R_KEYLIST
4350  || s_id->s.isid.indx_info->range_type == R_RANGELIST))
4351  {
4352  if (!(s_id->position == S_BEFORE && s_id->s.isid.one_range == true))
4353  {
4354  /* get the next set of object identifiers specified in the range */
4355  if (scan_get_index_oidset (thread_p, s_id, NULL, NULL) != NO_ERROR)
4356  {
4357  return S_ERROR;
4358  }
4359 
4360  if (s_id->s.isid.oids_count == 0)
4361  { /* range is empty */
4362  s_id->position = S_AFTER;
4363  return S_END;
4364  }
4365 
4366  if (s_id->position == S_BEFORE && BTREE_END_OF_SCAN (&s_id->s.isid.bt_scan)
4367  && s_id->s.isid.indx_info->range_type != R_KEYLIST
4368  && s_id->s.isid.indx_info->range_type != R_RANGELIST)
4369  {
4370  s_id->s.isid.one_range = true;
4371  }
4372  }
4373 
4374  if (s_id->s.isid.iscan_oid_order == true)
4375  {
4376  s_id->position = S_ON;
4377  s_id->direction = S_BACKWARD;
4378  s_id->s.isid.curr_oidno = s_id->s.isid.oids_count;
4379  }
4380 
4381  return S_SUCCESS;
4382  }
4383  else
4384  {
4385  s_id->position = S_AFTER;
4386  return S_END;
4387  }
4388 
4389  }
4390  else
4391  {
4392  return ((s_id->position == S_BEFORE) ? S_SUCCESS : S_END);
4393  }
4394 
4395  case S_INDX_KEY_INFO_SCAN:
4396  case S_INDX_NODE_INFO_SCAN:
4397  if (s_id->grouped)
4398  {
4399  assert (0);
4400  return S_ERROR;
4401  }
4402  return ((s_id->position == S_BEFORE) ? S_SUCCESS : S_END);
4403 
4404  case S_CLASS_ATTR_SCAN:
4405  case S_LIST_SCAN:
4406  case S_SHOWSTMT_SCAN:
4407  case S_SET_SCAN:
4408  case S_METHOD_SCAN:
4409  case S_VALUES_SCAN:
4410  return (s_id->position == S_BEFORE) ? S_SUCCESS : S_END;
4411 
4412  default:
4413  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_QPROC_INVALID_XASLNODE, 0);
4414  return S_ERROR;
4415  }
4416 }
4417 
4418 /*
4419  * scan_end_scan () - End the scan process on the given scan identifier.
4420  * return:
4421  * scan_id(in/out): Scan identifier
4422  *
4423  * Note: If you feel the need
4424  */
4425 void
4426 scan_end_scan (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, SCAN_ID * scan_id)
4427 {
4428  HEAP_SCAN_ID *hsidp;
4429  INDX_SCAN_ID *isidp;
4430  LLIST_SCAN_ID *llsidp;
4431  REGU_VALUES_SCAN_ID *rvsidp;
4432  SET_SCAN_ID *ssidp;
4433  KEY_VAL_RANGE *key_vals;
4434  int i;
4435 
4436  if (scan_id == NULL)
4437  {
4438  return;
4439  }
4440 
4441  if ((scan_id->status == S_ENDED) || (scan_id->status == S_CLOSED))
4442  {
4443  return;
4444  }
4445 
4446  switch (scan_id->type)
4447  {
4448  case S_HEAP_SCAN:
4449  case S_HEAP_SCAN_RECORD_INFO:
4450  hsidp = &scan_id->s.hsid;
4451 
4452  /* do not free attr_cache here. xs_clear_access_spec_list() will free attr_caches. */
4453 
4454  if (scan_id->grouped)
4455  {
4456  if (hsidp->scanrange_inited)
4457  {
4458  heap_scanrange_end (thread_p, &hsidp->scan_range);
4459  }
4460  }
4461  else
4462  {
4463  if (hsidp->scancache_inited)
4464  {
4465  (void) heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &hsidp->scan_cache);
4466  }
4467  }
4468 
4469  /* switch scan direction for further iterations */
4470  if (scan_id->direction == S_FORWARD)
4471  {
4472  scan_id->direction = S_BACKWARD;
4473  }
4474  else
4475  {
4476  scan_id->direction = S_FORWARD;
4477  }
4478  break;
4479 
4480  case S_CLASS_ATTR_SCAN:
4481  /* do not free attr_cache here. xs_clear_access_spec_list() will free attr_caches. */
4482  break;
4483 
4484  case S_INDX_SCAN:
4485  isidp = &scan_id->s.isid;
4486 
4487  /* do not free attr_cache here. xs_clear_access_spec_list() will free attr_caches. */
4488 
4489  if (isidp->scancache_inited)
4490  {
4491  (void) heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &isidp->scan_cache);
4492  }
4493  if (isidp->curr_keyno >= 0 && isidp->curr_keyno < isidp->key_cnt)
4494  {
4495  key_vals = isidp->key_vals;
4496  for (i = 0; i < isidp->key_cnt; i++)
4497  {
4498  pr_clear_value (&key_vals[i].key1);
4499  pr_clear_value (&key_vals[i].key2);
4500  }
4501  }
4502  /* clear all the used keys */
4503  btree_scan_clear_key (&(isidp->bt_scan));
4504  /* clear last_key */
4505  (void) scan_init_iss (isidp);
4506  break;
4507 
4508  case S_LIST_SCAN:
4509  llsidp = &scan_id->s.llsid;
4510  qfile_end_scan_fix (thread_p, &llsidp->lsid);
4511  qfile_close_scan (thread_p, &llsidp->lsid);
4512  break;
4513 
4514  case S_SHOWSTMT_SCAN:
4515  showstmt_end_scan (thread_p, scan_id);
4516  break;
4517 
4518  case S_VALUES_SCAN:
4519  rvsidp = &scan_id->s.rvsid;
4520  break;
4521 
4522  case S_SET_SCAN:
4523  ssidp = &scan_id->s.ssid;
4524  pr_clear_value (&ssidp->set);
4525  break;
4526 
4527  case S_METHOD_SCAN:
4528  break;
4529 
4530  default:
4531  break;
4532  }
4533 
4534  scan_id->status = S_ENDED;
4535 }
4536 
4537 /*
4538  * scan_close_scan () - The scan identifier is closed and allocated areas and page buffers are freed.
4539  * return:
4540  * scan_id(in/out): Scan identifier
4541  *
4542  * Note: If you feel the need
4543  */
4544 void
4545 scan_close_scan (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, SCAN_ID * scan_id)
4546 {
4547  INDX_SCAN_ID *isidp;
4548  SHOWSTMT_SCAN_ID *stsidp;
4549 
4550  if (scan_id == NULL || scan_id->status == S_CLOSED)
4551  {
4552  return;
4553  }
4554 
4555  switch (scan_id->type)
4556  {
4557  case S_HEAP_SCAN:
4558  case S_HEAP_SCAN_RECORD_INFO:
4559  case S_HEAP_PAGE_SCAN:
4560  case S_CLASS_ATTR_SCAN:
4561  case S_VALUES_SCAN:
4562  break;
4563 
4564  case S_INDX_SCAN:
4565  isidp = &scan_id->s.isid;
4566  if (isidp->key_vals)
4567  {
4568  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->key_vals);
4569  }
4570 
4571  /* free allocated memory for the scan */
4572  if (isidp->bt_attr_ids)
4573  {
4574  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->bt_attr_ids);
4575  }
4576  if (isidp->bt_attrs_prefix_length)
4577  {
4578  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->bt_attrs_prefix_length);
4579  }
4580  if (isidp->vstr_ids)
4581  {
4582  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->vstr_ids);
4583  }
4584  if (isidp->oid_list != NULL)
4585  {
4586  scan_free_iscan_oid_buf_list (isidp->oid_list);
4587  isidp->oid_list = NULL;
4588  }
4589 
4590  /* free index key copy_buf */
4591  if (isidp->copy_buf)
4592  {
4593  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->copy_buf);
4594  }
4595 
4596  /* free index covering */
4597  if (isidp->indx_cov.lsid != NULL)
4598  {
4599  qfile_close_scan (thread_p, isidp->indx_cov.lsid);
4600  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->indx_cov.lsid);
4601  }
4602  if (isidp->indx_cov.list_id != NULL)
4603  {
4604  qfile_close_list (thread_p, isidp->indx_cov.list_id);
4605  qfile_destroy_list (thread_p, isidp->indx_cov.list_id);
4606  QFILE_FREE_AND_INIT_LIST_ID (isidp->indx_cov.list_id);
4607  }
4608  if (isidp->indx_cov.type_list != NULL)
4609  {
4610  if (isidp->indx_cov.type_list->domp != NULL)
4611  {
4612  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->indx_cov.type_list->domp);
4613  }
4614  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->indx_cov.type_list);
4615  }
4616  if (isidp->indx_cov.tplrec != NULL)
4617  {
4618  if (isidp->indx_cov.tplrec->tpl != NULL)
4619  {
4620  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->indx_cov.tplrec->tpl);
4621  }
4622  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->indx_cov.tplrec);
4623  }
4624 
4625  /* free multiple range optimization struct */
4626  if (isidp->multi_range_opt.top_n_items != NULL)
4627  {
4628  int i;
4629 
4630  for (i = 0; i < isidp->multi_range_opt.size; i++)
4631  {
4632  if (isidp->multi_range_opt.top_n_items[i] != NULL)
4633  {
4634  pr_clear_value (&(isidp->multi_range_opt.top_n_items[i]->index_value));
4635  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->multi_range_opt.top_n_items[i]);
4636  }
4637  }
4638  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->multi_range_opt.top_n_items);
4639  isidp->multi_range_opt.top_n_items = NULL;
4640  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->multi_range_opt.tplrec.tpl);
4641  isidp->multi_range_opt.tplrec.tpl = 0;
4642  }
4643  /* free buffer */
4644  if (isidp->multi_range_opt.buffer != NULL)
4645  {
4646  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->multi_range_opt.buffer);
4647  }
4648  if (isidp->multi_range_opt.sort_att_idx != NULL)
4649  {
4650  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->multi_range_opt.sort_att_idx);
4651  }
4652  if (isidp->multi_range_opt.is_desc_order != NULL)
4653  {
4654  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->multi_range_opt.is_desc_order);
4655  }
4656  if (isidp->multi_range_opt.sort_col_dom != NULL)
4657  {
4658  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, isidp->multi_range_opt.sort_col_dom);
4659  }
4660  memset ((void *) (&(isidp->multi_range_opt)), 0, sizeof (MULTI_RANGE_OPT));
4661  break;
4662 
4663  case S_LIST_SCAN:
4664  break;
4665 
4666  case S_SHOWSTMT_SCAN:
4667  stsidp = &scan_id->s.stsid;
4668  if (stsidp->arg_values != NULL)
4669  {
4670  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, stsidp->arg_values);
4671  }
4672  if (stsidp->out_values != NULL)
4673  {
4674  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, stsidp->out_values);
4675  }
4676  break;
4677 
4678  case S_SET_SCAN:
4679  break;
4680 
4681  case S_METHOD_SCAN:
4682  method_close_scan (thread_p, &scan_id->s.vaid.scan_buf);
4683  break;
4684 
4685  default:
4686  /* S_VALUES_SCAN */
4687  break;
4688  }
4689 
4690  scan_id->status = S_CLOSED;
4691 }
4692 
4693 /*
4694  * call_get_next_index_oidset () - Wrapper for scan_get_next_oidset, accounts
4695  * for scan variations, such as the "index
4696  * skip scan" optimization.
4697  * return: SCAN_CODE (S_SUCCESS, S_END, S_ERROR)
4698  * thread_p (in):
4699  * scan_id (in/out):
4700  * isidp (in/out):
4701  * should_go_to_next_value (in): see Notes
4702  *
4703  * Note:
4704  * This function tries to obtain the next set of OIDs for the scan to consume.
4705  * The real heavy-lifting function is get_next_index_oidset(), which we call,
4706  * this one is a wrapper.
4707  * If the "Index Skip Scan" optimization is used, we cycle through successive
4708  * values of the first index column until we find one that lets
4709  * get_index_oidset() return with some results.
4710  * We also handle the case where we are called just because a new crop of OIDs
4711  * is needed.
4712  *
4713  * The boolean should_go_to_next_value controls whether we skip to the next
4714  * value for the first index column, or we still have data to read for the
4715  * current value (i.e. because the buffer was full. It is controlled by
4716  * the caller by evaluating BTREE_END_OF_SCAN. If this is true, there are no
4717  * more OIDS for the current value of the first index column and we should
4718  * "skip" to the next one.
4719  */
4720 static SCAN_CODE
4721 call_get_next_index_oidset (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, SCAN_ID * scan_id, INDX_SCAN_ID * isidp,
4722  bool should_go_to_next_value)
4723 {
4724  DB_BIGINT *p_kl_upper = NULL;
4725  DB_BIGINT *p_kl_lower = NULL;
4726  int oids_cnt;
4727 
4728 /*
4729  * WHILE (true)
4730  * {
4731  * if (iss && should-skip-to-next-iss-value)
4732  * obtain-next-iss-value() or return if it does not find anything;
4733  *
4734  * get-index-oidset();
4735  *
4736  * if (oids count == 0) // did not find anything
4737  * {
4738  * should-skip-to-next-iss-value = true;
4739  * if (iss)
4740  * continue; // to allow the while () to fetch the next value for the
4741  * // first column in the index
4742  * return S_END; // BTRS returned nothing and we are not in ISS mode. Leave.
4743  * }
4744  *
4745  * break; //at least one OID found. get out of the loop.
4746  *}
4747  */
4748 
4749  while (1)
4750  {
4751  if (isidp->iss.use && should_go_to_next_value)
4752  {
4753  SCAN_CODE code = scan_get_next_iss_value (thread_p, scan_id, isidp);
4754  if (code != S_SUCCESS)
4755  {
4756  /* anything wrong? or even end of scan? just leave */
4757  return code;
4758  }
4759  }
4760 
4761  p_kl_lower = isidp->key_limit_lower == -1 ? NULL : &isidp->key_limit_lower;
4762  p_kl_upper = isidp->key_limit_upper == -1 ? NULL : &isidp->key_limit_upper;
4763 
4764  if (scan_get_index_oidset (thread_p, scan_id, p_kl_upper, p_kl_lower) != NO_ERROR)
4765  {
4766  return S_ERROR;
4767  }
4768 
4769  oids_cnt = isidp->multi_range_opt.use ? isidp->multi_range_opt.cnt : isidp->oids_count;
4770 
4771  if (oids_cnt == 0)
4772  {
4773  if (isidp->iss.use)
4774  {
4775  should_go_to_next_value = true;
4776  continue;
4777  }
4778  return S_END; /* no ISS, no oids, this is the end of scan. */
4779  }
4780 
4781  /* We have at least one OID. Break the loop, allow normal processing. */
4782  break;
4783  }
4784 
4785  return S_SUCCESS;
4786 }
4787 
4788 /*
4789  * scan_next_scan_local () - The scan is moved to the next scan item.
4790  * return: SCAN_CODE (S_SUCCESS, S_END, S_ERROR)
4791  * scan_id(in/out): Scan identifier
4792  *
4793  * Note: If there are no more scan items, S_END is returned. If an error occurs, S_ERROR is returned.
4794  */
4795 static SCAN_CODE
4796 scan_next_scan_local (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, SCAN_ID * scan_id)
4797 {
4798  SCAN_CODE status;
4799  bool on_trace;
4800  UINT64 old_fetches = 0, old_ioreads = 0;
4801  TSC_TICKS start_tick, end_tick;
4802  TSCTIMEVAL tv_diff;
4803 
4804  on_trace = thread_is_on_trace (thread_p);
4805  if (on_trace)
4806  {
4807  tsc_getticks (&start_tick);
4808 
4809  old_fetches = perfmon_get_from_statistic (thread_p, PSTAT_PB_NUM_FETCHES);
4810  old_ioreads = perfmon_get_from_statistic (thread_p, PSTAT_PB_NUM_IOREADS);
4811  }
4812 
4813  switch (scan_id->type)
4814  {
4815  case S_HEAP_SCAN:
4816  case S_HEAP_SCAN_RECORD_INFO:
4817  status = scan_next_heap_scan (thread_p, scan_id);
4818  break;
4819 
4820  case S_HEAP_PAGE_SCAN:
4821  status = scan_next_heap_page_scan (thread_p, scan_id);
4822  break;
4823 
4824  case S_CLASS_ATTR_SCAN:
4825  status = scan_next_class_attr_scan (thread_p, scan_id);
4826  break;
4827 
4828  case S_INDX_SCAN:
4829  status = scan_next_index_scan (thread_p, scan_id);
4830  break;
4831 
4832  case S_INDX_KEY_INFO_SCAN:
4833  status = scan_next_index_key_info_scan (thread_p, scan_id);
4834  break;
4835 
4836  case S_INDX_NODE_INFO_SCAN:
4837  status = scan_next_index_node_info_scan (thread_p, scan_id);
4838  break;
4839 
4840  case S_LIST_SCAN:
4841  status = scan_next_list_scan (thread_p, scan_id);
4842  break;
4843 
4844  case S_SHOWSTMT_SCAN:
4845  status = scan_next_showstmt_scan (thread_p, scan_id);
4846  break;
4847 
4848  case S_VALUES_SCAN:
4849  status = scan_next_value_scan (thread_p, scan_id);
4850  break;
4851 
4852  case S_SET_SCAN:
4853  status = scan_next_set_scan (thread_p, scan_id);
4854  break;
4855 
4856  case S_METHOD_SCAN:
4857  status = scan_next_method_scan (thread_p, scan_id);
4858  break;
4859 
4860  default:
4861  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_QPROC_INVALID_XASLNODE, 0);
4862  return S_ERROR;
4863  }
4864 
4865  if (on_trace)
4866  {
4867  tsc_getticks (&end_tick);
4868  tsc_elapsed_time_usec (&tv_diff, end_tick, start_tick);
4869  TSC_ADD_TIMEVAL (scan_id->scan_stats.elapsed_scan, tv_diff);
4870 
4871  scan_id->scan_stats.num_fetches += perfmon_get_from_statistic (thread_p, PSTAT_PB_NUM_FETCHES) - old_fetches;
4872  scan_id->scan_stats.num_ioreads += perfmon_get_from_statistic (thread_p, PSTAT_PB_NUM_IOREADS) - old_ioreads;
4873  }
4874 
4875  return status;
4876 }
4877 
4878 typedef enum
4879 {
4880  OBJ_GET_WITHOUT_LOCK = 0,
4881  OBJ_REPEAT_GET_WITH_LOCK = 1,
4882  OBJ_GET_WITH_LOCK_COMPLETE = 2
4883 } OBJECT_GET_STATUS;
4884 /*
4885  * scan_next_heap_scan () - The scan is moved to the next heap scan item.
4886  * return: SCAN_CODE (S_SUCCESS, S_END, S_ERROR)
4887  * scan_id(in/out): Scan identifier
4888  *
4889  * Note: If there are no more scan items, S_END is returned. If an error occurs, S_ERROR is returned.
4890  */
4891 static SCAN_CODE
4892 scan_next_heap_scan (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, SCAN_ID * scan_id)
4893 {
4894  HEAP_SCAN_ID *hsidp;
4895  FILTER_INFO data_filter;
4896  RECDES recdes;
4897  SCAN_CODE sp_scan;
4898  DB_LOGICAL ev_res;
4899  OID current_oid, *p_current_oid = NULL;
4900  MVCC_SCAN_REEV_DATA mvcc_sel_reev_data;
4901  MVCC_REEV_DATA mvcc_reev_data;
4902  FILTER_INFO *p_range_filter = NULL, *p_key_filter = NULL;
4903  OID retry_oid;
4904  LOG_LSA ref_lsa;
4905  bool is_peeking;
4906  OBJECT_GET_STATUS object_get_status;
4907  REGU_VARIABLE_LIST p;
4908 
4909  hsidp = &scan_id->s.hsid;
4910  if (scan_id->mvcc_select_lock_needed)
4911  {
4912  p_current_oid = &current_oid;
4913  }
4914  else
4915  {
4916  p_current_oid = &hsidp->curr_oid;
4917  }
4918 
4919  /* set data filter information */
4920  scan_init_filter_info (&data_filter, &hsidp->scan_pred, &hsidp->pred_attrs, scan_id->val_list, scan_id->vd,
4921  &hsidp->cls_oid, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL);
4922 
4923  is_peeking = scan_id->fixed;
4924  if (scan_id->grouped)
4925  {
4926  is_peeking = PEEK;
4927  }
4928 
4929  if (data_filter.val_list)
4930  {
4931  for (p = data_filter.scan_pred->regu_list; p; p = p->next)
4932  {
4933  if (DB_NEED_CLEAR (p->value.vfetch_to))
4934  {
4935  pr_clear_value (p->value.vfetch_to);
4936  }
4937  }
4938  }
4939 
4940  while (1)
4941  {
4942  COPY_OID (&retry_oid, &hsidp->curr_oid);
4943  object_get_status = OBJ_GET_WITHOUT_LOCK;
4944 
4945  restart_scan_oid:
4946 
4947  /* get next object */
4948  if (scan_id->grouped)
4949  {
4950  /* grouped, fixed scan */
4951  sp_scan = heap_scanrange_next (thread_p, &hsidp->curr_oid, &recdes, &hsidp->scan_range, is_peeking);
4952  }
4953  else
4954  {
4955  recdes.data = NULL;
4956  if (scan_id->direction == S_FORWARD)
4957  {
4958  /* move forward */
4959  if (scan_id->type == S_HEAP_SCAN)
4960  {
4961  sp_scan =
4962  heap_next (thread_p, &hsidp->hfid, &hsidp->cls_oid, &hsidp->curr_oid, &recdes, &hsidp->scan_cache,
4963  is_peeking);
4964  }
4965  else
4966  {
4967  assert (scan_id->type == S_HEAP_SCAN_RECORD_INFO);
4968  sp_scan =
4969  heap_next_record_info (thread_p, &hsidp->hfid, &hsidp->cls_oid, &hsidp->curr_oid, &recdes,
4970  &hsidp->scan_cache, is_peeking, hsidp->cache_recordinfo);
4971  }
4972  }
4973  else
4974  {
4975  /* move backward */
4976  if (scan_id->type == S_HEAP_SCAN)
4977  {
4978  sp_scan =
4979  heap_prev (thread_p, &hsidp->hfid, &hsidp->cls_oid, &hsidp->curr_oid, &recdes, &hsidp->scan_cache,
4980  is_peeking);
4981  }
4982  else
4983  {
4984  assert (scan_id->type == S_HEAP_SCAN_RECORD_INFO);
4985  sp_scan =
4986  heap_prev_record_info (thread_p, &hsidp->hfid, &hsidp->cls_oid, &hsidp->curr_oid, &recdes,
4987  &hsidp->scan_cache, is_peeking, hsidp->cache_recordinfo);
4988  }
4989  }
4990  }
4991 
4992  if (sp_scan != S_SUCCESS)
4993  {
4994  /* scan error or end of scan */
4995  return (sp_scan == S_END) ? S_END : S_ERROR;
4996  }
4997 
4998  if (hsidp->scan_cache.page_watcher.pgptr != NULL)
4999  {
5000  LSA_COPY (&ref_lsa, pgbuf_get_lsa (hsidp->scan_cache.page_watcher.pgptr));
5001  }
5002 
5003  /* evaluate the predicates to see if the object qualifies */
5004  scan_id->scan_stats.read_rows++;
5005 
5006  ev_res = eval_data_filter (thread_p, p_current_oid, &recdes, &hsidp->scan_cache, &data_filter);
5007  if (ev_res == V_ERROR)
5008  {
5009  return S_ERROR;
5010  }
5011 
5012  if (is_peeking == PEEK && hsidp->scan_cache.page_watcher.pgptr != NULL
5013  && pgbuf_page_has_changed (hsidp->scan_cache.page_watcher.pgptr, &ref_lsa))
5014  {
5015  is_peeking = COPY;
5016  COPY_OID (&hsidp->curr_oid, &retry_oid);
5017  goto restart_scan_oid;
5018  }
5019 
5020  if (scan_id->qualification == QPROC_QUALIFIED)
5021  {
5022  if (ev_res != V_TRUE) /* V_FALSE || V_UNKNOWN */
5023  {
5024  continue; /* not qualified, continue to the next tuple */
5025  }
5026  }
5027  else if (scan_id->qualification == QPROC_NOT_QUALIFIED)
5028  {
5029  if (ev_res != V_FALSE) /* V_TRUE || V_UNKNOWN */
5030  {
5031  continue; /* qualified, continue to the next tuple */
5032  }
5033  }
5034  else if (scan_id->qualification == QPROC_QUALIFIED_OR_NOT)
5035  {
5036  if (ev_res == V_TRUE)
5037  {
5038  scan_id->qualification = QPROC_QUALIFIED;
5039  }
5040  else if (ev_res == V_FALSE)
5041  {
5042  scan_id->qualification = QPROC_NOT_QUALIFIED;
5043  }
5044  else /* V_UNKNOWN */
5045  {
5046  /* nop */
5047  ;
5048  }
5049  }
5050  else
5051  { /* invalid value; the same as QPROC_QUALIFIED */
5052  if (ev_res != V_TRUE) /* V_FALSE || V_UNKNOWN */
5053  {
5054  continue; /* not qualified, continue to the next tuple */
5055  }
5056  }
5057 
5058  /* Data filter passed. If object should be locked and is not locked yet, lock it. */
5059 
5060  if (scan_id->mvcc_select_lock_needed)
5061  {
5062  /* data filter already initialized, don't have key or range init scan reevaluation structure */
5063  INIT_SCAN_REEV_DATA (&mvcc_sel_reev_data, p_range_filter, p_key_filter, &data_filter,
5064  &scan_id->qualification);
5065  SET_MVCC_SELECT_REEV_DATA (&mvcc_reev_data, &mvcc_sel_reev_data, V_TRUE);
5066  COPY_OID (&current_oid, &hsidp->curr_oid);
5067  if (scan_id->fixed)
5068  {
5069  /* Reset recdes.data */
5070  recdes.data = NULL;
5071  }
5072 
5073  /* get with lock and reevaluate if the visible version wasn't the latest version */
5074  sp_scan =
5075  locator_lock_and_get_object_with_evaluation (thread_p, &current_oid, NULL, &recdes, &hsidp->scan_cache,
5076  is_peeking, NULL_CHN, &mvcc_reev_data, LOG_WARNING_IF_DELETED);
5077  if (sp_scan == S_SUCCESS && mvcc_reev_data.filter_result == V_FALSE)
5078  {
5079  continue;
5080  }
5081  else if (er_errid () == ER_HEAP_UNKNOWN_OBJECT || sp_scan == S_DOESNT_EXIST)
5082  {
5083  er_clear ();
5084  continue;
5085  }
5086  else if (sp_scan != S_SUCCESS)
5087  {
5088  return S_ERROR;
5089  }
5090  }
5091 
5092  if (mvcc_is_mvcc_disabled_class (&hsidp->cls_oid))
5093  {
5094  LOCK lock = NULL_LOCK;
5095  int tran_index = LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p);
5096  TRAN_ISOLATION tran_isolation = logtb_find_isolation (tran_index);
5097 
5098  if (scan_id->scan_op_type == S_DELETE || scan_id->scan_op_type == S_UPDATE)
5099  {
5100  lock = X_LOCK;
5101  }
5102  else if (oid_is_serial (&hsidp->cls_oid))
5103  {
5104  /* S_SELECT is currently handled only for serial, but may be extended to the other non-MVCC classes
5105  * if needed */
5106  lock = S_LOCK;
5107  }
5108 
5109  if (lock != NULL_LOCK && hsidp->scan_cache.page_watcher.pgptr != NULL)
5110  {
5111  if (tran_isolation == TRAN_READ_COMMITTED && lock == S_LOCK)
5112  {
5113  if (lock_hold_object_instant (thread_p, &hsidp->curr_oid, &hsidp->cls_oid, lock) == LK_GRANTED)
5114  {
5115  lock = NULL_LOCK;
5116  /* object_need_rescan needs to be kept false (page is still fixed, no other transaction could
5117  * have change it) */
5118  }
5119  }
5120  else
5121  {
5122  if (lock_object (thread_p, &hsidp->curr_oid, &hsidp->cls_oid, lock, LK_COND_LOCK) == LK_GRANTED)
5123  {
5124  /* successfully locked */
5125  lock = NULL_LOCK;
5126  /* object_need_rescan needs to be kept false (page is still fixed, no other transaction could
5127  * have change it) */
5128  }
5129  }
5130  }
5131 
5132  if (lock != NULL_LOCK)
5133  {
5134  VPID curr_vpid;
5135 
5136  VPID_SET_NULL (&curr_vpid);
5137 
5138  if (hsidp->scan_cache.page_watcher.pgptr != NULL)
5139  {
5140  pgbuf_get_vpid (hsidp->scan_cache.page_watcher.pgptr, &curr_vpid);
5141  pgbuf_ordered_unfix (thread_p, &hsidp->scan_cache.page_watcher);
5142  }
5143 #if defined (SERVER_MODE)
5144  else
5145  {
5146  if (object_get_status == OBJ_GET_WITHOUT_LOCK)
5147  {
5148  /* page not fixed, recdes was read without lock, object may have changed */
5149  object_get_status = OBJ_REPEAT_GET_WITH_LOCK;
5150  }
5151  else if (object_get_status == OBJ_REPEAT_GET_WITH_LOCK)
5152  {
5153  /* already read with lock, set flag to continue scanning next object */
5154  object_get_status = OBJ_GET_WITH_LOCK_COMPLETE;
5155  }
5156  }
5157 #endif
5158 
5159  if (lock_object (thread_p, &hsidp->curr_oid, &hsidp->cls_oid, lock, LK_UNCOND_LOCK) != LK_GRANTED)
5160  {
5161  return S_ERROR;
5162  }
5163 
5164  if (!heap_does_exist (thread_p, NULL, &hsidp->curr_oid))
5165  {
5166  /* not qualified, continue to the next tuple */
5167  lock_unlock_object_donot_move_to_non2pl (thread_p, &hsidp->curr_oid, &hsidp->cls_oid, lock);
5168  continue;
5169  }
5170 
5171  if (tran_isolation == TRAN_READ_COMMITTED && lock == S_LOCK)
5172  {
5173  /* release acquired lock in RC */
5174  lock_unlock_object_donot_move_to_non2pl (thread_p, &hsidp->curr_oid, &hsidp->cls_oid, lock);
5175  }
5176 
5177  assert (hsidp->scan_cache.page_watcher.pgptr == NULL);
5178 
5179  if (!VPID_ISNULL (&curr_vpid)
5180  && pgbuf_ordered_fix (thread_p, &curr_vpid, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_READ,
5181  &hsidp->scan_cache.page_watcher) != NO_ERROR)
5182  {
5183  return S_ERROR;
5184  }
5185 
5186  if (object_get_status == OBJ_REPEAT_GET_WITH_LOCK
5187  || (hsidp->scan_cache.page_watcher.pgptr != NULL
5188  && pgbuf_page_has_changed (hsidp->scan_cache.page_watcher.pgptr, &ref_lsa)))
5189  {
5190  is_peeking = COPY;
5191  COPY_OID (&hsidp->curr_oid, &retry_oid);
5192  goto restart_scan_oid;
5193  }
5194  }
5195  }
5196 
5197 
5198  scan_id->scan_stats.qualified_rows++;
5199 
5200  if (hsidp->rest_regu_list)
5201  {
5202  /* read the rest of the values from the heap into the attribute cache */
5203  if (heap_attrinfo_read_dbvalues (thread_p, p_current_oid, &recdes, &hsidp->scan_cache,
5204  hsidp->rest_attrs.attr_cache) != NO_ERROR)
5205  {
5206  return S_ERROR;
5207  }
5208 
5209  if (is_peeking == PEEK && hsidp->scan_cache.page_watcher.pgptr != NULL
5210  && pgbuf_page_has_changed (hsidp->scan_cache.page_watcher.pgptr, &ref_lsa))
5211  {
5212  is_peeking = COPY;
5213  COPY_OID (&hsidp->curr_oid, &retry_oid);
5214  goto restart_scan_oid;
5215  }
5216 
5217  /* fetch the rest of the values from the object instance */
5218  if (scan_id->val_list)
5219  {
5220  if (fetch_val_list (thread_p, hsidp->rest_regu_list, scan_id->vd, &hsidp->cls_oid, p_current_oid, NULL,
5221  PEEK) != NO_ERROR)
5222  {
5223  return S_ERROR;
5224  }
5225 
5226  if (is_peeking != 0 && hsidp->scan_cache.page_watcher.pgptr != NULL
5227  && pgbuf_page_has_changed (hsidp->scan_cache.page_watcher.pgptr, &ref_lsa))
5228  {
5229  is_peeking = COPY;
5230  COPY_OID (&hsidp->curr_oid, &retry_oid);
5231  goto restart_scan_oid;
5232  }
5233  }
5234  }
5235 
5236  if (hsidp->recordinfo_regu_list != NULL)
5237  {
5238  /* fetch the record info values */
5239  if (scan_id->val_list)
5240  {
5241  if (fetch_val_list (thread_p, hsidp->recordinfo_regu_list, scan_id->vd, &hsidp->cls_oid, p_current_oid,
5242  NULL, PEEK) != NO_ERROR)
5243  {
5244  return S_ERROR;
5245  }
5246 
5247  if (is_peeking == PEEK && hsidp->scan_cache.page_watcher.pgptr != NULL
5248  && pgbuf_page_has_changed (hsidp->scan_cache.page_watcher.pgptr, &ref_lsa))
5249  {
5250  is_peeking = COPY;
5251  COPY_OID (&hsidp->curr_oid, &retry_oid);
5252  goto restart_scan_oid;
5253  }
5254  }
5255  }
5256 
5257  return S_SUCCESS;
5258  }
5259 }
5260 
5261 /*
5262  * scan_next_heap_page_scan () - The scan is moved to the next page.
5263  *
5264  * return : Error code.
5265  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry.
5266  * scan_id (in) : Scan data.
5267  */
5268 static SCAN_CODE
5269 scan_next_heap_page_scan (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, SCAN_ID * scan_id)
5270 {
5271  HEAP_PAGE_SCAN_ID *hpsidp = NULL;
5272  FILTER_INFO data_filter;
5273  SCAN_CODE sp_scan;
5274  DB_LOGICAL ev_res;
5275 
5276  hpsidp = &scan_id->s.hpsid;
5277 
5278  scan_init_filter_info (&data_filter, &hpsidp->scan_pred, NULL, scan_id->val_list, scan_id->vd, &hpsidp->cls_oid, 0,
5279  NULL, NULL, NULL);
5280 
5281  while (true)
5282  {
5283  if (scan_id->direction == S_FORWARD)
5284  {
5285  /* move forward */
5286  sp_scan = heap_page_next (thread_p, &hpsidp->cls_oid, &hpsidp->hfid, &hpsidp->curr_vpid,
5287  hpsidp->cache_page_info);
5288  }
5289  else
5290  {
5291  /* move backward */
5292  sp_scan = heap_page_prev (thread_p, &hpsidp->cls_oid, &hpsidp->hfid, &hpsidp->curr_vpid,
5293  hpsidp->cache_page_info);
5294  }
5295 
5296  if (sp_scan != S_SUCCESS)
5297  {
5298  return (sp_scan == S_END) ? S_END : S_ERROR;
5299  }
5300 
5301  /* evaluate filter to see if the page qualifies */
5302  ev_res = eval_data_filter (thread_p, &hpsidp->cls_oid, NULL, NULL, &data_filter);
5303 
5304  if (ev_res == V_ERROR)
5305  {
5306  return S_ERROR;
5307  }
5308  else if (ev_res != V_TRUE)
5309  {
5310  /* V_FALSE || V_UNKNOWN */
5311  continue;
5312  }
5313 
5314  if (hpsidp->page_info_regu_list != NULL)
5315  {
5316  /* fetch the page info values */
5317  if (scan_id->val_list)
5318  {
5319  if (fetch_val_list (thread_p, hpsidp->page_info_regu_list, scan_id->vd, &hpsidp->cls_oid, NULL, NULL,
5320  PEEK) != NO_ERROR)
5321  {
5322  return S_ERROR;
5323  }
5324  }
5325  }
5326 
5327  return S_SUCCESS;
5328  }
5329 }
5330 
5331 /*
5332  * scan_next_class_attr_scan () - The scan is moved to the next class attribute scan item.
5333  * return: SCAN_CODE (S_SUCCESS, S_END, S_ERROR)
5334  * scan_id(in/out): Scan identifier
5335  *
5336  * Note: If there are no more scan items, S_END is returned. If an error occurs, S_ERROR is returned.
5337  */
5338 static SCAN_CODE
5339 scan_next_class_attr_scan (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, SCAN_ID * scan_id)
5340 {
5341  HEAP_SCAN_ID *hsidp;
5342  FILTER_INFO data_filter;
5343  DB_LOGICAL ev_res;
5344 
5345  hsidp = &scan_id->s.hsid;
5346 
5347  /* set data filter information */
5348  scan_init_filter_info (&data_filter, &hsidp->scan_pred, &hsidp->pred_attrs, scan_id->val_list, scan_id->vd,
5349  &hsidp->cls_oid, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL);
5350 
5351  if (scan_id->position == S_BEFORE)
5352  {
5353  /* Class attribute scans are always single row scan. */
5354  scan_id->position = S_AFTER;
5355 
5356  /* evaluate the predicates to see if the object qualifies */
5357  ev_res = eval_data_filter (thread_p, NULL, NULL, NULL, &data_filter);
5358  if (ev_res == V_ERROR)
5359  {
5360  return S_ERROR;
5361  }
5362 
5363  if (scan_id->qualification == QPROC_QUALIFIED)
5364  {
5365  if (ev_res != V_TRUE)
5366  { /* V_FALSE || V_UNKNOWN */
5367  return S_END; /* not qualified */
5368  }
5369  }
5370  else if (scan_id->qualification == QPROC_NOT_QUALIFIED)
5371  {
5372  if (ev_res != V_FALSE)
5373  { /* V_TRUE || V_UNKNOWN */
5374  return S_END; /* qualified */
5375  }
5376  }
5377  else if (scan_id->qualification == QPROC_QUALIFIED_OR_NOT)
5378  {
5379  if (ev_res == V_TRUE)
5380  {
5381  scan_id->qualification = QPROC_QUALIFIED;
5382  }
5383  else if (ev_res == V_FALSE)
5384  {
5385  scan_id->qualification = QPROC_NOT_QUALIFIED;
5386  }
5387  else /* V_UNKNOWN */
5388  {
5389  /* nop */
5390  ;
5391  }
5392  }
5393  else
5394  { /* invalid value; the same as QPROC_QUALIFIED */
5395  if (ev_res != V_TRUE)
5396  { /* V_FALSE || V_UNKNOWN */
5397  return S_END; /* not qualified */
5398  }
5399  }
5400 
5401  if (hsidp->rest_regu_list)
5402  {
5403  /* read the rest of the values from the heap into the attribute cache */
5404  if (heap_attrinfo_read_dbvalues (thread_p, NULL, NULL, NULL, hsidp->rest_attrs.attr_cache) != NO_ERROR)
5405  {
5406  return S_ERROR;
5407  }
5408 
5409  /* fetch the rest of the values from the object instance */
5410  if (scan_id->val_list)
5411  {
5412  if (fetch_val_list (thread_p, hsidp->rest_regu_list, scan_id->vd, &hsidp->cls_oid, NULL, NULL, PEEK) !=
5413  NO_ERROR)
5414  {
5415  return S_ERROR;
5416  }
5417  }
5418  }
5419 
5420  return S_SUCCESS;
5421  }
5422  else
5423  {
5424  /* Class attribute scans are always single row scan. */
5425  return S_END;
5426  }
5427 }
5428 
5429 /*
5430  * scan_next_index_scan () - The scan is moved to the next index scan item.
5431  * return: SCAN_CODE (S_SUCCESS, S_END, S_ERROR)
5432  * scan_id(in/out): Scan identifier
5433  *
5434  * Note: If there are no more scan items, S_END is returned. If an error occurs, S_ERROR is returned.
5435  */
5436 static SCAN_CODE
5437 scan_next_index_scan (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, SCAN_ID * scan_id)
5438 {
5439  INDX_SCAN_ID *isidp;
5440  FILTER_INFO data_filter;
5441  QFILE_TUPLE_RECORD tplrec = { NULL, 0 };
5442  SCAN_CODE lookup_status;
5443  TRAN_ISOLATION isolation;
5444 
5445  TSC_TICKS start_tick, end_tick;
5446  TSCTIMEVAL tv_diff;
5447 
5448  isidp = &scan_id->s.isid;
5449 
5450  assert (!OID_ISNULL (&isidp->cls_oid));
5451 
5452  /* multi range optimization safe guard : fall-back to normal output (OID list or covering index instead of "on the
5453  * fly" lists), if sorting column is not yet set at this stage; also 'grouped' is not supported */
5454  if (isidp->multi_range_opt.use && (isidp->multi_range_opt.sort_att_idx == NULL || scan_id->grouped))
5455  {
5456  isidp->multi_range_opt.use = false;
5457  scan_id->scan_stats.multi_range_opt = false;
5458  }
5459 
5460  /* set data filter information */
5461  scan_init_filter_info (&data_filter, &isidp->scan_pred, &isidp->pred_attrs, scan_id->val_list, scan_id->vd,
5462  &isidp->cls_oid, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL);
5463 
5464  /* Due to the length of time that we hold onto the oid list, it is possible at lower isolation levels (UNCOMMITTED
5465  * INSTANCES) that the index/heap may have changed since the oid list was read from the btree. In particular, some
5466  * of the instances that we are reading may have been deleted by the time we go to fetch them via heap_get_visible_version ().
5467  * According to the semantics of UNCOMMITTED, it is ok if they are deleted out from under us and we can ignore the
5468  * SCAN_DOESNT_EXIST error. */
5469 
5470  isolation = logtb_find_current_isolation (thread_p);
5471 
5472  while (1)
5473  {
5474  /* get next object from OID list */
5475  if (scan_id->grouped)
5476  {
5477  assert (isidp->oid_list != NULL);
5478  /* grouped scan */
5479  if (scan_id->direction == S_FORWARD)
5480  {
5481  /* move forward (to the next object) */
5482  if (isidp->curr_oidno == -1)
5483  {
5484  isidp->curr_oidno = 0; /* first oid number */
5485  isidp->curr_oidp = isidp->oid_list->oidp;
5486  }
5487  else if (isidp->curr_oidno < isidp->oids_count - 1)
5488  {
5489  isidp->curr_oidno++;
5490  isidp->curr_oidp++;
5491  }
5492  else
5493  {
5494  return S_END;
5495  }
5496  }
5497  else
5498  {
5499  /* move backward (to the previous object */
5500  if (isidp->curr_oidno == isidp->oids_count)
5501  {
5502  isidp->curr_oidno = isidp->oids_count - 1;
5503  isidp->curr_oidp = GET_NTH_OID (isidp->oid_list->oidp, isidp->curr_oidno);
5504  }
5505  else if (isidp->curr_oidno > 0)
5506  {
5507  isidp->curr_oidno--;
5508  isidp->curr_oidp = GET_NTH_OID (isidp->oid_list->oidp, isidp->curr_oidno);
5509  }
5510  else
5511  {
5512  return S_END;
5513  }
5514  }
5515  }
5516  else
5517  {
5518  /* non-grouped, regular index scan */
5519  if (scan_id->position == S_BEFORE)
5520  {
5521  SCAN_CODE ret;
5522 
5523  /* Either we are not using ISS, or we are using it, and in this case, we are supposed to be here for the
5524  * first time */
5525  assert_release (!isidp->iss.use || isidp->iss.current_op == ISS_OP_NONE);
5526 
5527  ret = call_get_next_index_oidset (thread_p, scan_id, isidp, true);
5528  if (ret != S_SUCCESS)
5529  {
5530  return ret;
5531  }
5532 
5533  if (isidp->need_count_only == true)
5534  {
5535  /* no more scan is needed. just return */
5536  return S_SUCCESS;
5537  }
5538 
5539  scan_id->position = S_ON;
5540  isidp->curr_oidno = 0; /* first oid number */
5541 
5542  if (SCAN_IS_INDEX_COVERED (isidp))
5543  {
5544  qfile_close_list (thread_p, isidp->indx_cov.list_id);
5545  if (qfile_open_list_scan (isidp->indx_cov.list_id, isidp->indx_cov.lsid) != NO_ERROR)
5546  {
5547  return S_ERROR;
5548  }
5549  }
5550  else
5551  {
5552  if (isidp->multi_range_opt.use)
5553  {
5554  assert (isidp->curr_oidno < isidp->multi_range_opt.cnt);
5555  assert (isidp->multi_range_opt.top_n_items[isidp->curr_oidno] != NULL);
5556 
5557  isidp->curr_oidp = &(isidp->multi_range_opt.top_n_items[isidp->curr_oidno]->inst_oid);
5558  }
5559  else
5560  {
5561  assert (isidp->oid_list != NULL);
5562  isidp->curr_oidp = GET_NTH_OID (isidp->oid_list->oidp, isidp->curr_oidno);
5563  }
5564  assert (HEAP_ISVALID_OID (thread_p, isidp->curr_oidp) != DISK_INVALID);
5565  }
5566  }
5567  else if (scan_id->position == S_ON)
5568  {
5569  int oids_cnt;
5570  /* we are in the S_ON case */
5571 
5572  oids_cnt = isidp->multi_range_opt.use ? isidp->multi_range_opt.cnt : isidp->oids_count;
5573 
5574  /* if there are OIDs left */
5575  if (isidp->curr_oidno < oids_cnt - 1)
5576  {
5577  isidp->curr_oidno++;
5578  if (!SCAN_IS_INDEX_COVERED (isidp))
5579  {
5580  if (isidp->multi_range_opt.use)
5581  {
5582  assert (isidp->curr_oidno < isidp->multi_range_opt.cnt);
5583  assert (isidp->multi_range_opt.top_n_items[isidp->curr_oidno] != NULL);
5584 
5585  isidp->curr_oidp = &(isidp->multi_range_opt.top_n_items[isidp->curr_oidno]->inst_oid);
5586  }
5587  else
5588  {
5589  assert (isidp->oid_list != NULL);
5590  isidp->curr_oidp = GET_NTH_OID (isidp->oid_list->oidp, isidp->curr_oidno);
5591  }
5592  assert (HEAP_ISVALID_OID (thread_p, isidp->curr_oidp) != DISK_INVALID);
5593  }
5594  else
5595  {
5596  /* TODO: Index covering case keeps OID's in isidp->indx_cov.list_id and not in isidp->oid_list.
5597  * Fall through. */
5598  }
5599  }
5600  else
5601  {
5602  /* there are no more OIDs left. Decide what to do */
5603 
5604  /* We can ignore the END OF SCAN signal if we're certain there can be more results, for instance if
5605  * we have a multiple range scan, or if we have the "index skip scan" optimization on */
5606  if (BTREE_END_OF_SCAN (&isidp->bt_scan) && isidp->indx_info->range_type != R_RANGELIST
5607  && isidp->indx_info->range_type != R_KEYLIST && !isidp->iss.use)
5608  {
5609  return S_END;
5610  }
5611  else
5612  {
5613  SCAN_CODE ret;
5614  bool go_to_next_iss_value;
5615 
5616  /* a list in a range is exhausted */
5617  if (isidp->multi_range_opt.use)
5618  {
5619  /* for "on the fly" case (multi range opt), all ranges are exhausted from first shoot, force
5620  * exit */
5621  isidp->oids_count = 0;
5622  return S_END;
5623  }
5624 
5625  if (SCAN_IS_INDEX_COVERED (isidp))
5626  {
5627  /* close current list and start a new one */
5628  qfile_close_scan (thread_p, isidp->indx_cov.lsid);
5629  qfile_destroy_list (thread_p, isidp->indx_cov.list_id);
5630  QFILE_FREE_AND_INIT_LIST_ID (isidp->indx_cov.list_id);
5631  isidp->indx_cov.list_id =
5632  qfile_open_list (thread_p, isidp->indx_cov.type_list, NULL, isidp->indx_cov.query_id, 0);
5633  if (isidp->indx_cov.list_id == NULL)
5634  {
5635  return S_ERROR;
5636  }
5637  }
5638  /* if this the current scan is not done (i.e. the buffer was full and we need to fetch more rows,
5639  * do not go to the next value */
5640  go_to_next_iss_value = BTREE_END_OF_SCAN (&isidp->bt_scan)
5641  && (isidp->indx_info->range_type == R_KEY || isidp->indx_info->range_type == R_RANGE);
5642  ret = call_get_next_index_oidset (thread_p, scan_id, isidp, go_to_next_iss_value);
5643  if (ret != S_SUCCESS)
5644  {
5645  return ret;
5646  }
5647 
5648  if (isidp->need_count_only == true)
5649  {
5650  /* no more scan is needed. just return */
5651  return S_SUCCESS;
5652  }
5653 
5654  isidp->curr_oidno = 0; /* first oid number */
5655  if (SCAN_IS_INDEX_COVERED (isidp))
5656  {
5657  qfile_close_list (thread_p, isidp->indx_cov.list_id);
5658  if (qfile_open_list_scan (isidp->indx_cov.list_id, isidp->indx_cov.lsid) != NO_ERROR)
5659  {
5660  return S_ERROR;
5661  }
5662  }
5663  else
5664  {
5665  assert (isidp->oid_list != NULL);
5666  isidp->curr_oidp = isidp->oid_list->oidp;
5667  assert (HEAP_ISVALID_OID (thread_p, isidp->curr_oidp) != DISK_INVALID);
5668  }
5669  }
5670  }
5671  }
5672  else if (scan_id->position == S_AFTER)
5673  {
5674  return S_END;
5675  }
5676  else
5677  {
5678  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_QPROC_UNKNOWN_CRSPOS, 0);
5679  return S_ERROR;
5680  }
5681  }
5682 
5683  assert (scan_id->position == S_ON);
5684 
5685  scan_id->scan_stats.key_qualified_rows++;
5686 
5687  /* get pages for read */
5688  if (!SCAN_IS_INDEX_COVERED (isidp))
5689  {
5690  perfmon_inc_stat (thread_p, PSTAT_BT_NUM_NONCOVERED);
5691 
5692  assert (isidp->curr_oidno >= 0);
5693  assert (isidp->curr_oidp != NULL);
5694  assert (HEAP_ISVALID_OID (thread_p, isidp->curr_oidp) != DISK_INVALID);
5695 
5696  if (thread_is_on_trace (thread_p))
5697  {
5698  tsc_getticks (&start_tick);
5699  }
5700 
5701  lookup_status = scan_next_index_lookup_heap (thread_p, scan_id, isidp, &data_filter, isolation);
5702 
5703  if (thread_is_on_trace (thread_p))
5704  {
5705  tsc_getticks (&end_tick);
5706  tsc_elapsed_time_usec (&tv_diff, end_tick, start_tick);
5707  TSC_ADD_TIMEVAL (scan_id->scan_stats.elapsed_lookup, tv_diff);
5708  }
5709 
5710  if (lookup_status == S_SUCCESS)
5711  {
5712  scan_id->scan_stats.data_qualified_rows++;
5713  }
5714  else if (lookup_status == S_DOESNT_EXIST)
5715  {
5716  if (scan_id->mvcc_select_lock_needed && isidp->key_limit_upper != -1)
5717  {
5718  isidp->key_limit_upper++;
5719  }
5720  /* not qualified, continue to the next tuple */
5721  continue;
5722  }
5723  else
5724  {
5725  /* S_ERROR, S_END */
5726  return lookup_status;
5727  }
5728  }
5729  else
5730  {
5731  /* TO DO - in MVCC when mvcc_select_lock_needed is true index coverage must be disabled */
5732  if (isidp->multi_range_opt.use)
5733  {
5734  assert (isidp->curr_oidno < isidp->multi_range_opt.cnt);
5735  assert (isidp->multi_range_opt.top_n_items[isidp->curr_oidno] != NULL);
5736 
5737  if (scan_dump_key_into_tuple (thread_p, isidp,
5738  &(isidp->multi_range_opt.top_n_items[isidp->curr_oidno]->index_value),
5739  isidp->curr_oidp, &isidp->multi_range_opt.tplrec) != NO_ERROR)
5740  {
5741  return S_ERROR;
5742  }
5743  tplrec.tpl = isidp->multi_range_opt.tplrec.tpl;
5744  tplrec.size = isidp->multi_range_opt.tplrec.size;
5745  }
5746  else
5747  {
5748  if (qfile_scan_list_next (thread_p, isidp->indx_cov.lsid, &tplrec, PEEK) != S_SUCCESS)
5749  {
5750  return S_ERROR;
5751  }
5752  }
5753 
5754  perfmon_inc_stat (thread_p, PSTAT_BT_NUM_COVERED);
5755 
5756  if (scan_id->val_list)
5757  {
5758  if (fetch_val_list (thread_p, isidp->indx_cov.regu_val_list, scan_id->vd, NULL, NULL, tplrec.tpl, PEEK) !=
5759  NO_ERROR)
5760  {
5761  return S_ERROR;
5762  }
5763  }
5764  }
5765 
5766  return S_SUCCESS;
5767  }
5768 }
5769 
5770 /*
5771  * scan_next_index_lookup_heap () - fetch heap record and evaluate data filter
5772  * return: SCAN_CODE (S_SUCCESS, S_END, S_ERROR, S_DOESNT_EXIST)
5773  * scan_id(in/out): Scan identifier
5774  * isidp(in/out): Index scan identifier
5775  * data_filter(in): data filter information
5776  * isolation(in): transaction isolation level
5777  *
5778  * Note: If the tuple is not qualified for data filter, S_DOESNT_EXIST is returned.
5779  */
5780 static SCAN_CODE
5781 scan_next_index_lookup_heap (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, SCAN_ID * scan_id, INDX_SCAN_ID * isidp,
5782  FILTER_INFO * data_filter, TRAN_ISOLATION isolation)
5783 {
5784  SCAN_CODE sp_scan;
5785  DB_LOGICAL ev_res;
5786  RECDES recdes;
5787  INDX_INFO *indx_infop;
5788  BTID *btid;
5789  char *indx_name_p;
5790  char *class_name_p;
5791  QFILE_TUPLE_RECORD tplrec = { NULL, 0 };
5792 
5793  assert (scan_id != NULL);
5794  assert (isidp != NULL);
5795  assert (isidp->curr_oidp != NULL && !OID_ISNULL (isidp->curr_oidp));
5796 
5797  if (scan_id->fixed == false)
5798  {
5799  recdes.data = NULL;
5800  }
5801 
5802  sp_scan = heap_get_visible_version (thread_p, isidp->curr_oidp, NULL, &recdes, &isidp->scan_cache, scan_id->fixed,
5803  NULL_CHN);
5804  if (sp_scan == S_SNAPSHOT_NOT_SATISFIED)
5805  {
5806  if (SCAN_IS_INDEX_COVERED (isidp))
5807  {
5808  /* goto the next tuple */
5809  if (!isidp->multi_range_opt.use)
5810  {
5811  if (qfile_scan_list_next (thread_p, isidp->indx_cov.lsid, &tplrec, PEEK) != S_SUCCESS)
5812  {
5813  return S_ERROR;
5814  }
5815  }
5816  }
5817 
5818  return S_DOESNT_EXIST; /* not qualified, continue to the next tuple */
5819  }
5820 
5821 
5822  /* evaluate the predicates to see if the object qualifies */
5823  ev_res = eval_data_filter (thread_p, isidp->curr_oidp, &recdes, &isidp->scan_cache, data_filter);
5824  if (isidp->key_pred.regu_list != NULL)
5825  {
5826  FILTER_INFO key_filter;
5827 
5828  scan_init_filter_info (&key_filter, &isidp->key_pred, &isidp->key_attrs, scan_id->val_list, scan_id->vd,
5829  &isidp->cls_oid, isidp->bt_num_attrs, isidp->bt_attr_ids, &isidp->num_vstr,
5830  isidp->vstr_ids);
5831  ev_res =
5832  update_logical_result (thread_p, ev_res, (int *) &scan_id->qualification, &key_filter, &recdes,
5833  isidp->curr_oidp);
5834  }
5835  else
5836  {
5837  ev_res = update_logical_result (thread_p, ev_res, (int *) &scan_id->qualification, NULL, NULL, NULL);
5838  }
5839  if (ev_res == V_ERROR)
5840  {
5841  return S_ERROR;
5842  }
5843  if (ev_res != V_TRUE)
5844  {
5845  return S_DOESNT_EXIST;
5846  }
5847 
5848  if (scan_id->mvcc_select_lock_needed)
5849  {
5850  FILTER_INFO range_filter, key_filter;
5851  MVCC_SCAN_REEV_DATA mvcc_sel_reev_data;
5852  MVCC_REEV_DATA mvcc_reev_data;
5853 
5854  /* initialize range and key filter, data filter already initialized */
5855  INIT_FILTER_INFO_FOR_SCAN_REEV (scan_id, &range_filter, &key_filter, NULL);
5856  /* init scan reevaluation structure */
5857  INIT_SCAN_REEV_DATA (&mvcc_sel_reev_data, &range_filter, &key_filter, data_filter, &scan_id->qualification);
5858  /* set reevaluation data */
5859  SET_MVCC_SELECT_REEV_DATA (&mvcc_reev_data, &mvcc_sel_reev_data, V_TRUE);
5860 
5861  sp_scan = locator_lock_and_get_object_with_evaluation (thread_p, isidp->curr_oidp, NULL, &recdes,
5862  &isidp->scan_cache, scan_id->fixed, NULL_CHN,
5863  &mvcc_reev_data, LOG_WARNING_IF_DELETED);
5864  if (sp_scan == S_SUCCESS)
5865  {
5866  switch (mvcc_reev_data.filter_result)
5867  {
5868  case V_ERROR:
5869  return S_ERROR;
5870  case V_FALSE:
5871  return S_DOESNT_EXIST;
5872  default:
5873  break;
5874  }
5875  }
5876  }
5877 
5878  if (sp_scan == S_DOESNT_EXIST || er_errid () == ER_HEAP_UNKNOWN_OBJECT)
5879  {
5880  er_clear ();
5881  if (SCAN_IS_INDEX_COVERED (isidp))
5882  {
5883  /* goto the next tuple */
5884  if (!isidp->multi_range_opt.use)
5885  {
5886  if (qfile_scan_list_next (thread_p, isidp->indx_cov.lsid, &tplrec, PEEK) != S_SUCCESS)
5887  {
5888  return S_ERROR;
5889  }
5890  }
5891  }
5892 
5893  return S_DOESNT_EXIST; /* not qualified, continue to the next tuple */
5894  }
5895 
5896  if (sp_scan != S_SUCCESS && sp_scan != S_SNAPSHOT_NOT_SATISFIED)
5897  {
5898  /* check end of scan */
5899  if (sp_scan == S_END)
5900  {
5901  assert (false); /* is impossible case */
5902  return S_END;
5903  }
5904 
5905  indx_infop = isidp->indx_info;
5906  btid = &indx_infop->btid;
5907  indx_name_p = NULL;
5908  class_name_p = NULL;
5909 
5910  /* check scan error */
5911  if (er_errid () == NO_ERROR)
5912  {
5913  (void) heap_get_indexinfo_of_btid (thread_p, &isidp->cls_oid, btid, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, &indx_name_p,
5914  NULL);
5915 
5916  if (heap_get_class_name (thread_p, &isidp->cls_oid, &class_name_p) != NO_ERROR)
5917  {
5918  /* ignore */
5919  er_clear ();
5920  }
5921 
5922  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_LC_INCONSISTENT_BTREE_ENTRY_TYPE2, 11,
5923  (indx_name_p) ? indx_name_p : "*UNKNOWN-INDEX*", (class_name_p) ? class_name_p : "*UNKNOWN-CLASS*",
5924  isidp->cls_oid.volid, isidp->cls_oid.pageid, isidp->cls_oid.slotid, isidp->curr_oidp->volid,
5925  isidp->curr_oidp->pageid, isidp->curr_oidp->slotid, btid->vfid.volid, btid->vfid.fileid,
5926  btid->root_pageid);
5927 
5928  if (class_name_p)
5929  {
5930  free_and_init (class_name_p);
5931  }
5932 
5933  if (indx_name_p)
5934  {
5935  free_and_init (indx_name_p);
5936  }
5937  }
5938 
5939  return S_ERROR;
5940  }
5941 
5942  if (!scan_id->mvcc_select_lock_needed && mvcc_is_mvcc_disabled_class (&isidp->cls_oid))
5943  {
5944  /* Data filter passed. If object should be locked and is not locked yet, lock it. */
5945  LOCK lock = NULL_LOCK;
5946  int tran_index = LOG_FIND_THREAD_TRAN_INDEX (thread_p);
5947  TRAN_ISOLATION tran_isolation = logtb_find_isolation (tran_index);
5948 
5949  if (scan_id->scan_op_type == S_DELETE || scan_id->scan_op_type == S_UPDATE)
5950  {
5951  lock = X_LOCK;
5952  }
5953  else if (oid_is_serial (&isidp->cls_oid))
5954  {
5955  /* S_SELECT is currently handled only for serial, but may be extended to the other non-MVCC classes if
5956  * needed */
5957  lock = S_LOCK;
5958  }
5959 
5960  if (lock != NULL_LOCK)
5961  {
5962  if (tran_isolation == TRAN_READ_COMMITTED && lock == S_LOCK)
5963  {
5964  if (lock_hold_object_instant (thread_p, isidp->curr_oidp, &isidp->cls_oid, lock) == LK_GRANTED)
5965  {
5966  lock = NULL_LOCK;
5967  }
5968  }
5969  else
5970  {
5971  if (lock_object (thread_p, isidp->curr_oidp, &isidp->cls_oid, lock, LK_COND_LOCK) == LK_GRANTED)
5972  {
5973  /* successfully locked */
5974  lock = NULL_LOCK;
5975  }
5976  }
5977  }
5978 
5979  if (lock != NULL_LOCK)
5980  {
5981  if (isidp->scan_cache.page_watcher.pgptr != NULL)
5982  {
5983  pgbuf_ordered_unfix (thread_p, &isidp->scan_cache.page_watcher);
5984  }
5985 
5986  if (lock_object (thread_p, isidp->curr_oidp, &isidp->cls_oid, lock, LK_UNCOND_LOCK) != LK_GRANTED)
5987  {
5988  return S_ERROR;
5989  }
5990 
5991  if (!heap_does_exist (thread_p, NULL, isidp->curr_oidp))
5992  {
5993  /* not qualified, continue to the next tuple */
5994  lock_unlock_object_donot_move_to_non2pl (thread_p, isidp->curr_oidp, &isidp->cls_oid, lock);
5995  return S_DOESNT_EXIST;
5996  }
5997 
5998  if (tran_isolation == TRAN_READ_COMMITTED && lock == S_LOCK)
5999  {
6000  /* release acquired lock in RC */
6001  lock_unlock_object_donot_move_to_non2pl (thread_p, isidp->curr_oidp, &isidp->cls_oid, lock);
6002  }
6003  }
6004  }
6005 
6006  if (isidp->rest_regu_list)
6007  {
6008  /* read the rest of the values from the heap into the attribute cache */
6009  if (heap_attrinfo_read_dbvalues (thread_p, isidp->curr_oidp, &recdes, &isidp->scan_cache,
6010  isidp->rest_attrs.attr_cache) != NO_ERROR)
6011  {
6012  return S_ERROR;
6013  }
6014 
6015  /* fetch the rest of the values from the object instance */
6016  if (scan_id->val_list)
6017  {
6018  if (fetch_val_list (thread_p, isidp->rest_regu_list, scan_id->vd, &isidp->cls_oid, isidp->curr_oidp, NULL,
6019  PEEK) != NO_ERROR)
6020  {
6021  return S_ERROR;
6022  }
6023  }
6024  }
6025 
6026  return S_SUCCESS;
6027 }
6028 
6029 /*
6030  * scan_next_index_key_info_scan () - Scans each key in index and obtains
6031  * information about that key.
6032  *
6033  * return : Scan code.
6034  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry.
6035  * scan_id (in) : Scan data.
6036  */
6037 static SCAN_CODE
6038 scan_next_index_key_info_scan (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, SCAN_ID * scan_id)
6039 {
6040  INDX_SCAN_ID *isidp = NULL;
6041  FILTER_INFO data_filter;
6042  SCAN_CODE sp_scan;
6043  DB_LOGICAL ev_res;
6044 
6045  isidp = &scan_id->s.isid;
6046 
6047  scan_init_filter_info (&data_filter, &isidp->scan_pred, NULL, scan_id->val_list, scan_id->vd, &isidp->cls_oid, 0,
6048  NULL, NULL, NULL);
6049 
6050  while (true)
6051  {
6052  sp_scan =
6053  btree_get_next_key_info (thread_p, &isidp->indx_info->btid, &isidp->bt_scan, 1, &isidp->cls_oid,
6054  isidp, isidp->key_info_values);
6055  if (sp_scan != S_SUCCESS)
6056  {
6057  return (sp_scan == S_END) ? S_END : S_ERROR;
6058  }
6059 
6060  ev_res = eval_data_filter (thread_p, NULL, NULL, NULL, &data_filter);
6061  if (ev_res == V_ERROR)
6062  {
6063  return S_ERROR;
6064  }
6065  else if (ev_res != V_TRUE)
6066  {
6067  /* V_FALSE || V_UNKNOWN */
6068  continue;
6069  }
6070 
6071  if (isidp->key_info_regu_list != NULL && scan_id->val_list != NULL)
6072  {
6073  if (fetch_val_list (thread_p, isidp->key_info_regu_list, scan_id->vd, &isidp->cls_oid, NULL, NULL, PEEK) !=
6074  NO_ERROR)
6075  {
6076  return S_ERROR;
6077  }
6078  }
6079 
6080  return S_SUCCESS;
6081  }
6082 }
6083 
6084 /*
6085  * scan_next_index_node_info_scan () - Scans for nodes in b-tree and obtains
6086  * information about the nodes.
6087  *
6088  * return : Scan code.
6089  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry.
6090  * scan_id (in) : Scan data.
6091  */
6092 static SCAN_CODE
6093 scan_next_index_node_info_scan (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, SCAN_ID * scan_id)
6094 {
6095  INDEX_NODE_SCAN_ID *insidp = NULL;
6096  FILTER_INFO data_filter;
6097  SCAN_CODE sp_scan;
6098  DB_LOGICAL ev_res;
6099 
6100  insidp = &scan_id->s.insid;
6101 
6102  scan_init_filter_info (&data_filter, &insidp->scan_pred, NULL, scan_id->val_list, scan_id->vd, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL,
6103  NULL);
6104 
6105  while (true)
6106  {
6107  sp_scan = btree_get_next_node_info (thread_p, &insidp->indx_info->btid, &insidp->btns, insidp->node_info_values);
6108  if (sp_scan != S_SUCCESS)
6109  {
6110  return (sp_scan == S_END) ? S_END : S_ERROR;
6111  }
6112 
6113  ev_res = eval_data_filter (thread_p, NULL, NULL, NULL, &data_filter);
6114  if (ev_res == V_ERROR)
6115  {
6116  return S_ERROR;
6117  }
6118  else if (ev_res != V_TRUE)
6119  {
6120  /* V_FALSE || V_UNKNOWN */
6121  continue;
6122  }
6123 
6124  if (insidp->node_info_regu_list != NULL && scan_id->val_list != NULL)
6125  {
6126  if (fetch_val_list (thread_p, insidp->node_info_regu_list, scan_id->vd, NULL, NULL, NULL, PEEK) != NO_ERROR)
6127  {
6128  return S_ERROR;
6129  }
6130  }
6131 
6132  return S_SUCCESS;
6133  }
6134 }
6135 
6136 /*
6137  * scan_next_list_scan () - The scan is moved to the next list scan item.
6138  * return: SCAN_CODE (S_SUCCESS, S_END, S_ERROR)
6139  * scan_id(in/out): Scan identifier
6140  *
6141  * Note: If there are no more scan items, S_END is returned. If an error occurs, S_ERROR is returned.
6142  */
6143 static SCAN_CODE
6144 scan_next_list_scan (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, SCAN_ID * scan_id)
6145 {
6146  LLIST_SCAN_ID *llsidp;
6147  SCAN_CODE qp_scan;
6148  DB_LOGICAL ev_res;
6149  QFILE_TUPLE_RECORD tplrec = { NULL, 0 };
6150 
6151  llsidp = &scan_id->s.llsid;
6152 
6153  tplrec.size = 0;
6154  tplrec.tpl = (QFILE_TUPLE) NULL;
6155 
6156  resolve_domains_on_list_scan (llsidp, scan_id->val_list);
6157 
6158  while ((qp_scan = qfile_scan_list_next (thread_p, &llsidp->lsid, &tplrec, PEEK)) == S_SUCCESS)
6159  {
6160 
6161  /* fetch the values for the predicate from the tuple */
6162  if (scan_id->val_list)
6163  {
6164  if (fetch_val_list (thread_p, llsidp->scan_pred.regu_list, scan_id->vd, NULL, NULL, tplrec.tpl, PEEK) !=
6165  NO_ERROR)
6166  {
6167  return S_ERROR;
6168  }
6169  }
6170 
6171  scan_id->scan_stats.read_rows++;
6172 
6173  /* evaluate the predicate to see if the tuple qualifies */
6174  ev_res = V_TRUE;
6175  if (llsidp->scan_pred.pr_eval_fnc && llsidp->scan_pred.pred_expr)
6176  {
