6177  ev_res = (*llsidp->scan_pred.pr_eval_fnc) (thread_p, llsidp->scan_pred.pred_expr, scan_id->vd, NULL);
6178  if (ev_res == V_ERROR)
6179  {
6180  return S_ERROR;
6181  }
6182  }
6183 
6184  if (scan_id->qualification == QPROC_QUALIFIED)
6185  {
6186  if (ev_res != V_TRUE) /* V_FALSE || V_UNKNOWN */
6187  {
6188  continue; /* not qualified, continue to the next tuple */
6189  }
6190  }
6191  else if (scan_id->qualification == QPROC_NOT_QUALIFIED)
6192  {
6193  if (ev_res != V_FALSE) /* V_TRUE || V_UNKNOWN */
6194  {
6195  continue; /* qualified, continue to the next tuple */
6196  }
6197  }
6198  else if (scan_id->qualification == QPROC_QUALIFIED_OR_NOT)
6199  {
6200  if (ev_res == V_TRUE)
6201  {
6202  scan_id->qualification = QPROC_QUALIFIED;
6203  }
6204  else if (ev_res == V_FALSE)
6205  {
6206  scan_id->qualification = QPROC_NOT_QUALIFIED;
6207  }
6208  else /* V_UNKNOWN */
6209  {
6210  /* nop */
6211  ;
6212  }
6213  }
6214  else
6215  { /* invalid value; the same as QPROC_QUALIFIED */
6216  if (ev_res != V_TRUE) /* V_FALSE || V_UNKNOWN */
6217  {
6218  continue; /* not qualified, continue to the next tuple */
6219  }
6220  }
6221 
6222  scan_id->scan_stats.qualified_rows++;
6223 
6224  /* fetch the rest of the values from the tuple */
6225  if (scan_id->val_list)
6226  {
6227  if (fetch_val_list (thread_p, llsidp->rest_regu_list, scan_id->vd, NULL, NULL, tplrec.tpl, PEEK) != NO_ERROR)
6228  {
6229  return S_ERROR;
6230  }
6231  }
6232 
6233  if (llsidp->tplrecp)
6234  {
6235  llsidp->tplrecp->size = tplrec.size;
6236  llsidp->tplrecp->tpl = tplrec.tpl;
6237  }
6238 
6239  return S_SUCCESS;
6240  }
6241 
6242  return qp_scan;
6243 }
6244 
6245 /*
6246  * scan_next_value_scan () - The scan is moved to the next value scan item.
6247  * return: SCAN_CODE (S_SUCCESS, S_END, S_ERROR)
6248  * scan_id(in/out): Scan identifier
6249  *
6250  * Note: If there are no more scan items, S_END is returned. If an error occurs, S_ERROR is returned.
6251  */
6252 static SCAN_CODE
6253 scan_next_value_scan (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, SCAN_ID * scan_id)
6254 {
6255  REGU_VALUES_SCAN_ID *rvsidp;
6256  REGU_VARIABLE_LIST list_node;
6257  REGU_VALUE_LIST *regu_value_list;
6258  int i;
6259 
6260  rvsidp = &scan_id->s.rvsid;
6261  if (scan_id->position == S_BEFORE)
6262  {
6263  scan_id->position = S_ON;
6264  }
6265  else if (scan_id->position == S_ON)
6266  {
6267  for (i = 0, list_node = rvsidp->regu_list; list_node; ++i, list_node = list_node->next)
6268  {
6269  regu_value_list = list_node->value.value.reguval_list;
6270  if (regu_value_list == NULL)
6271  {
6272  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_QPROC_INVALID_CRSPOS, 0);
6273  return S_ERROR;
6274  }
6275 
6276  assert (regu_value_list->current_value != NULL);
6277 
6278  regu_value_list->current_value = regu_value_list->current_value->next;
6279 
6280  if (regu_value_list->current_value == NULL)
6281  {
6282  scan_id->position = S_AFTER;
6283 
6284  if (i == 0)
6285  {
6286  return S_END;
6287  }
6288  else
6289  {
6290  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_QPROC_INVALID_CRSPOS, 0);
6291  return S_ERROR;
6292  }
6293  }
6294  }
6295  }
6296  else if (scan_id->position == S_AFTER)
6297  {
6298  return S_END;
6299  }
6300  else
6301  {
6302  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_QPROC_UNKNOWN_CRSPOS, 0);
6303  return S_ERROR;
6304  }
6305 
6306  return S_SUCCESS;
6307 }
6308 
6309 /*
6310  * scan_next_showstmt_scan () - The scan is moved to the next value scan item.
6311  * return: SCAN_CODE (S_SUCCESS, S_END, S_ERROR)
6312  * scan_id(in/out): Scan identifier
6313  *
6314  * Note: If there are no more scan items, S_END is returned. If an error occurs, S_ERROR is returned.
6315  */
6316 static SCAN_CODE
6317 scan_next_showstmt_scan (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, SCAN_ID * scan_id)
6318 {
6319  SHOWSTMT_SCAN_ID *stsidp;
6320  SCAN_CODE qp_scan;
6321  DB_LOGICAL ev_res;
6322 
6323  stsidp = &scan_id->s.stsid;
6324 
6325  if (scan_id->position == S_BEFORE)
6326  {
6327  scan_id->position = S_ON;
6328  }
6329 
6330  if (scan_id->position == S_ON)
6331  {
6332  while ((qp_scan = showstmt_next_scan (thread_p, scan_id)) == S_SUCCESS)
6333  {
6334  /* evaluate the predicate to see if the tuple qualifies */
6335  ev_res = V_TRUE;
6336  if (stsidp->scan_pred.pr_eval_fnc && stsidp->scan_pred.pred_expr)
6337  {
6338  ev_res = (*stsidp->scan_pred.pr_eval_fnc) (thread_p, stsidp->scan_pred.pred_expr, scan_id->vd, NULL);
6339  if (ev_res == V_ERROR)
6340  {
6341  return S_ERROR;
6342  }
6343  }
6344 
6345  if (scan_id->qualification == QPROC_QUALIFIED)
6346  {
6347  if (ev_res != V_TRUE) /* V_FALSE || V_UNKNOWN */
6348  {
6349  continue; /* not qualified, continue to the next tuple */
6350  }
6351  }
6352  else if (scan_id->qualification == QPROC_NOT_QUALIFIED)
6353  {
6354  if (ev_res != V_FALSE) /* V_TRUE || V_UNKNOWN */
6355  {
6356  continue; /* qualified, continue to the next tuple */
6357  }
6358  }
6359  else if (scan_id->qualification == QPROC_QUALIFIED_OR_NOT)
6360  {
6361  if (ev_res == V_TRUE)
6362  {
6363  scan_id->qualification = QPROC_QUALIFIED;
6364  }
6365  else if (ev_res == V_FALSE)
6366  {
6367  scan_id->qualification = QPROC_NOT_QUALIFIED;
6368  }
6369  else /* V_UNKNOWN */
6370  {
6371  /* nop */
6372  ;
6373  }
6374  }
6375  else
6376  { /* invalid value; the same as QPROC_QUALIFIED */
6377  if (ev_res != V_TRUE) /* V_FALSE || V_UNKNOWN */
6378  {
6379  continue; /* not qualified, continue to the next tuple */
6380  }
6381  }
6382 
6383  return S_SUCCESS;
6384  }
6385 
6386  }
6387  else if (scan_id->position == S_AFTER)
6388  {
6389  return S_END;
6390  }
6391  else
6392  {
6393  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_QPROC_UNKNOWN_CRSPOS, 0);
6394  return S_ERROR;
6395  }
6396 
6397  return qp_scan;
6398 }
6399 
6400 /*
6401  * scan_next_set_scan () - The scan is moved to the next set scan item.
6402  * return: SCAN_CODE (S_SUCCESS, S_END, S_ERROR)
6403  * scan_id(in/out): Scan identifier
6404  *
6405  * Note: If there are no more scan items, S_END is returned. If an error occurs, S_ERROR is returned.
6406  */
6407 static SCAN_CODE
6408 scan_next_set_scan (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, SCAN_ID * scan_id)
6409 {
6410  SET_SCAN_ID *ssidp;
6411  SCAN_CODE qp_scan;
6412  DB_LOGICAL ev_res;
6413  REGU_VARIABLE *func;
6414  REGU_VARIABLE_LIST ptr;
6415  int size;
6416 
6417  ssidp = &scan_id->s.ssid;
6418 
6419  /* if we are in the before position, fetch the set */
6420  if (scan_id->position == S_BEFORE)
6421  {
6422  func = ssidp->set_ptr;
6423  if (func->type == TYPE_FUNC && func->value.funcp->ftype == F_SEQUENCE)
6424  {
6425  size = 0;
6426  for (ptr = func->value.funcp->operand; ptr; ptr = ptr->next)
6427  {
6428  size++;
6429  }
6430  ssidp->operand = func->value.funcp->operand;
6431  ssidp->set_card = size;
6432  }
6433  else
6434  {
6435  pr_clear_value (&ssidp->set);
6436  if (fetch_copy_dbval (thread_p, ssidp->set_ptr, scan_id->vd, NULL, NULL, NULL, &ssidp->set) != NO_ERROR)
6437  {
6438  return S_ERROR;
6439  }
6440  }
6441  }
6442 
6443  /* evaluate set expression and put resultant set in DB_VALUE */
6444  while ((qp_scan = qproc_next_set_scan (thread_p, scan_id)) == S_SUCCESS)
6445  {
6446 
6447  assert (scan_id->val_list != NULL);
6448  assert (scan_id->val_list->val_cnt == 1);
6449 
6450  ev_res = V_TRUE;
6451  if (ssidp->scan_pred.pr_eval_fnc && ssidp->scan_pred.pred_expr)
6452  {
6453  ev_res = (*ssidp->scan_pred.pr_eval_fnc) (thread_p, ssidp->scan_pred.pred_expr, scan_id->vd, NULL);
6454  if (ev_res == V_ERROR)
6455  {
6456  return S_ERROR;
6457  }
6458  }
6459 
6460  if (scan_id->qualification == QPROC_QUALIFIED)
6461  {
6462  if (ev_res != V_TRUE) /* V_FALSE || V_UNKNOWN */
6463  {
6464  continue; /* not qualified, continue to the next tuple */
6465  }
6466  }
6467  else if (scan_id->qualification == QPROC_NOT_QUALIFIED)
6468  {
6469  if (ev_res != V_FALSE) /* V_TRUE || V_UNKNOWN */
6470  {
6471  continue; /* qualified, continue to the next tuple */
6472  }
6473  }
6474  else if (scan_id->qualification == QPROC_QUALIFIED_OR_NOT)
6475  {
6476  if (ev_res == V_TRUE)
6477  {
6478  scan_id->qualification = QPROC_QUALIFIED;
6479  }
6480  else if (ev_res == V_FALSE)
6481  {
6482  scan_id->qualification = QPROC_NOT_QUALIFIED;
6483  }
6484  else /* V_UNKNOWN */
6485  {
6486  /* nop */
6487  ;
6488  }
6489  }
6490  else
6491  { /* invalid value; the same as QPROC_QUALIFIED */
6492  if (ev_res != V_TRUE) /* V_FALSE || V_UNKNOWN */
6493  {
6494  continue; /* not qualified, continue to the next tuple */
6495  }
6496  }
6497 
6498  return S_SUCCESS;
6499 
6500  } /* while ((qp_scan = ) == S_SUCCESS) */
6501 
6502  return qp_scan;
6503 }
6504 
6505 /*
6506  * scan_next_method_scan () - The scan is moved to the next method scan item.
6507  * return: SCAN_CODE (S_SUCCESS, S_END, S_ERROR)
6508  * scan_id(in/out): Scan identifier
6509  *
6510  * Note: If there are no more scan items, S_END is returned. If an error occurs, S_ERROR is returned.
6511  */
6512 static SCAN_CODE
6513 scan_next_method_scan (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, SCAN_ID * scan_id)
6514 {
6515  VA_SCAN_ID *vaidp;
6516  SCAN_CODE qp_scan;
6517  VAL_LIST vl;
6518  QPROC_DB_VALUE_LIST src_valp;
6519  QPROC_DB_VALUE_LIST dest_valp;
6520 
6521  vaidp = &scan_id->s.vaid;
6522 
6523  /* execute method scan */
6524  qp_scan = method_scan_next (thread_p, &vaidp->scan_buf, &vl);
6525  if (qp_scan != S_SUCCESS)
6526  {
6527  /* scan error or end of scan */
6528  if (qp_scan == S_END)
6529  {
6530  scan_id->position = S_AFTER;
6531  return S_END;
6532  }
6533  else
6534  {
6535  return S_ERROR;
6536  }
6537  }
6538 
6539  /* copy the result into the value list of the scan ID */
6540  for (src_valp = vl.valp, dest_valp = scan_id->val_list->valp; src_valp && dest_valp;
6541  src_valp = src_valp->next, dest_valp = dest_valp->next)
6542  {
6543 
6544  if (DB_IS_NULL (src_valp->val))
6545  {
6546  pr_clear_value (dest_valp->val);
6547  }
6548  else if (DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (src_valp->val) != DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (dest_valp->val))
6549  {
6550  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_QPROC_INVALID_DATATYPE, 0);
6551  pr_clear_value (src_valp->val);
6552  free_and_init (src_valp->val);
6553  return S_ERROR;
6554  }
6555  else if (!qdata_copy_db_value (dest_valp->val, src_valp->val))
6556  {
6557  return S_ERROR;
6558  }
6559  pr_clear_value (src_valp->val);
6560  free_and_init (src_valp->val);
6561 
6562  }
6563 
6564  return S_SUCCESS;
6565 }
6566 
6567 /*
6568  * scan_handle_single_scan () -
6569  * return: SCAN_CODE (S_SUCCESS, S_END, S_ERROR)
6570  * scan_id(in/out): Scan identifier
6571  *
6572  * Note: This second order function applies the given next-scan function,
6573  * then enforces the single_fetch , null_fetch semantics.
6574  * Note that when "single_fetch", "null_fetch" is asserted, at least one
6575  * qualified scan item, the NULL row, is returned.
6576  */
6577 static SCAN_CODE
6578 scan_handle_single_scan (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, SCAN_ID * s_id, QP_SCAN_FUNC next_scan)
6579 {
6580  SCAN_CODE result = S_ERROR;
6581 
6582  if (s_id->scan_immediately_stop == true)
6583  {
6584  result = S_END;
6585  goto end;
6586  }
6587 
6588  switch (s_id->single_fetch)
6589  {
6590  case QPROC_NO_SINGLE_INNER:
6591  result = (*next_scan) (thread_p, s_id);
6592 
6593  if (result == S_ERROR)
6594  {
6595  goto exit_on_error;
6596  }
6597  break;
6598 
6599  case QPROC_SINGLE_OUTER:
6600  /* already returned a row? */
6601  /* if scan works in a single_fetch mode and first qualified scan item has already been fetched, return
6602  * end_of_scan. */
6603  if (s_id->single_fetched)
6604  {
6605  result = S_END;
6606  }
6607  else
6608  /* if it is known that scan has no qualified items, return the NULL row, without searching. */
6609  if (s_id->join_dbval && DB_IS_NULL (s_id->join_dbval))
6610  {
6611  qdata_set_value_list_to_null (s_id->val_list);
6612  s_id->single_fetched = true;
6613  result = S_SUCCESS;
6614  }
6615  else
6616  {
6617  result = (*next_scan) (thread_p, s_id);
6618 
6619  if (result == S_ERROR)
6620  {
6621  goto exit_on_error;
6622  }
6623 
6624  if (result == S_END)
6625  {
6626  qdata_set_value_list_to_null (s_id->val_list);
6627  result = S_SUCCESS;
6628  }
6629 
6630  s_id->single_fetched = true;
6631  }
6632  break;
6633 
6634  case QPROC_SINGLE_INNER: /* currently, not used */
6635  /* already returned a row? */
6636  /* if scan works in a single_fetch mode and first qualified scan item has already been fetched, return
6637  * end_of_scan. */
6638  if (s_id->single_fetched)
6639  {
6640  result = S_END;
6641  }
6642  /* if it is known that scan has no qualified items, return the NULL row, without searching. */
6643  else if (s_id->join_dbval && DB_IS_NULL (s_id->join_dbval))
6644  {
6645  result = S_END;
6646  }
6647  else
6648  {
6649  result = (*next_scan) (thread_p, s_id);
6650 
6651  if (result == S_ERROR)
6652  {
6653  goto exit_on_error;
6654  }
6655 
6656  if (result == S_SUCCESS)
6657  {
6658  s_id->single_fetched = true;
6659  }
6660  }
6661  break;
6662 
6663  case QPROC_NO_SINGLE_OUTER:
6664  /* already returned a NULL row? if scan works in a left outer join mode and a NULL row has already fetched,
6665  * return end_of_scan. */
6666  if (s_id->null_fetched)
6667  {
6668  result = S_END;
6669  }
6670  else
6671  {
6672  result = (*next_scan) (thread_p, s_id);
6673 
6674  if (result == S_ERROR)
6675  {
6676  goto exit_on_error;
6677  }
6678 
6679  if (result == S_END)
6680  {
6681  if (!s_id->single_fetched)
6682  {
6683  /* no qualified items, return a NULL row */
6684  qdata_set_value_list_to_null (s_id->val_list);
6685  s_id->null_fetched = true;
6686  result = S_SUCCESS;
6687  }
6688  }
6689 
6690  if (result == S_SUCCESS)
6691  {
6692  s_id->single_fetched = true;
6693  }
6694  }
6695  break;
6696  }
6697 
6698 end:
6699  /* maintain what is apparently supposed to be an invariant-- S_END implies position is "after" the scan */
6700  if (result == S_END)
6701  {
6702  if (s_id->direction != S_BACKWARD)
6703  {
6704  s_id->position = S_AFTER;
6705  }
6706  else
6707  {
6708  s_id->position = S_BEFORE;
6709  }
6710  }
6711 
6712  return result;
6713 
6714 exit_on_error:
6715 
6716  return S_ERROR;
6717 }
6718 
6719 /*
6720  * scan_next_scan () -
6721  * return: SCAN_CODE (S_SUCCESS, S_END, S_ERROR)
6722  * scan_id(in/out): Scan identifier
6723  */
6724 SCAN_CODE
6725 scan_next_scan (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, SCAN_ID * s_id)
6726 {
6727  return scan_handle_single_scan (thread_p, s_id, scan_next_scan_local);
6728 }

6730 /*
6731  * scan_prev_scan_local () - The scan is moved to the previous scan item.
6732  * return: SCAN_CODE (S_SUCCESS, S_END, S_ERROR)
6733  * scan_id(in/out): Scan identifier
6734  *
6735  * Note: If there are no more scan items, S_END is returned.
6736  * If an error occurs, S_ERROR is returned. This routine currently supports only LIST FILE scans.
6737  */
6738 static SCAN_CODE
6739 scan_prev_scan_local (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, SCAN_ID * scan_id)
6740 {
6741  LLIST_SCAN_ID *llsidp;
6742  SCAN_CODE qp_scan;
6743  DB_LOGICAL ev_res;
6744  QFILE_TUPLE_RECORD tplrec;
6745 
6746 
6747  switch (scan_id->type)
6748  {
6749  case S_LIST_SCAN:
6750  llsidp = &scan_id->s.llsid;
6751 
6752  tplrec.size = 0;
6753  tplrec.tpl = (QFILE_TUPLE) NULL;
6754 
6755  while ((qp_scan = qfile_scan_list_prev (thread_p, &llsidp->lsid, &tplrec, PEEK)) == S_SUCCESS)
6756  {
6757 
6758  /* fetch the values for the predicate from the tuple */
6759  if (scan_id->val_list)
6760  {
6761  if (fetch_val_list (thread_p, llsidp->scan_pred.regu_list, scan_id->vd, NULL, NULL, tplrec.tpl, PEEK) !=
6762  NO_ERROR)
6763  {
6764  return S_ERROR;
6765  }
6766  }
6767 
6768  /* evaluate the predicate to see if the tuple qualifies */
6769  ev_res = V_TRUE;
6770  if (llsidp->scan_pred.pr_eval_fnc && llsidp->scan_pred.pred_expr)
6771  {
6772  ev_res = (*llsidp->scan_pred.pr_eval_fnc) (thread_p, llsidp->scan_pred.pred_expr, scan_id->vd, NULL);
6773  if (ev_res == V_ERROR)
6774  {
6775  return S_ERROR;
6776  }
6777  }
6778 
6779  if (scan_id->qualification == QPROC_QUALIFIED)
6780  {
6781  if (ev_res != V_TRUE) /* V_FALSE || V_UNKNOWN */
6782  {
6783  continue; /* not qualified, continue to the next tuple */
6784  }
6785  }
6786  else if (scan_id->qualification == QPROC_NOT_QUALIFIED)
6787  {
6788  if (ev_res != V_FALSE) /* V_TRUE || V_UNKNOWN */
6789  {
6790  continue; /* qualified, continue to the next tuple */
6791  }
6792  }
6793  else if (scan_id->qualification == QPROC_QUALIFIED_OR_NOT)
6794  {
6795  if (ev_res == V_TRUE)
6796  {
6797  scan_id->qualification = QPROC_QUALIFIED;
6798  }
6799  else if (ev_res == V_FALSE)
6800  {
6801  scan_id->qualification = QPROC_NOT_QUALIFIED;
6802  }
6803  else /* V_UNKNOWN */
6804  {
6805  /* nop */
6806  ;
6807  }
6808  }
6809  else
6810  { /* invalid value; the same as QPROC_QUALIFIED */
6811  if (ev_res != V_TRUE) /* V_FALSE || V_UNKNOWN */
6812  {
6813  continue; /* not qualified, continue to the next tuple */
6814  }
6815  }
6816 
6817  /* fetch the rest of the values from the tuple */
6818  if (scan_id->val_list)
6819  {
6820  if (fetch_val_list (thread_p, llsidp->rest_regu_list, scan_id->vd, NULL, NULL, tplrec.tpl, PEEK) !=
6821  NO_ERROR)
6822  {
6823  return S_ERROR;
6824  }
6825  }
6826 
6827  if (llsidp->tplrecp)
6828  {
6829  llsidp->tplrecp->size = tplrec.size;
6830  llsidp->tplrecp->tpl = tplrec.tpl;
6831  }
6832  return S_SUCCESS;
6833 
6834  } /* while ((qp_scan = ...) == S_SUCCESS) */
6835  if (qp_scan == S_END)
6836  {
6837  scan_id->position = S_BEFORE;
6838  }
6839 
6840  return qp_scan;
6841 
6842  default:
6843  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_QPROC_INVALID_XASLNODE, 0);
6844  return S_ERROR;
6845  } /* switch (scan_id->type) */
6846 
6847 }

6850  * scan_prev_scan () - The scan is moved to the previous scan item.
6851  * return: SCAN_CODE (S_SUCCESS, S_END, S_ERROR)
6852  * scan_id(in/out): Scan identifier
6853  *
6854  * Note: If there are no more scan items, S_END is returned.
6855  * If an error occurs, S_ERROR is returned. This routine currently supports only LIST FILE scans.

6857 SCAN_CODE
6858 scan_prev_scan (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, SCAN_ID * s_id)

6860  return scan_handle_single_scan (thread_p, s_id, scan_prev_scan_local);

6865  * return:
6866  * scan_id(in/out): Scan identifier

6868  *
6869  * Note: This routine currently assumes only LIST FILE scans.

6880 /*
6881  * scan_jump_scan_pos () - Jump to the given scan position and move the scan
6882  * from that point on in the forward direction.
6883  * return: SCAN_CODE (S_SUCCESS, S_END, S_ERROR)
6884  * scan_id(in/out): Scan identifier
6885  * scan_pos(in/out): Set to contain current scan position
6886  *
6887  * Note: This routine currently assumes only LIST FILE scans.
6888  */
6889 SCAN_CODE
6890 scan_jump_scan_pos (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, SCAN_ID * s_id, SCAN_POS * scan_pos)
6891 {
6892  LLIST_SCAN_ID *llsidp;
6893  DB_LOGICAL ev_res;
6894  QFILE_TUPLE_RECORD tplrec;
6895  SCAN_CODE qp_scan;
6896 
6897  llsidp = &s_id->s.llsid;
6898 
6899  /* put back saved scan position */
6900  s_id->status = scan_pos->status;
6901  s_id->position = scan_pos->position;
6902 
6903  /* jump to the previouslt saved scan position and continue from that point on forward */
6904  tplrec.size = 0;
6905  tplrec.tpl = (QFILE_TUPLE) NULL;
6906 
6907  qp_scan = qfile_jump_scan_tuple_position (thread_p, &llsidp->lsid, &scan_pos->ls_tplpos, &tplrec, PEEK);
6908  if (qp_scan != S_SUCCESS)
6909  {
6910  if (qp_scan == S_END)
6911  {
6912  s_id->position = S_AFTER;
6913  }
6914  return qp_scan;
6915  }
6916 
6917  do
6918  {
6919  /* fetch the value for the predicate from the tuple */
6920  if (s_id->val_list)
6921  {
6922  if (fetch_val_list (thread_p, llsidp->scan_pred.regu_list, s_id->vd, NULL, NULL, tplrec.tpl, PEEK) !=
6923  NO_ERROR)
6924  {
6925  return S_ERROR;
6926  }
6927  }
6928 
6929  /* evaluate the predicate to see if the tuple qualifies */
6930  ev_res = V_TRUE;
6931  if (llsidp->scan_pred.pr_eval_fnc && llsidp->scan_pred.pred_expr)
6932  {
6933  ev_res = (*llsidp->scan_pred.pr_eval_fnc) (thread_p, llsidp->scan_pred.pred_expr, s_id->vd, NULL);
6934  if (ev_res == V_ERROR)
6935  {
6936  return S_ERROR;
6937  }
6938  }
6939 
6940  if (s_id->qualification == QPROC_QUALIFIED)
6941  {
6942  if (ev_res == V_TRUE)
6943  {
6944  /* nop */ ;
6945  }
6946  /* qualified, return it */
6947  }
6948  else if (s_id->qualification == QPROC_NOT_QUALIFIED)
6949  {
6950  if (ev_res == V_FALSE)
6951  {
6952  ev_res = V_TRUE; /* not qualified, return it */
6953  }
6954  }
6955  else if (s_id->qualification == QPROC_QUALIFIED_OR_NOT)
6956  {
6957  if (ev_res == V_TRUE)
6958  {
6959  s_id->qualification = QPROC_QUALIFIED;
6960  }
6961  else if (ev_res == V_FALSE)
6962  {
6963  s_id->qualification = QPROC_NOT_QUALIFIED;
6964  }
6965  else /* V_UNKNOWN */
6966  {
6967  /* nop */
6968  ;
6969  }
6970  ev_res = V_TRUE; /* return it */
6971  }
6972  else
6973  { /* invalid value; the same as QPROC_QUALIFIED */
6974  if (ev_res == V_TRUE)
6975  {
6976  /* nop */ ;
6977  }
6978  /* qualified, return it */
6979  }
6980 
6981  if (ev_res == V_TRUE)
6982  {
6983  /* fetch the rest of the values from the tuple */
6984  if (s_id->val_list)
6985  {
6986  if (fetch_val_list (thread_p, llsidp->rest_regu_list, s_id->vd, NULL, NULL, tplrec.tpl, PEEK) != NO_ERROR)
6987  {
6988  return S_ERROR;
6989  }
6990  }
6991 
6992  if (llsidp->tplrecp)
6993  {
6994  llsidp->tplrecp->size = tplrec.size;
6995  llsidp->tplrecp->tpl = tplrec.tpl;
6996  }
6997  return S_SUCCESS;
6998  }
6999 
7000  }
7001  while ((qp_scan = qfile_scan_list_next (thread_p, &llsidp->lsid, &tplrec, PEEK)) == S_SUCCESS);
7002 
7003  if (qp_scan == S_END)
7004  {
7005  s_id->position = S_AFTER;
7006  }
7007  return qp_scan;
7008 }
7009 
7010 /*
7011  * scan_initialize () - initialize scan management routine
7012  * return: NO_ERROR if all OK, ER status otherwise
7013  */
7014 int
7015 scan_initialize (void)
7016 {
7017  BTREE_ISCAN_OID_LIST *new_oid_list = NULL;
7018  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
7019  int i = 0;
7020 
7021  /* Initialize */
7022  scan_Iscan_oid_buf_list = NULL;
7023  scan_Iscan_oid_buf_list_count = 0;
7024 
7025  /* Allocate oid buffer list. */
7026  for (i = 0; i < SCAN_ISCAN_OID_BUF_LIST_DEFAULT_SIZE; i++)
7027  {
7028  /* Allocate new entry. */
7029  new_oid_list = NULL;
7030  error_code = scan_alloc_oid_list (&new_oid_list);
7031  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
7032  {
7033  ASSERT_ERROR ();
7034  /* Free what was already allocated. */
7035  scan_finalize ();
7036 
7037  /* Return error. */
7038  return error_code;
7039  }
7040  /* Safe guard. */
7041  assert (new_oid_list->oidp != NULL);
7042  assert (new_oid_list->capacity > 0);
7043 
7044  /* Save new buffer to buffer list. */
7045  new_oid_list->next_list = scan_Iscan_oid_buf_list;
7046  scan_Iscan_oid_buf_list = new_oid_list;
7047  scan_Iscan_oid_buf_list_count++;
7048  }
7049  /* Success. */
7050  return NO_ERROR;
7051 }
7052 
7053 /*
7054  * scan_finalize () - finalize scan management routine
7055  * return:
7056  */
7057 void
7058 scan_finalize (void)
7059 {
7060  BTREE_ISCAN_OID_LIST *oid_list_p;
7061 
7062  while (scan_Iscan_oid_buf_list != NULL)
7063  {
7064  /* Save current. */
7065  oid_list_p = scan_Iscan_oid_buf_list;
7066 
7067  /* Advance to next. */
7068  scan_Iscan_oid_buf_list = oid_list_p->next_list;
7069 
7070  /* Free current. */
7071  scan_free_oid_list (oid_list_p);
7072  }
7073 
7074  /* Reset count. */
7075  scan_Iscan_oid_buf_list_count = 0;
7076 }

7078 /*
7079  * reverse_key_list () - reverses the key list
7080  * return: number of keys, -1 for error
7081  * key_vals (in): pointer to array of KEY_VAL_RANGE structure
7082  * key_cnt (in): number of keys; size of key_vals
7083  */
7084 static int
7085 reverse_key_list (KEY_VAL_RANGE * key_vals, int key_cnt)
7086 {
7087  int i, j;
7088  KEY_VAL_RANGE temp;
7089 
7090  for (i = 0, j = key_cnt - 1; i < j; i++, j--)
7091  {
7092  temp = key_vals[i];
7093  key_vals[i] = key_vals[j];
7094  key_vals[j] = temp;
7095  }
7096 
7097  return key_cnt;
7098 }

7100 /*
7101  * resolve_domains_on_list_scan () - scans the structures in a list scan id
7102  * and resolves the domains in sub-components like regu variables from scan
7103  * predicates;
7104  *
7105  * llsidp (in/out): pointer to list scan id structure
7106  * ref_val_list (in): list of DB_VALUEs (VAL_LIST) used as reference
7107  *
7108  * Note : this function is used in context of HV late binding
7109  */
7110 static void
7111 resolve_domains_on_list_scan (LLIST_SCAN_ID * llsidp, VAL_LIST * ref_val_list)
7112 {
7113  REGU_VARIABLE_LIST scan_regu = NULL;
7114 
7115  assert (llsidp != NULL);
7116 
7117  if (llsidp->list_id == NULL || ref_val_list == NULL)
7118  {
7119  return;
7120  }
7121 
7122  /* resolve domains on regu_list of scan predicate */
7123  for (scan_regu = llsidp->scan_pred.regu_list; scan_regu != NULL; scan_regu = scan_regu->next)
7124  {
7125  if ((TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (scan_regu->value.domain) == DB_TYPE_VARIABLE
7126  || TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION_FLAG (scan_regu->value.domain)) && scan_regu->value.type == TYPE_POSITION)
7127  {
7128  int pos = scan_regu->value.value.pos_descr.pos_no;
7129  TP_DOMAIN *new_dom = NULL;
7130 
7131  assert (pos < llsidp->list_id->type_list.type_cnt);
7132  new_dom = llsidp->list_id->type_list.domp[pos];
7133 
7134  if (TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (new_dom) == DB_TYPE_VARIABLE
7135  || TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION_FLAG (new_dom) != TP_DOMAIN_COLL_NORMAL)
7136  {
7137  continue;
7138  }
7139 
7140  scan_regu->value.value.pos_descr.dom = new_dom;
7141  scan_regu->value.domain = new_dom;
7142  }
7143  }
7144 
7145  /* resolve domains on rest_regu_list of scan predicate */
7146  for (scan_regu = llsidp->rest_regu_list; scan_regu != NULL; scan_regu = scan_regu->next)
7147  {
7148  if ((TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (scan_regu->value.domain) == DB_TYPE_VARIABLE
7149  || TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION_FLAG (scan_regu->value.domain) != TP_DOMAIN_COLL_NORMAL)
7150  && scan_regu->value.type == TYPE_POSITION)
7151  {
7152  int pos = scan_regu->value.value.pos_descr.pos_no;
7153  TP_DOMAIN *new_dom = NULL;
7154 
7155  assert (pos < llsidp->list_id->type_list.type_cnt);
7156  new_dom = llsidp->list_id->type_list.domp[pos];
7157 
7158  if (TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (new_dom) == DB_TYPE_VARIABLE
7159  || TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION_FLAG (new_dom) != TP_DOMAIN_COLL_NORMAL)
7160  {
7161  continue;
7162  }
7163  scan_regu->value.value.pos_descr.dom = new_dom;
7164  scan_regu->value.domain = new_dom;
7165  }
7166  }
7167 
7168  /* resolve domains on predicate expression of scan predicate */
7169  if (llsidp->scan_pred.pred_expr == NULL)
7170  {
7171  return;
7172  }
7173 
7174  if (llsidp->scan_pred.pred_expr->type == T_EVAL_TERM)
7175  {
7176  EVAL_TERM ev_t = llsidp->scan_pred.pred_expr->pe.eval_term;
7177 
7178  if (ev_t.et_type == T_COMP_EVAL_TERM)
7179  {
7180  if (ev_t.et.et_comp.lhs != NULL
7181  && (TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (ev_t.et.et_comp.lhs->domain) == DB_TYPE_VARIABLE
7182  || TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION_FLAG (ev_t.et.et_comp.lhs->domain) != TP_DOMAIN_COLL_NORMAL))
7183  {
7184  resolve_domain_on_regu_operand (ev_t.et.et_comp.lhs, ref_val_list, &(llsidp->list_id->type_list));
7185  }
7186  if (ev_t.et.et_comp.rhs != NULL
7187  && (TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (ev_t.et.et_comp.rhs->domain) == DB_TYPE_VARIABLE
7188  || TP_DOMAIN_COLLATION_FLAG (ev_t.et.et_comp.rhs->domain) != TP_DOMAIN_COLL_NORMAL))
7189  {
7190  resolve_domain_on_regu_operand (ev_t.et.et_comp.rhs, ref_val_list, &(llsidp->list_id->type_list));
7191  }
7192  }
7193  }
7194 }
7195 
7196 /*
7197  * resolve_domain_on_regu_operand () - resolves a domain on a regu variable
7198  * from a scan list; helper functions for 'resolve_domains_on_list_scan'
7199  *
7200  * regu_var (in/out): regulator variable with unresolved domain
7201  * ref_val_list (in): list of DB_VALUEs (VAL_LIST) used for cross-checking
7202  * p_type_list (in): list of domains used as reference
7203  *
7204  * Note : this function is used in context of HV late binding
7205  */
7206 static void
7207 resolve_domain_on_regu_operand (REGU_VARIABLE * regu_var, VAL_LIST * ref_val_list,
7208  QFILE_TUPLE_VALUE_TYPE_LIST * p_type_list)
7209 {
7210  assert (regu_var != NULL);
7211  assert (ref_val_list != NULL);
7212 
7213  if (regu_var->type == TYPE_CONSTANT)
7214  {
7215  QPROC_DB_VALUE_LIST value_list;
7216  int pos = 0;
7217  bool found = false;
7218 
7219  /* search in ref_val_list for the corresponding DB_VALUE */
7220  for (value_list = ref_val_list->valp; value_list != NULL; value_list = value_list->next, pos++)
7221  {
7222  if (regu_var->value.dbvalptr == ref_val_list->valp->val)
7223  {
7224  found = true;
7225  break;
7226  }
7227  }
7228 
7229  if (found)
7230  {
7231  assert (pos < p_type_list->type_cnt);
7232  regu_var->domain = p_type_list->domp[pos];
7233  }
7234  }
7235 
7236 }

7238 /*
7239  * scan_init_multi_range_optimization () - initialize structure for multiple
7240  * range optimization
7241  *
7242  * return: error code
7243  *
7244  * multi_range_opt(in): multiple range optimization structure
7245  * use_range_opt(in): to use or not optimization
7246  * max_size(in): size of arrays for the top N values
7247  */
7248 static int
7249 scan_init_multi_range_optimization (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, MULTI_RANGE_OPT * multi_range_opt, bool use_range_opt,
7250  int max_size)
7251 {
7252  int err = NO_ERROR;
7253 
7254  if (multi_range_opt == NULL)
7255  {
7256  return ER_FAILED;
7257  }
7258 
7259  memset ((void *) (multi_range_opt), 0, sizeof (MULTI_RANGE_OPT));
7260  multi_range_opt->use = use_range_opt;
7261  multi_range_opt->cnt = 0;
7262 
7263  if (use_range_opt)
7264  {
7265  multi_range_opt->size = max_size;
7266  /* we don't have sort information here, just set an invalid value */
7267  multi_range_opt->sort_att_idx = NULL;
7268  multi_range_opt->is_desc_order = NULL;
7269  multi_range_opt->num_attrs = 0;
7270 
7271  multi_range_opt->top_n_items =
7272  (RANGE_OPT_ITEM **) db_private_alloc (thread_p, max_size * sizeof (RANGE_OPT_ITEM *));
7273  if (multi_range_opt->top_n_items == NULL)
7274  {
7275  err = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
7276  goto exit_on_error;
7277  }
7278  multi_range_opt->buffer = (RANGE_OPT_ITEM **) db_private_alloc (thread_p, max_size * sizeof (RANGE_OPT_ITEM *));
7279  if (multi_range_opt->buffer == NULL)
7280  {
7281  err = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
7282  goto exit_on_error;
7283  }
7284  memset (multi_range_opt->top_n_items, 0, max_size * sizeof (RANGE_OPT_ITEM *));
7285 
7286  multi_range_opt->tplrec.size = 0;
7287  multi_range_opt->tplrec.tpl = NULL;
7288 
7289  perfmon_inc_stat (thread_p, PSTAT_BT_NUM_MULTI_RANGE_OPT);
7290  }
7291 
7292  return err;
7293 
7294 exit_on_error:
7295 
7296  if (multi_range_opt->top_n_items != NULL)
7297  {
7298  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, multi_range_opt->top_n_items);
7299  }
7300  if (multi_range_opt->buffer != NULL)
7301  {
7302  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, multi_range_opt->buffer);
7303  }
7304 
7305  return err;
7306 }

7308 /*
7309  * scan_dump_key_into_tuple () - outputs the value stored in 'key' into the
7310  * tuple 'tplrec'
7311  *
7312  * return: error code
7313  * iscan_id(in):
7314  * key(in): MIDXKEY key (as it is retreived from index)
7315  * oid(in): oid (required if objects are stored in 'key')
7316  * tplrec(out):
7317  *
7318  * Note : this function is used by multiple range search optimization;
7319  * although not required here, the key should be a MIDXKEY value,
7320  * when multiple range search optimization is enabled.
7321  */
7322 static int
7323 scan_dump_key_into_tuple (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, INDX_SCAN_ID * iscan_id, DB_VALUE * key, OID * oid,
7324  QFILE_TUPLE_RECORD * tplrec)
7325 {
7326  int error;
7327  REGU_VARIABLE_LIST p;
7328 
7329  if (iscan_id == NULL || iscan_id->indx_cov.val_descr == NULL || iscan_id->indx_cov.output_val_list == NULL
7330  || iscan_id->rest_attrs.attr_cache == NULL)
7331  {
7332  return ER_FAILED;
7333  }
7334 
7335  error =
7336  btree_attrinfo_read_dbvalues (thread_p, key, iscan_id->bt_attr_ids, iscan_id->bt_num_attrs,
7337  iscan_id->rest_attrs.attr_cache, -1);
7338  if (error != NO_ERROR)
7339  {
7340  return error;
7341  }
7342 
7343  for (p = iscan_id->rest_regu_list; p; p = p->next)
7344  {
7345  pr_clear_value (p->value.vfetch_to);
7346  }
7347 
7348  error = fetch_val_list (thread_p, iscan_id->rest_regu_list, iscan_id->indx_cov.val_descr, NULL, oid, NULL, PEEK);
7349  if (error != NO_ERROR)
7350  {
7351  return error;
7352  }
7353 
7354  error =
7355  qdata_copy_valptr_list_to_tuple (thread_p, iscan_id->indx_cov.output_val_list, iscan_id->indx_cov.val_descr,
7356  tplrec);
7357 
7358  if (error != NO_ERROR)
7359  {
7360  return error;
7361  }
7362 
7363  return NO_ERROR;
7364 }
